)@@G@@    THIS SUBROUTINE PERFORMS ALL CHECKS FOR CORRECT FORMAT  @G@@@J.     GD
)@@G@@    OF QUESTIONS AND COPIES THE QUESTION TO THE BUFFER 'UQUES'.   @F@@@JGE

)@@G@@.     @G@@@J.         LOOK AT THE BEGINNING OF THE QUESTION AND SEE IF IGK
)@@G@@T IS ONE    @F@@@J.         OF THE MOST COMMONLY USED BEGINNINGS OF QUESGL
)@@G@@TIONS WHICH @G@@@J.         CANNOT BE ANSWERED YES OR NO.  SUCH QUESTIONGM

)@@G@@ BY PEOPLE WHO DON'T    @F@@@J.         COMPREHEND WHAT 'A QUESTION THATGO

)@@G@@.     @B@@@H.         TREE MANIPULATION FUNCTIONS     @[@@@H.     @[@@@HOR
)@@G@@.     @^@@@H.         CREATE NODE   @[@@@H.     @D@@@H.         LA,U    OS
)@@G@@  A0,<LENGTH OF TEXT IN CHARACTERS> @A@@@H.         LMJ       X11,MAKENOOT
)@@G@@DE    @G@@@H.         <RETURN>                      A1 = NODE ADDRESS (ROU
)@@G@@ELATIVE)    @[@@@H.     @F@@@H.         THIS SUBROUTINE ALLOCATES A MEMOOV
)@@G@@RY BUFFER FOR THE NODE, @F@@@H.         EXPANDING THE MEMORY IF NECESSAROW
)@@G@@Y.  THE NODE IS CHAINED @F@@@H.         INTO THE LIST OF NODES (LINKS NOOX
)@@G@@DEFL, NODEBKL).  THE    @F@@@H.         TEXT LENGTH IN CHARACTERS (NODELOY
)@@G@@EN) IS INITIALISED, AND @F@@@H.         THE NODE CREATOR INFORMATION (NOOZ
)@@G@@DEUID, NODEAC) IS FILLED@F@@@H.         IN.  THE FIELDS NODEYL, NODENL, PA
)@@G@@NODEBL, NODEREFC, AND   @A@@@H.         NODEBITS WILL BE ZEROED.  @[@@@HPB
)@@G@@.     @G@@@HMAKENODE  SA        A0,A5               SAVE TEXT LENGTH IN PC
)@@G@@CHARACTERS  @H@@@H          DSL       A0,36               SHIFT CHARACTEPD
)@@G@@R LENGTH FOR DIVIDE     @G@@@H          AA,U      A1,5                ROPE
)@@G@@UND UP FOR COVERED DIVIDE     @H@@@H          DI,U      A0,6            PF
)@@G@@    COMPUTE NODE TEXT LENGTH IN WORDS     @H@@@H          LA        A1,HPG
)@@G@@IGHUSE          LOAD ABSOLUTE ADDRESS OF NEW NODE     @G@@@H          AUPH
)@@G@@,U      A1,NODETEXT,A0      ADD TOTAL LENGTH OF NEW NODE    @F@@@H      PI
)@@G@@    TG        A2,HIGHCORE         NEED MEMORY BE EXPANDED ? @H@@@H      PJ
)@@G@@    LMJ       X4,NUFF             YES.  ALLOCATE ANOTHER MEMORY BLOCK   PK
)@@G@@@G@@@H          SA        A2,HIGHUSE          UPDATE NEXT AVAILABLE ADDRPL
)@@G@@ESS   @F@@@H          ANA,U     A1,MEMORY           MAKE NODE ADDRESS REPM
)@@G@@LATIVE@[@@@H.     @C@@@H.         INITIALISE FIELDS IN THE NEW NODE     PN
)@@G@@@[@@@H.     @F@@@H          SZ        M(NODELNK),A1       CLEAR YES AND PO
)@@G@@NO LINKS    @F@@@H          SA        A5,M(NODELEN),A1    SET TEXT LENGTPP
)@@G@@H IN NODE   @G@@@H          SZ        M(NODEREFC),A1      ZERO REFERENCEPQ
)@@G@@ COUNT ON NODE    @G@@@H          SZ        M(NODEBL),A1        CLEAR QUPR
)@@G@@ESTION LINK IN NODE     @E@@@H          SZ        M(NODEBITS),A1      CLPS
)@@G@@EAR NODE TYPE BITS@[@@@H.     @B@@@H.         ATTACH NODE TO LINEAR NODEPT
)@@G@@ LIST @[@@@H.     @G@@@H          LA        A0,M(NODEBKL)       LOAD LINPU
)@@G@@K TO LAST NODE IN LIST  @G@@@H          SA        A0,M(NODEBKL),A1    SEPV
)@@G@@T AS PREDECESSOR TO NEW NODE  @E@@@H          SA        A1,M(NODEBKL)   PW
)@@G@@    SET NEW NODE AS LAST@H@@@H          SA        A1,M(NODEFL),A0     SEPX
)@@G@@T NEW NODE AS SUCCESSOR TO PREVIOUS @H@@@H          SZ        M(NODEFL),PY
)@@G@@A1        MARK HEAD AS SUCCESSOR TO NEW NODE    @[@@@H.     @G@@@H      PZ
)@@G@@    LA        A0,USERID           LOAD USERID FOR CURRENT USER    @F@@@HQA
)@@G@@          SA        A0,M(NODEUID),A1    SET USERID OF CREATOR     @F@@@HQB
)@@G@@          DL        A4,ACCOUNT          LOAD ACCOUNT OF CREATOR   @G@@@HQC
)@@G@@          DS        A4,M(NODEAC),A1     SET CREATOR'S ACCOUNT IN NODE   QD
)@@G@@@E@@@H          J         0,X11               RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@HQE
)@@G@@.     @^@@@H.         DELETE ANIMAL @[@@@H.     @C@@@H.         LA,U    QF
)@@G@@  A0,<ANIMAL NODE>  (RELATIVE)@A@@@H.         LMJ       X4,DELANIMAL    QG
)@@G@@@#@@@H.         <RETURN>@[@@@H.     @G@@@HDELANIMAL TZ        M(NODELNK)QH
)@@G@@,A0       CALLED DELANIMAL ON A QUESTION ?@F@@@H          ERR$      .   QI
)@@G@@                YES.  BETTER TAKE A DUMP  @F@@@H          LA        A1,MQJ
)@@G@@(NODEBITS),A0   LOAD MODE BITS FOR NODE   @F@@@H          OR,U      A1,NQK
)@@G@@BDEL            MARK THE NODE DELETED     @G@@@H          SA        A2,MQL
)@@G@@(NODEBITS),A0   SET DELETE BIT IN NODE BITS     @G@@@H          LA      QM
)@@G@@  A1,M(NODEBL),A0     LOAD LINK TO PREVIOUS QUESTION  @G@@@H          LAQN
)@@G@@        A3,M(NODEYL),A1     LOAD YES LINK FROM QUESTION     @G@@@H      QO
)@@G@@    TNE       A3,A0               IS YES LINK TO DELETED ANIMAL ? @F@@@HQP
)@@G@@          LA        A3,M(NODENL),A1     YES.  TAKE THE NO LINK    @H@@@HQQ
)@@G@@          TNE       A1,BASENODE         IS PREVIOUS QUESTION THE BASE NOQR
)@@G@@DE ?  @H@@@H          J         DELBN               YES.  WE WILL HAVE AQS
)@@G@@ NEW BASE NODE    @G@@@H          LA        A2,M(NODEBL),A1     LOAD NODQT
)@@G@@E PRIOR TO QUESTION NODE@G@@@H          TNE       A1,M(NODEYL),A2     WAQU
)@@G@@S QUESTION OFF YES LINK ?     @F@@@H          SA        A3,M(NODEYL),A2 QV
)@@G@@    YES.  UPDATE YES LINK     @F@@@H          TNE       A1,M(NODENL),A2 QW
)@@G@@    WAS QUESTION OFF NO LINK ?@H@@@H          SA        A3,M(NODENL),A2 QX
)@@G@@    YES.  ATTACH REMAINDER TO NO LINK     @H@@@H          SA        A2,MQY
)@@G@@(NODEBL),A3     UPDATE BACK LINK IN REMAINING CHAIN   @F@@@HDELASF    LAQZ
)@@G@@        A2,M(NODEBITS),A1   LOAD BITS FROM QUESTION   @F@@@H          ORRA
)@@G@@,U      A2,NBDEL            MARK THE QUESTION DELETED @G@@@H          SARB
)@@G@@        A3,M(NODEBITS),A1   SET DELETE FLAG IN QUESTION NODE@D@@@H      RC
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,1                LOAD A ONE    @G@@@H          SA      RD
)@@G@@  A2,NEEDPACK         MARK 'TREE NEEDS TO BE PACKED'  @A@@@H          ONRE
)@@G@@        MAINTENANCE     @F@@@H          TNZ       MAINT               INRF
)@@G@@ MAINTENANCE MODE ?     @H@@@H          J         MMDAN               NORG
)@@G@@.  SKIP LOGGING OF DELETED QUESTION @F@@@H          SX        X8,A5     RH
)@@G@@          SAVE CURRENT NODE POINTER @G@@@H          LX        X8,A1     RI
)@@G@@          LOAD POINTER TO DELETED QUESTION@F@@@H          F$MSG     ALSDRJ
)@@G@@EL              EDIT 'ALSO DELETED:  '    @E@@@H          SX        X4,ARK
)@@G@@4               SAVE CALL ADDRESS   @G@@@H          LMJ       X4,RELADR RL
)@@G@@          EDIT ADDRESS OF DELETED NODE    @F@@@H          LX        X4,ARM
)@@G@@4               RELOAD THE CALL ADDRESS   @F@@@H          LA,U      A0,MRN
)@@G@@(NODETEXT),X8   LOAD QUESTION TEXT ADDRESS@F@@@H          LA        A1,MRO
)@@G@@(NODELEN),X8    LOAD LENGTH OF QUESTION   @F@@@H          F$COPY    .   RP
)@@G@@                COPY DELETED QUESTION     @G@@@H          LX        X8,ARQ
)@@G@@5               RELOAD CURRENT NODE POINTER     @E@@@H          F$CHAR  RR
)@@G@@  '?'                 EDIT QUESTION MARK  @F@@@H          F$PRT     1   RS
)@@G@@                PRINT THE DELETED QUESTION@A@@@HMMDAN     OFF       MAINRT
)@@G@@TENANCE     @E@@@H          J         0,X4                RETURN TO CALLRU
)@@G@@ER    @[@@@H.     @B@@@H.         HANDLE DELETION OF BASE NODE    @[@@@HRV
)@@G@@.     @H@@@HDELBN     SA        A3,BASENODE         SET REMAINDER CHAIN RW
)@@G@@HEAD AS BASE NODE @H@@@H          SZ        M(NODEBL),A3        MARK REMRX
)@@G@@AINDER CHAIN WITH NO BACK LINK@H@@@H          J         DELASF          RY
)@@G@@    GO SET DELETE FLAG IN OLD BASE NODE   @[@@@H.     @[@@@H.     @^@@@HRZ
)@@G@@.         DELETE SUBTREE@[@@@H.     @C@@@H.         LA,U      A0,<BASE NSA
)@@G@@ODE OF SUBTREE>   @ @@@H.         LMJ       X4,DELTREE@#@@@H.         <RSB
)@@G@@ETURN>@[@@@H.     @G@@@H.         ALL NONZERO LINKS OF THE DESIGNATED SUSC
)@@G@@BTREE WILL BE FOLLOWED  @G@@@H.         AND THE DELETE BIT WILL BE SET FSD
)@@G@@OR EACH NODE ENCOUNTERED.     @[@@@H.     @A@@@H          ON        MAINSE
)@@G@@TENANCE     @G@@@HDELTREE   LA        A1,A0               SET RUNNING POSF
)@@G@@INTER TO BASE NODE@E@@@H          SX        X4,A4               SAVE CALSG
)@@G@@L ADDRESS   @E@@@H          SX        X8,A5               SAVE ORIGINAL SH
)@@G@@X8    @F@@@H          SA        A0,A6               SAVE BASE NODE POINTSI
)@@G@@ER    @F@@@HDELTFL    TNZ       M(NODELNK),A1       IS THIS A LEAF NODE SJ
)@@G@@?     @F@@@H          J         DELTLEAF            YES.  DELETE A LEAF SK
)@@G@@NODE  @G@@@H          TZ        M(NODENL),A1        DOES NODE HAVE A 'NOSL
)@@G@@' LINK ?    @F@@@H          LA        A1,M(NODENL),A1     YES.  ADVANCE SM
)@@G@@UP NO LINK  @G@@@H          TZ        M(NODEYL),A1        DOES THIS (OR SN
)@@G@@NEXT) NODE HAVE A @D@@@H.                                       YES LINKSO
)@@G@@ ?    @F@@@H          LA        A1,M(NODEYL),A1     YES.  ADVANCE UP YESSP
)@@G@@ LINK @G@@@H          J         DELTFL              LOOP LOOKING FOR ENDSQ
)@@G@@ OF TREE    @[@@@H.     @F@@@HDELTLEAF  LA        A2,M(NODEBITS),A1   LOSR
)@@G@@AD NODE STATUS BITS     @F@@@H          OR,U      A2,NBDEL            MASS
)@@G@@RK THIS NODE DELETED    @F@@@H          SA        A3,M(NODEBITS),A1   SEST
)@@G@@T DELETE BIT IN NODE    @H@@@H          TNE       A1,A6               JUSU
)@@G@@ST DELETED BASE NODE OF SUB-TREE ?  @F@@@H          J         DELTDONE  SV
)@@G@@          YES.  SUB TREE ALL DELETED@G@@@H          F$MSG     ALSDEL    SW
)@@G@@          EDIT 'ALSO DELETED' MESSAGE     @F@@@H          LX        X8,ASX
)@@G@@1               LOAD CURRENT NODE POINTER @G@@@H          LMJ       X4,RSY
)@@G@@ELADR           EDIT RELATIVE ADDRESS OF NODE   @F@@@H          LA,U    SZ
)@@G@@  A0,M(NODETEXT),X8   LOAD NODE TEXT ADDRESS    @F@@@H          LA      TA
)@@G@@  A1,M(NODELEN),X8    LOAD LENGTH OF NODE TEXT  @E@@@H          F$COPY  TB
)@@G@@  .                   COPY THE NODE TEXT  @F@@@H          F$PRT     1   TC
)@@G@@                PRINT THE DELETED ITEM    @G@@@H          LA        A1,XTD
)@@G@@8               RESTORE CURRENT NODE POINTER    @F@@@H          LA      TE
)@@G@@  A2,M(NODEBL),A1     LOAD LINK TO PREVIOUS NODE@F@@@H          TNE     TF
)@@G@@  A1,M(NODENL),A2     CHAINED OFF 'NO' LINK ?   @E@@@H          SZ      TG
)@@G@@  M(NODENL),A2        YES.  CLEAR NO LINK @F@@@H          TNE       A1,MTH
)@@G@@(NODEYL),A2     CHAINED OFF 'YES' LINK ?  @F@@@H          SZ        M(NOTI
)@@G@@DEYL),A2        YES.  CLEAR THE YES LINK  @G@@@H          LA        A1,ATJ
)@@G@@2               LOAD ADDRESS OF PREVIOUS NODE   @F@@@H          J       TK
)@@G@@  DELTFL              LOOP DELETING SUB TREE    @[@@@H.     @D@@@HDELTDOTL
)@@G@@NE  LA,U      A1,1                LOAD A ONE    @G@@@H          SA      TM
)@@G@@  A1,NEEDPACK         MARK TREE NEEDS TO BE PACKED    @E@@@H          LXTN
)@@G@@        X4,A4               RESTORE CALL ADDRESS@G@@@H          LX      TO
)@@G@@  X8,A5               RELOAD CURRENT NODE POINTER     @D@@@H          J TP
)@@G@@        0,X4                RETURN TO CALL@[@@@H.     @[@@@H.     @B@@@HTQ
)@@G@@.         PACK DELETED NODE FROM TREE     @[@@@H.     @ @@@H.         LMTR
)@@G@@J       X4,PACK   @#@@@H.         <RETURN>@[@@@H.     @G@@@HP         PRTS
)@@G@@OC      1                   ADJUST A LINK TO NEW ADDRESSING @^@@@HADJUSTTT
)@@G@@*   NAME      0   @G@@@H          LA        A3,P(1,1),P(1,2)    LOAD ADDTU
)@@G@@RESS TO BE ADJUSTED     @F@@@H          TG        A3,X1               ISTV
)@@G@@ IT ABOVE DELETED NODE ?@H@@@H          ANA       A3,A2               YETW
)@@G@@S.  SUBTRACT LENGTH OF DELETED ITEM @G@@@H          SA        A3,P(1,1),TX
)@@G@@P(1,2)    STORE THE ADJUSTED ADDRESS BACK @^@@@H          END       .   TY
)@@G@@@[@@@H.     @F@@@HPACK      SZ        NEEDPACK            CLEAR PACK STITZ
)@@G@@LL NEEDED   @F@@@HPACK1     LX,U      X1                  CLEAR CURRENT UA
)@@G@@NODE POINTER@[@@@H.     @F@@@HPKNEXT    LX        X1,M(NODEFL),X1     LOUB
)@@G@@AD LINK TO NEXT NODE    @D@@@H          TNZ       X1                  ENUC
)@@G@@D OF TREE ? @F@@@H          J         0,X4                YES.  PACK IS UD
)@@G@@NOW COMPLETE@G@@@H          LA        A0,M(NODEBITS),X1   LOAD STATUS BIUE
)@@G@@TS FOR THIS NODE  @F@@@H          TOP,U     A0,NBDEL            IS THIS UF
)@@G@@NODE DELETED ?    @F@@@H          J         PKNEXT              NO.  LOOUG
)@@G@@K AT THE NEXT NODE@F@@@H          LA        A0,M(NODEFL),X1     LOAD LINUH
)@@G@@K TO NEXT NODE    @F@@@H          LA        A1,M(NODEBKL),X1    LOAD LINUI
)@@G@@K TO PREVIOUS NODE@H@@@H          SA        A0,M(NODEFL),A1     ATTACH NUJ
)@@G@@EXT NODE TO PREVIOUS NODE     @H@@@H          SA        A1,M(NODEBKL),A0UK
)@@G@@    ATTACH PREVIOUS NODE TO NEXT NODE     @G@@@H          LA        A2,MUL
)@@G@@(NODELEN),X1    LOAD LENGTH OF DELETED NODE     @F@@@H          DSL     UM
)@@G@@  A2,36               SHIFT DOWN FOR DIVIDE     @G@@@H          AA,U    UN
)@@G@@  A3,5                ROUND UP FOR COVERED DIVIDE     @G@@@H          DIUO
)@@G@@,U      A2,6                COMPUTE WORDS OF TEXT IN ITEM   @E@@@H      UP
)@@G@@    AA,U      A2,NODETEXT         ADD LENGTH OF HEADER@G@@@H          LXUQ
)@@G@@        X2,M(NODEFL)        LOAD LINK TO FIRST NODE IN TREE @[@@@H.     UR
)@@G@@@D@@@H.         ADJUST ALL ADDRESSES ABOVE THE DELETED ITEM @[@@@H.     US
)@@G@@@D@@@HPKADNX    TNZ       X2                  END OF TREE ? @H@@@H      UT
)@@G@@    J         PKADJD              YES.  ADDRESS ADJUSTMENT COMPLETE     UU
)@@G@@@H@@@H          LA        A4,M(NODEFL),X2     LOAD ORIGINAL FORWARD LINKUV
)@@G@@ FOR NODE   @F@@@H.                                       (ADJUSTMENT MAUW
)@@G@@Y CHANGE IT)@F@@@H          ADJUST    M(NODEYL),X2        ADJUST YES LINUX
)@@G@@K FROM NODE @F@@@H          ADJUST    M(NODENL),X2        ADJUST THE NO UY
)@@G@@LINK, ALSO  @F@@@H          ADJUST    M(NODEBL),X2        FIX THE QUESTIUZ
)@@G@@ON LINK     @F@@@H          ADJUST    M(NODEFL),X2        ADJUST THE FORVA
)@@G@@WARD LINK   @F@@@H          ADJUST    M(NODEBKL),X2       ADJUST THE BACVB
)@@G@@KWARD LINK  @F@@@H          LX        X2,A4               LOAD LINK TO TVC
)@@G@@HE NEXT NODE@F@@@H          J         PKADNX              GO ADJUST THE VD
)@@G@@NEXT NODE   @[@@@H.     @F@@@HPKADJD    ADJUST    BASENODE            FIVE
)@@G@@X THE BASE NODE ADDRESS @F@@@H          ADJUST    M(NODEFL)           FIVF
)@@G@@X THE HEAD FORWARD LINK @G@@@H          ADJUST    M(NODEBKL)          FIVG
)@@G@@X THE LINK TO THE LAST NODE   @H@@@H          LA        A0,(1,0)        VH
)@@G@@    LOAD POINTER TO COMPRESS THE TREE     @G@@@H          AA,U      A0,,VI
)@@G@@X1              COMPUTE OFFSET OF DELETED NODE  @I@@@H          AU,U    VJ
)@@G@@  A0,,A2              START OF TREE ABOVE NODE TO BE COMPRESSED   @F@@@HVK
)@@G@@          LA        A3,HIGHUSE          LOAD HIGHEST WORD IN USE  @H@@@HVL
)@@G@@          ANA,U     A3,MEMORY,A1        A3 = NUMBER OF WORDS ABOVE THE GVM
)@@G@@AP    @H@@@H          SA        A3,R1               SET AS COUNT FOR TREVN
)@@G@@E COMPRESSION     @I@@@H          BT        A0,MEMORY,*A1       SQUEEZE VO
)@@G@@THE DELETED ITEM OUT OF THE TREE    @G@@@H          ANA       A2,HIGHUSEVP
)@@G@@          COMPUTE -(HIGHEST WORD IN USE)  @F@@@H          SNA       A2,HVQ
)@@G@@IGHUSE          UPDATE HIGHEST WORD IN USE@G@@@H          J         PACKVR
)@@G@@1               LOOK FOR MORE DELETED NODES     @[@@@H/.    @[@@@H.     VS
)@@G@@@[@@@H.     @A@@@H.         ASK THE USER A QUESTION   @[@@@H.     @C@@@HVT
)@@G@@.         LX,U      X6,<QUESTION CONTROL BLOCK> @A@@@H.         LMJ     VU
)@@G@@  X5,QUESTION     @C@@@H.         A15 = LENGTH OF ANSWER IN CHARACTERS  VV
)@@G@@@[@@@H.     @H@@@HQUESTION  LMJ       A2,RANFDIT          EDIT A RANDOM VW
)@@G@@QUESTION FROM BLOCK     @E@@@HQUESTK    F$FD3     ('? ')              APVX
)@@G@@PEND QUESTION MARK@E@@@H          F$CHAR    EOL                 APPEND EVY
)@@G@@ND OF LINE  @D@@@H          TREAD$P   GIGO.               GET THE ANSWERVZ
)@@G@@@F@@@H          F$DT      .                   CLEAR THE QUESTION LINE   WA
)@@G@@@D@@@H          TNZ,U     0,A0                NULL ANSWER ? @F@@@H      WB
)@@G@@    J         QUESTION            GO ASK ANOTHER QUESTION   @D@@@HQUESTLWC
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,,A0              GET RID OF H1 @F@@@H          LA      WD
)@@G@@  A2,REPLY-1,A0       LOAD LAST WORD IN REPLY   @E@@@H          LA,U    WE
)@@G@@  A15,,A0             LOAD WORDS RETURNED @H@@@H          MSI,U     A15,WF
)@@G@@6               COMPUTE CHARACTERS IN FULL QUESTION   @E@@@H          LRWG
)@@G@@,U      R1,5                LOAD LOOP COUNTER   @H@@@HQSL       DSC     WH
)@@G@@  A1,6                SHIFT CHARACTERS FROM RIGHT INTO A1   @F@@@H      WI
)@@G@@    SSL       A1,30               RIGHT JUSTIFY CHARACTER   @E@@@H      WJ
)@@G@@    TE,U      A1,' '              TRAILING SPACE ?    @F@@@H          J WK
)@@G@@        0,X5                NO.  DONE SCANNING REPLY  @G@@@H          ANWL
)@@G@@A,U     A15,1               YES.  DECREMENT LENGTH OF REPLY @H@@@H      WM
)@@G@@    JGD       R1,QSL              LOOP FOR ALL CHARACTERS IN LAST WORD  WN
)@@G@@@E@@@H          J         0,X5                RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@HWO
)@@G@@.     @[@@@H.     @E@@@H.         EDIT A RANDOM STRING FROM A QUESTION CWP
)@@G@@ONTROL BLOCK@[@@@H.     @C@@@H.         LX,U      X6,<QUESTION CONTROL BWQ
)@@G@@LOCK> @ @@@H.         LMJ       A2,RANFDIT@G@@@H.         <RETURN>      WR
)@@G@@                TEXT EDITED INTO FDIT IMAGE     @[@@@H.     @G@@@HRANFDIWS
)@@G@@T   LA,U      A1                  CLEAR INITIAL QUESTION INDEX    @H@@@HWT
)@@G@@          TNZ,H1    0,X6                MORE THAN ONE QUESTION IN BLOCK WU
)@@G@@?     @E@@@H          J         RFDSIMP             NO.  SIMPLE CASE    WV
)@@G@@@E@@@H          TIME$     .                   GET RANDOM TIME     @E@@@HWW
)@@G@@          DSL       A0,36               MOVE TIME DOWN TO A1@G@@@H      WX
)@@G@@    DI,H1     A0,,X6              DIVIDE BY NUMBER OF QUESTIONS   @H@@@HWY
)@@G@@RFDSIMP   AA,U      A1,,X6              COMPUTE ADDRESS OF QUESTION POINWZ
)@@G@@TER   @F@@@H          F$MSG     0,A1,H2             EDIT THE QUESTION TEXA
)@@G@@XT    @D@@@H          J         0,A2                RETURN TO CALL@[@@@HXB
)@@G@@.     @[@@@H.     @B@@@H.         DECIDE A YES OR NO QUESTION     @[@@@HXC
)@@G@@.     @G@@@HDECIDE    LX,U      X6,YORN             GET YES OR NO LIST FXD
)@@G@@OR RETRY    @F@@@H          LMJ       X5,QUESTK           ASK THE ORIGINXE
)@@G@@AL QUESTION @G@@@HDECID1    LA,S1     A0,REPLY            LOAD FIRST CHAXF
)@@G@@RACTER OF REPLY   @C@@@H          TNE,U     A0,'Y'              YES ?   XG
)@@G@@@G@@@H          J         0,X4                YES.  TAKE AFFIRMATIVE EXIXH
)@@G@@T     @D@@@H          TNE,U     A0,'N'              NEGATIVE ?    @F@@@HXI
)@@G@@          J         1,X4                YES.  TAKE NEGATIVE EXIT  @[@@@HXJ
)@@G@@.     @F@@@H.         LOOK FOR AFFIRMATIVE AND NEGATIVE SOUNDING WORDS IXK
)@@G@@N A   @F@@@H.         TABLE.  CURRENTLY THIS TABLE IS ASSEMBLED IN, BUT XL
)@@G@@IT    @D@@@H.         MAY BE KEPT IN THE MEMORY IN THE FUTURE.    @[@@@HXM
)@@G@@.     @H@@@H          LA        A0,REPLY            LOAD USER'S REPLY TOXN
)@@G@@ THE QUESTION     @A@@@H          ON        MAINTENANCE     @F@@@H      XO
)@@G@@    TNE       A0,('THAT''S')      IS THE REPLY 'THAT'S IT' ?@H@@@H      XP
)@@G@@    TNZ       MAINT               YES.  ARE WE IN MAINTENANCE MODE ?    XQ
)@@G@@@G@@@H          J         DECNOM              NO.  SKIP NODE FINDING CODXR
)@@G@@E     @H@@@H          LX        X11,R5              YES.  LOAD CALL ADDRXS
)@@G@@ESS FOR FINDNODE  @G@@@H          TZ        X11                 WERE WE XT
)@@G@@INVOKED BY FINDNODE ?   @F@@@H          J         0,X11               YEXU
)@@G@@S.  TAKE FINDNODE RETURN@A@@@HDECNOM    OFF       MAINTENANCE     @F@@@HXV
)@@G@@          LR,U      R1,YESLL            LOAD LENGTH OF 'YES' LIST @E@@@HXW
)@@G@@          LA        A1,(1,0)            LOAD SEARCH POINTER @G@@@H      XX
)@@G@@    SE        A0,YESL,*A1         LOOK FOR ANSWER IN THE LIST     @G@@@HXY
)@@G@@          J         $+2                 NOT FOUND.  CHECK THE 'NO' LIST XZ
)@@G@@@H@@@H          J         0,X4                FOUND IN YES LIST.  TAKE YYA
)@@G@@ES REPLY    @F@@@H          LA        A1,(1,0)            RESTORE SEARCHYB
)@@G@@ POINTER    @F@@@H          LR,U      R1,NOLL             LOAD LENGTH OFYC
)@@G@@ 'NO' LIST  @G@@@H          SE        A0,NOL,*A1          LOOK FOR ANSWEYD
)@@G@@R IN 'NO' LIST    @F@@@H          J         $+2                 NOT FOUNYE
)@@G@@D.  REASK QUESTION@H@@@H          J         1,X4                FOUND INYF
)@@G@@ 'NO' LIST.  TAKE NO REPLY    @F@@@H          LMJ       X5,QUESTION     YG
)@@G@@    ASK THE QUESTION AGAIN    @F@@@H          J         DECID1          YH
)@@G@@    GO INTERPRET NEXT ANSWER  @[@@@H.     @[@@@H.     @G@@@H.         THYI
)@@G@@IS SUBROUTINE SCANS A QUESTION FOUND IN THE BUFFER 'REPLY'  @G@@@H.     YJ
)@@G@@    WHOSE LENGTH IS SPECIFIED BY A15 FOR A PRONOUN.  UPON FINDING @G@@@HYK
)@@G@@.         ONE, IT IS PLUGGED WITH AN EMSG$ STOP CHARACTER TO PERMIT     YL
)@@G@@@ @@@H.         SUBSTITUTION FOR IT.@[@@@H.     @C@@@H.         LA,U    YM
)@@G@@  A15,<LENGTH OF QUESTION>    @ @@@H.         LMJ       X7,PLUGGEN@F@@@HYN
)@@G@@.         <NO PRONOUN>                  REPLY BUFFER UNCHANGED    @ @@@HYO
)@@G@@.         <PRONOUN PLUGGED>   @[@@@H.     @F@@@HPLUGGEN   E$COL     0   YP
)@@G@@                TAB TO START OF MESSAGE   @[@@@H.     @E@@@H.         SEYQ
)@@G@@ARCH THE USER'S QUESTION FOR 'IT', AND SET UP TO@E@@@H.         PLUG THEYR
)@@G@@ ANIMAL NAME WHEN WE ASK IT BACK TO HIM.  @[@@@H.     @H@@@HFINDIT    U$YS
)@@G@@CHAR    .                   LOAD A CHARACTER FROM THE MESSAGE     @D@@@HYT
)@@G@@          TE,U      A0,'I'              IS IT AN 'I' ?@H@@@H          J YU
)@@G@@        FIND1               NO.  ADVANCE TO NEXT START OF WORD    @H@@@HYV
)@@G@@          U$CHAR    .                   LOAD NEXT CHARACTER AND PEEK AHEYW
)@@G@@AD    @E@@@H          TNE,U     A0,'T'              IS IT AN 'IT' ?     YX
)@@G@@@G@@@H          TE,U      A2,' '              (MUST BE FOLLOWED BY SPACEYY
)@@G@@)     @F@@@H          J         FIND2               NO.  RECOVER AND CONYZ
)@@G@@TINUE @E@@@H          E$SKIP    -2                  BACK UP OVER THE 'I'ZA
)@@G@@@H@@@H          E$FD1     ('&&')              EDIT TWO STOP CHARCTERS INZB
)@@G@@TO THE LINE @F@@@H          E$COL     A15,,W              TAB TO END OF ZC
)@@G@@MESSAGE     @G@@@H          E$CHAR    '&'                 INSERT END OF ZD
)@@G@@MESSAGE THERE     @E@@@H          E$DITX    .                   LEAVE EDZE
)@@G@@ITING MODE  @F@@@H          J         1,X7                PRONOUN PLUGGEZF
)@@G@@D.  RETURN  @[@@@H.     @G@@@HFIND2     TNE,U     A0,' '              WAZG
)@@G@@S THE BAD CHARACTER A SPACE ? @G@@@H          J         FIND3           ZH
)@@G@@    YES.  SKIP ADVANCE TO NEXT SPACE@F@@@HFIND1     U$POS1    ' '       ZI
)@@G@@          FIND THE END OF THIS WORD @H@@@H          JN        A0,,X7    ZJ
)@@G@@          TAKE NO FIND RETURN IF NO PRONOUN     @E@@@HFIND3     U$POS3  ZK
)@@G@@  .                   FIND NEXT NON-BLANK @F@@@H          E$COLN    .   ZL
)@@G@@                RETURN COLUMN POINTER     @F@@@H          TG        A0,AZM
)@@G@@15              BEYOND END OF USER IMAGE ?@G@@@H          J         0,X7ZN
)@@G@@                YES.  NO PRONOUN IN SENTENCE    @F@@@H          J       ZO
)@@G@@  FINDIT              GO PROCESS THIS CHARACTER @[@@@H.     @[@@@H.     ZP
)@@G@@@F@@@H.         THIS SUBROUTINE INSERTS THE USER'S ANIMAL (FROM UANML)  ZQ
)@@G@@@F@@@H.         INTO A QUESTION IN THE BUFFER 'REPLY' PREVIOUSLY SCANNEDZR
)@@G@@@^@@@H.         BY 'PLUGGEN'. @[@@@H.     @ @@@H.         LMJ       X7,SZS

)@@G@@@]@@@@300 Y=RND   @#@@@@305 Y$='HEADS'    @ @@@@310 IF Y>.5 THEN Y$='TAIDB
)@@G@@LS'   @^@@@@320 IF D$=Y$ THEN 410   @]@@@@330 H=0     @E@@@@370 PRINT 'YDC
)@@G@@OU LOST THE TOSS.  THE ';A$;' ARE UP FIRST.'    @]@@@@380 PRINT   @]@@@@DD
)@@G@@381 PRINT   @]@@@@390 A=0     @]@@@@400 GOTO 520@E@@@@410 PRINT 'YOU WINDE

)@@G@@690 IF O>1 THEN PRINT 'THERE ARE';O;'OUTS'@^@@@@700 P=B(1)+B(2)+B(3)    DP
)@@G@@@^@@@@702 IF P<>3 THEN 726    @^@@@@710 PRINT 'BASES LOADED'@]@@@@720 GODQ

)@@G@@.         TO  A FREE SPACE POOL.  THIS SPACE MAY EXPAND AND CONTRACT DYNIZ
)@@G@@AMI-  @#@@@@.         CALLY.  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         TO ALLOCATE A JA

)@@G@@UIRED>@A@@@@.                 LMJ       X11,BGET@ @@@@.                 JC

)@@G@@  ADDRESS OF THE FIRST WORD OF THE  @#@@@@.         BUFFER. @[@@@@.     JE
)@@G@@@ @@@@.         TO RELEASE A BUFFER:@[@@@@.     @D@@@@.                 JF
)@@G@@LA,U      A0,<ADDRESS OF BUFFER>    @A@@@@.                 LMJ       X1JG
)@@G@@1,BREL@ @@@@.                 <RETURN>    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.         BOJH
)@@G@@TH  ROUTINES  DESTROY  ONLY THE REGISTERS X11 AND A0, AND MAY BE  @H@@@@JI
)@@G@@.         CALLED  BY  ACTIVITIES RUNNING IN THE MINOR SET OF REGISTERS. JJ
)@@G@@ THE  @H@@@@.         ROUTINES  ARE  QUARTER  WORD INSENSITIVE, AND MAY JK
)@@G@@BE CALLED SIMUL-  @H@@@@.         TANEOUSLY  BY MULTI-ACTIVITY PROGRAMS JL
)@@G@@OR INCORPORATED INTO A REEN-  @ @@@@.         TRANT PROCESSOR.    @[@@@@JM
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@.                 THE  ABOVE  IS SUFFICIENT INFORMATION TO IJN
)@@G@@NTELLIGENTLY USE  @H@@@@.         THE  BUFFER  ALLOCATION PACKAGE.  THOSJO
)@@G@@E OF YOU WHOSE BLOOD COURSES  @H@@@@.         AT THE THOUGHT OF THE UNKNJP
)@@G@@OWN ARE NOW INVITED DOWN THE RABBIT HOLE  @H@@@@.         TO LEARN HOW TJQ
)@@G@@HIS THING OPERATES AND HOW TO CONFIGURE IT OPTIMALLY  @ @@@@.         FOJR
)@@G@@R AN APPLICATION. @[@@@@/.    @H@@@@.                 EACH  BUFFER  IS PJS
)@@G@@RECEDED BY TWO WORDS OF CONTROL INFORMA-  @G@@@@.         TION.  THIS INJT
)@@G@@FORMATION CONSISTS OF FOUR HALF WORD ITEMS:     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     JU
)@@G@@            SIZE      SIZE  OF THIS BUFFER INCLUDING CONTROL@F@@@@.     JV
)@@G@@                      WORDS.   THIS FIELD IS NEGATIVE IF THE@C@@@@.     JW
)@@G@@                      BUFFER IS IN USE.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.           JX
)@@G@@      HL        LINK  TO  PREVIOUS  BLOCK IN CORE.  IF@F@@@@.           JY
)@@G@@                ZERO, THE PREVIOUS BLOCK IS IN USE.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@JZ
)@@G@@.                 FL        LINK TO NEXT FREE BUFFER (USED ONLY IF@C@@@@KA
)@@G@@.                           BUFFER IS FREE).    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     KB
)@@G@@            BL - ARQ  IF  BUFFER  IS  FREE, LINK TO PREVIOUS@F@@@@.     KC
)@@G@@                      FREE BUFFER (BL), IF BUFFER IS IN USE,@F@@@@.     KD
)@@G@@                      ADDRESS  OF  REQUESTOR  OF  THE BUFFER@A@@@@.     KE
)@@G@@                      (ARQ).  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                 AT  THKF
)@@G@@E  TAG HEAD IS THE HEAD OF THE LIST OF FREE BUFFERS.  @H@@@@.         THKG
)@@G@@E LENGTH FIELD OF THE HEAD IS SET TO -1 TO PREVENT ALLOCATION OF  @^@@@@KH
)@@G@@.         THE HEAD.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                 THE  ROUTINEKI
)@@G@@  BGET  ALLOCATES  BUFFERS  BY THE 'FIRST FIT'  @H@@@@.         METHOD, KJ
)@@G@@ AS  FOLLOWS:   STARTING  AT  HEAD,  IT  LINKS THROUGH THE  @H@@@@.     KK
)@@G@@    BUFFERS  UNTIL  IT  FINDS ONE LARGE ENOUGH TO SATISFY THE REQUEST.  KL
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         HAVING FOUND ONE, IT DETERMINES HOW MUCH UNUSED SPACE WIKM
)@@G@@LL BE LEFT  @H@@@@.         OVER  ONCE  THE  REQUESTED  SPACE IS GIVEN TKN
)@@G@@O THE USER.  IF ENOUGH  @H@@@@.         SPACE REMAINS TO FORM ANOTHER FRKO
)@@G@@EE BLOCK, IT REDUCES THE LENGTH OF  @H@@@@.         THE  FREE BLOCK BY TKP
)@@G@@HE LENGTH TO BE ALLOCATED, CONSTRUCTS A BUFFER  @H@@@@.         FROM  THKQ
)@@G@@E  END  OF  THE  FREE  BLOCK, AND PASSES THAT TO THE USER.  @H@@@@.     KR
)@@G@@    OTHERWISE,  THE  ENTIRE  FREE  BLOCK IS UNCHAINED AND GIVEN TO THE  KS
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         USER.  THE HEAD LINK OF THE NEXT BLOCK IS CLEARED TO INDKT
)@@G@@ICATE THAT  @B@@@@.         THE BLOCK HAS BEEN ALLOCATED.   @[@@@@.     KU
)@@G@@@H@@@@.                 THE ROUTINE BREL RETURNS A BUFFER TO THE FREE POKV
)@@G@@OL, POSSI-  @H@@@@.         BLY  RECOMBINING  IT  WITH  CONTIGUOUS  BLOCKW
)@@G@@KS TO FORM LARGER FREE  @H@@@@.         BLOCKS.   IF  BOTH  THE PRECEDINKX
)@@G@@G AND FOLLOWING BLOCKS OF A BUFFER  @H@@@@.         ARE  IN  USE,  THE  KY
)@@G@@BUFFER BEING RELEASED IS SIMPLY CHAINED TO THE  @H@@@@.         LIST  OFKZ
)@@G@@ FREE BUFFERS.  IF THE PRECEDING BLOCK IS FREE, THE BUFFER  @H@@@@.     LA
)@@G@@    BEING  RETURNED  IS  APPENDED  TO  THE  PRECEDING BUFFER, WHICH IS  LB
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         ALREADY  ON  THE  FREE  LIST.   AT  THIS POINT, THE NEXTLC
)@@G@@ BUFFER IS  @H@@@@.         EXAMINED.   IF  IT  IS  FREE, IT IS REMOVED LD
)@@G@@FROM THE FREE LIST AND  @D@@@@.         ABSORBED INTO THE BUFFER BEING RLE
)@@G@@ELEASED.    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                 IF  THE  EQU  EXPINC IS LF
)@@G@@NONZERO, CODE WILL BE GENERATED TO  @H@@@@.         DYNAMICALLY  EXPAND LG
)@@G@@THE BUFFER POOL WHEN SPACE IS EXHAUSTED.  THIS  @H@@@@.         CODE,  SLH
)@@G@@TARTING AT THE TAG MT, ACQUIRES ENOUGH CORE TO SATISFY THE  @H@@@@.     LI
)@@G@@    REQUEST  (OR AT LEAST EXPINC WORDS), AND CONSTRUCTS A LARGE BUFFER  LJ
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         OF  IT.   AN 'IMPENETRABLE BARRIER' ONE WORD LONG IS PLALK
)@@G@@CED AT THE  @H@@@@.         END  OF  THE  BUFFER.   THIS  BARRIER CONTAILL
)@@G@@NS THE NEGATIVE OF THE  @H@@@@.         BLOCK  LENGTH IN THE SIZE FIELD LM
)@@G@@TO STOP RECOMBINATION.  THE END OF  @H@@@@.         CORE  POINTER,  LASTLN
)@@G@@D, IS UPDATED.  THE NEW BUFFER IS THEN CHAINED  @F@@@@.         TO THE FLO
)@@G@@REE LIST, AND THE USER REQUEST IS THEN RETRIED. @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.     LP
)@@G@@            THE  EQU  LCORE CONTROLS WHETHER EXPANSION BLOCKS ACQUIRED  LQ
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         BY  THE  ABOVE  MECHANISM  WILL BE RELEASED WHEN TOTALLYLR
)@@G@@ FREE.  IN  @H@@@@.         GENERAL,  THIS  MECHANISM IS USEFUL ONLY TO LS
)@@G@@PROGRAMS WITH LONG RUN  @H@@@@.         TIMES,  LARGE  SIZE VARIATIONS, LT
)@@G@@AND A TRUE NESTING OF REQUESTS AND  @H@@@@.         RELEASES.   THE  CODLU
)@@G@@E, WHICH STARTS AT THE TAG BRL5, CHECKS WHEN A  @H@@@@.         BUFFER  LV
)@@G@@IS  RELEASED  TO SEE IF IT EXTENDS TO THE END OF CORE.  IF  @H@@@@.     LW
)@@G@@    SO,  THE ROUTINE STARTING AT BRL3 IS INVOKED TO DETERMINE FROM THE  LX
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         SIZE  FIELD  AND  THE BARRIER WORD WHETHER THE ENTIRE BLLY
)@@G@@OCK IS NOW  @H@@@@.         FREE.   IF  IT  IS,  THE BLOCK IS UNCHAINED LZ
)@@G@@FROM THE FREE LIST AND  @H@@@@.         RELEASED  VIA LCORE$.  IF OTHER MA
)@@G@@EXPANSION BLOCKS ARE PRESENT, THEY  @C@@@@.         ARE EXAMINED FOR POSMB
)@@G@@SIBLE RELEASE.    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                 BUFFERS ARE INITIAMC
)@@G@@LLY ALLOCATED FROM A POOL ASSEMBLED INTO  @H@@@@.         THE  ELEMENT. MD
)@@G@@  THE  SIZE OF THIS INITIAL RESERVE IS DETERMINED BY  @H@@@@.         THME
)@@G@@E  EQU  BSIZE.   THE  INTERNAL  BUFFER  STARTS AT THE TAG BIBUF,  @H@@@@MF
)@@G@@.         IMMEDIATELY  BEFORE  THE  HEAD PACKET.  THE FIRST WORD OF THE MG
)@@G@@HEAD  @H@@@@.         SERVES  AS THE BARRIER WORD FOR THE INTERNAL BUFFEMH

)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         DERIVATIVE VARIABLES FROM CONFIGQL

)@@G@@RLEV>2)++STATS    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         WAIT IS NON-ZERO IF CODE FQY
)@@G@@OR WAITING FOR SPACE IS NEEDED.     @A@@@@WAIT      EQU       HOPE**(EXPQZ
)@@G@@INC=0)@[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         CHECK VALIDITY OF PARAMETERS    @[@@@@RA
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@          DO        (BSIZE=0)**(EXPINC=0) , I FLAG INDICATESRB
)@@G@@ NO CORE POSSIBLE @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@.         PROCS   @[@@@@RC
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@          AXR$    @#@@@@          DEFUNCT$@^@@@@          LIRD
)@@G@@T$      2   @[@@@[.     @F@@@@P         PROC      1,1                 TORE
)@@G@@ GENERATE ERROR CALL    @^@@@@KABONG*   NAME      0   @A@@@@          DORF
)@@G@@        ERRLEV<2 , EABT$@E@@@@          DO        ERRLEV>1 , I$ 072,010,RG
)@@G@@P(1,1),,,KABTRAP  @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@E$        PRRH
)@@G@@OC      1,2 @^@@@@E$BO*     NAME      0   @ @@@@B         EQU       E$(1RI
)@@G@@,1)-1 @ @@@@Y         FORM      6,12,18   @C@@@@          DO        E$(0RJ
)@@G@@,0)=0 , SLJ    EBO$     @C@@@@          Y         E$(1,3),B-B/6*6,E$(1,2RK
)@@G@@)+B/6 @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@P*        PROC      1   RL
)@@G@@                INVOKE CRITICAL SECTION   @D@@@@          TS        P(1,RM
)@@G@@1)              SET THE LOCK  @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@RN
)@@G@@V*        PROC      1                   RELEASE CRITICAL SECTION  @B@@@@RO
)@@G@@          DO        TSQ=0 , SZ,S1 V(1,1)  @B@@@@          DO        TSQ>RP
)@@G@@0 , CTS$  V(1,1)  @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@P         PRRQ
)@@G@@OC      0,1                 CRITICAL SECTION LOCK     @^@@@@SEMA4*    NARR
)@@G@@ME      0   @A@@@@          DO        TSQ=0 , * 0     @A@@@@          DORS
)@@G@@        TSQ>0 , TCELL$  @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     RT
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         BUFFER FORMAT EQUATES     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@HL        EQRU
)@@G@@UF      0,,H1               POINTER TO PREVIOUS BLOCK @G@@@@.           RV
)@@G@@                            ZERO MEANS PREVIOUS BLOCK IN USE@[@@@@.     RW
)@@G@@@H@@@@SIZE      EQUF      0,,XH2              SIZE OF BLOCK INCLUDING CORX
)@@G@@NTROL WORDS @G@@@@.                                       NEGATIVE MEANSRY
)@@G@@ BLOCK IS IN USE  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@FBL       EQUF      1               RZ
)@@G@@    LINK WORD     @G@@@@FL        EQUF      FBL,,H1             FORWARD SA
)@@G@@LINK TO NEXT FREE BLOCK @H@@@@BL        EQUF      FBL,,H2             BASB
)@@G@@CKWARD LINK TO PREVIOUS FREE BLOCK  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ARQ       EQUF    SC
)@@G@@  1,,H2               ADDRESS OF REQUEST OF BLOCK IF IN USE @[@@@@.     SD
)@@G@@@H@@@@NCWIU     EQU       2                   NUMBER OF CONTROL WORDS IFSE
)@@G@@ IN USE     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@MIN       EQU       NCWIU+1             MISF
)@@G@@NIMUM SIZE BUFFER TO KEEP     @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.         DASG
)@@G@@TA AREA     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON        BSIZE>0   @ @@@@BIBUF SH
)@@G@@    *         0,BSIZE   @ @@@@          *         HEAD,HEAD @A@@@@      SI
)@@G@@    RES       BSIZE-NCWIU     @ @@@@          OFF       BSIZE>0   @A@@@@SJ
)@@G@@          DO        BSIZE=0 ,BIBUF. @C@@@@HEAD      *         BIBUF,-1  SK
)@@G@@          HL,SIZE @G@@@@          *         BIBUF,BIBUF         INITIALLSL
)@@G@@Y ONE BIG (?) BLOCK     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON        STATS     SM
)@@G@@@]@@@@BSTATW*   . @E@@@@GETCALL   *         0                   NUMBER OSN
)@@G@@F BGET CALLS@E@@@@RELCALL   *         0                   NUMBER OF BRELSO
)@@G@@ CALLS@D@@@@INUSE     EQUF      $,,H1               WORDS IN USE  @F@@@@SP
)@@G@@MAXUSE    EQUF      $,,XH2              -(MAX WORDS USED SO FAR)  @^@@@@SQ
)@@G@@          *         0,0 @ @@@@          OFF       STATS     @[@@@@.     SR
)@@G@@@^@@@@          ON        WAIT@G@@@@WAITC     *         0               SS
)@@G@@    # TIMES ANYONE HAD TO WAIT.     @^@@@@          OFF       WAIT@[@@@@ST
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@CRIT      SEMA4     .                   CRITICAL SECTION LOCSU
)@@G@@K     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON        EXPINC>0  @E@@@@LASTD     EQSV
)@@G@@UF      $,,H1               NEXT USABLE ADDRESS @F@@@@SVLEN     EQUF    SW
)@@G@@  $,,XH2              SAVE FOR BUFFER LENGTH    @A@@@@SNAPR     *       SX
)@@G@@  LASTD$+1,$-$    @ @@@@          OFF       EXPINC>0  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@SY
)@@G@@SVA1      RES       2                   SAVE A1, A2   @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@SZ
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@.         REQUEST CORE BLOCK  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@TA
)@@G@@.         LA,U      A0,<LENGTH>     @ @@@@.         LMJ       X11,BGET  TB
)@@G@@@E@@@@.         <RETURN>                      A0 = BUFFER ADDRESS @[@@@@TC
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@$(1). @G@@@@BGET*     P         CRIT                INVOKE CTD
)@@G@@RITICAL SECTION LOCK    @A@@@@          ON        TRACE++WAIT     @C@@@@TE
)@@G@@          SA        A0,TSAVE            SAVE A0 @A@@@@          OFF     TF
)@@G@@  TRACE++WAIT     @ @@@@          ON        TRACE     @F@@@@          TNTG
)@@G@@Z       BTRACE              IS TRACE OUTPUT DESIRED ? @E@@@@          J TH
)@@G@@        BGTTF               NO.  SKIP EDITING   @D@@@@          E$BO    TI
)@@G@@  38,T$BGET,12        EDIT PARAMETER@E@@@@          LA,U      A0,,X11   TJ
)@@G@@          GET RETURN ADDRESS  @D@@@@          ANA,U     A0,1            TK
)@@G@@    BACK IT UP    @E@@@@          E$BO      6,T$BGET,6          EDIT INTTL
)@@G@@O TRACE LINE@E@@@@          PRINT$    T$BGET,T$LBGET      PRINT THE TRACTM
)@@G@@E     @D@@@@          LA        A0,TSAVE            RELOAD A0     @]@@@@TN
)@@G@@BGTTF     . @ @@@@          OFF       TRACE     @D@@@@          DS      TO
)@@G@@  A1,SVA1             SAVE A1, A2   @ @@@@          ON        STATS     TP
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A1,GETCALL          LOAD NUMBER OF BGET CALLS TQ
)@@G@@@D@@@@          AA,U      A1,1                INCREMENT IT  @G@@@@      TR
)@@G@@    SA        A1,GETCALL          UPDATE CALLS ON BGET SO FAR     @ @@@@TS
)@@G@@          OFF       STATS     @B@@@@          ON        CHECK**(MAXSIZ>0TT
)@@G@@)     @G@@@@          TG,U      A0,MAXSIZ           IS USER REQUEST WITHTU
)@@G@@IN RANGE ?  @E@@@@          KABONG    1                   NO.  ERROR CODTV
)@@G@@E 1   @B@@@@          OFF       CHECK**(MAXSIZ>0)     @G@@@@          LNTW
)@@G@@A,U     A0,NCWIU,A0         A0 = -(ACTUAL LENGTH NEEDED)    @G@@@@BGET0 TX
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,HEAD             POINT TO HEAD OF FREE BLOCKS    @E@@@@TY
)@@G@@BGET1     LA        A2,FL,A2            LINK TO NEXT BLOCK  @G@@@@      TZ
)@@G@@    TNE,U     A2,HEAD             DOES THAT BRING US BACK HOME ?  @ @@@@UA
)@@G@@          ON        EXPINC>0  @I@@@@          J         MT              UB
)@@G@@    YES.  NEED MORE CORE TO SATISFY REQUEST     @ @@@@          OFF     UC
)@@G@@  EXPINC>0  @ @@@@          ON        EXPINC=0  @ @@@@          ON      UD
)@@G@@  WAIT=0    @F@@@@          KABONG    4                   NO MORE CORE. UE
)@@G@@ FATAL ERROR@ @@@@          OFF       WAIT=0    @^@@@@          ON      UF
)@@G@@  WAIT@F@@@@          J         QUYRSELF            NO MORE CORE. WAIT FUG
)@@G@@OR IT.@^@@@@          OFF       WAIT@ @@@@          OFF       EXPINC=0  UH
)@@G@@@F@@@@          AU        A0,SIZE,A2          IS THIS BLOCK BIG ENOUGH ?UI
)@@G@@@F@@@@          JN        A1,BGET1            NO.  LOOK AT NEXT ONE     UJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TLE,U     A1,MIN              CAN WE SPLIT THIS BLOCK ? UK
)@@G@@@G@@@@          J         BGET3               NO.  JUST REMOVE THE WHOLEUL
)@@G@@ THING@G@@@@.                                       OTHERWISE, TAKE THE UM
)@@G@@SECOND PART @I@@@@.                                       AND LEAVE THE UN
)@@G@@FIRST PART ON THE FREELIST    @F@@@@          SA        A1,SIZE,A2      UO
)@@G@@    UPDATE SIZE REMAINING     @H@@@@          AA,U      A1,,A2          UP
)@@G@@    POINT TO PART TO BE GIVEN TO USER     @G@@@@          SA        A2,HUQ
)@@G@@L,A1            POINT BACK TO PREVIOUS BUFFER   @F@@@@BGET2     SA      UR
)@@G@@  A0,SIZE,A1          STORE SIZE, MARKING IN USE@G@@@@          ANU,XU  US
)@@G@@  A1,,A0              COMPUTE NEXT BUFFER ADDRESS     @F@@@@          SZUT
)@@G@@        HL,A2               MARK THIS BUFFER IN USE   @F@@@@          SXUU
)@@G@@        X11,ARQ,A1          SAVE REQUESTOR'S ADDRESS  @ @@@@          ONUV
)@@G@@        STATS     @E@@@@          LA        A2,A1               SAVE BUFUW
)@@G@@FER ADDRESS.@G@@@@          ANU       A0,INUSE            A1 = -(TOTAL WUX
)@@G@@ORDS ALLOCATED)   @E@@@@          SNA       A1,INUSE            UPDATE IUY
)@@G@@NUSE COUNT  @F@@@@          TLE       A1,MAXUSE           IS IT A NEW HIUZ
)@@G@@GH (LOW)    @E@@@@          SA        A1,MAXUSE           YES.  UPDATE MVA
)@@G@@AX USE@E@@@@          LA        A1,A2               RESTORE ADDRESS.    VB
)@@G@@@ @@@@          OFF       STATS     @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,NCWIU,AVC
)@@G@@1         PASS BACK ADDRESS TO USER @^@@@@          ON        WAIT@E@@@@VD
)@@G@@          SA        A0,TSAVE            SAVE THE ANSWER.    @F@@@@      VE
)@@G@@    LMJ       A2,QUF              START UP WAITING REQUESTS.@E@@@@      VF
)@@G@@    LA        A0,TSAVE            RESTORE ANSWER.     @^@@@@          OFVG
)@@G@@F       WAIT@E@@@@          DL        A1,SVA1             RESTORE REGISTVH
)@@G@@ERS   @ @@@@          ON        TRACE     @E@@@@          TNZ       BTRAVI
)@@G@@CE              TRACING REQUESTS ?  @D@@@@          J         BGTTF1    VJ
)@@G@@          NO.  SKIP THIS@C@@@@          SA        A0,TSAVE            SAVK
)@@G@@VE A0 @F@@@@          E$BO      38,T$BGET1,12       EDIT ADDRESS RETURNEVL
)@@G@@D     @E@@@@          PRINT$    T$BGET1,T$LBGET1    PRINT TRACE LINE    VM
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA        A0,TSAVE            RELOAD A0     @]@@@@BGTTF1VN
)@@G@@    . @ @@@@          OFF       TRACE     @F@@@@          V         CRITVO
)@@G@@                CLEAR CRITICAL SECTION    @F@@@@          J         0,X1VP
)@@G@@1               RETURN TO CALLING SEQUENCE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@BGET3     LAVQ
)@@G@@        A0,FL,A2            LOAD FORWARD LINK IN BLOCK@E@@@@          LAVR
)@@G@@        A1,BL,A2            LOAD BACKWARD LINK  @G@@@@          SA      VS
)@@G@@  A0,FL,A1            PUT FORWARD LINK IN LAST BLOCK  @G@@@@          SAVT
)@@G@@        A1,BL,A0            PUT BACKWARD LINK IN NEXT BLOCK @F@@@@      VU
)@@G@@    LNA       A0,SIZE,A2          LOAD -(ACTUAL BLOCK SIZE) @F@@@@      VV
)@@G@@    LA,U      A1,,A2              GET BUFFER ADDRESS IN A1  @F@@@@      VW
)@@G@@    J         BGET2               JOIN RETURN TO USER CODE  @[@@@@.     VX
)@@G@@@E@@@@.         QUEUE ACTIVITY TO WAIT FOR SPACE AVAILABLILITY.   @[@@@@VY
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@          ON        WAIT@]@@@@QUYRSELF.   @ @@@@          ONVZ
)@@G@@        STATS     @G@@@@          ANU       A0,INUSE            A1 = -(TWA
)@@G@@OTAL WORDS ALLOCATED)   @F@@@@          TLE       A1,MAXUSE           ISWB
)@@G@@ IT A NEW HIGH (LOW)    @E@@@@          SA        A1,MAXUSE           YEWC
)@@G@@S.  UPDATE MAX USE@ @@@@          OFF       STATS     @F@@@@          LAWD
)@@G@@        A0,WAITC            COUNT OF PREVIOUS WAITS.  @D@@@@          AAWE
)@@G@@,U      A0,1                INCREMENT IT. @D@@@@          SA        A0,WWF
)@@G@@AITC            PUT BACK.     @F@@@@          LMJ       A2,QUF          WG
)@@G@@    START A WAITING ACTIVITY. @G@@@@          LA        A1,QCOUNT,A0    WH
)@@G@@    COUNT OF STUFF IN NEW QUEUE.    @C@@@@          AA,U      A1,1      WI
)@@G@@          BUMP IT.@C@@@@          SA        A1,QCOUNT,A0        SAVE IT.WJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@          DL        A1,SVA1             RESTORE A1-A2.@E@@@@      WK
)@@G@@    TE,U      A0,QUEUE0           IF GOING TO QUEUE 1,@D@@@@          J WL
)@@G@@        QUY1                GO THERE.     @D@@@@          LA        A0,TWM
)@@G@@SAVE            RESTORE A0.   @E@@@@          V         CRIT            WN
)@@G@@    OPEN CRITICAL CODE. @C@@@@          CTSQ$     QUEUE0              WAWO
)@@G@@IT.   @C@@@@          J         BGET                GO.     @D@@@@QUY1  WP
)@@G@@    LA        A0,TSAVE            RESTORE A0.   @E@@@@          V       WQ
)@@G@@  CRIT                OPEN CRITICAL CODE. @C@@@@          CTSQ$     QUEUWR
)@@G@@E1              WAIT.   @C@@@@          J         BGET                GOWS
)@@G@@ ON.  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@QUF       LA        A0,QFROM        WT
)@@G@@    QUEUE THAT THEY'RE COMING FROM. @F@@@@          LA        A1,QCOUNT,WU
)@@G@@A0        COUNT OF THINGS IN IT.    @F@@@@          JZ        A1,QUF1   WV
)@@G@@          IF NONE, NOTHING TO DO.   @D@@@@          ANA,U     A1,1      WW
)@@G@@          REDUCE COUNT. @D@@@@          SA        A1,QCOUNT,A0        PUWX
)@@G@@T IT BACK.  @E@@@@          CTSA$     0,A0                START SOMEBODYWY
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@QUF1. @F@@@@          LA        A0,QTO              POINT TOWZ
)@@G@@ THE OTHER QUEUE. @C@@@@          J         0,A2                RETURN. XA
)@@G@@@^@@@@          OFF       WAIT@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         ACQUIRE AN EXPXB
)@@G@@ANSION BLOCK@[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON        EXPINC>0  @]@@@@MT    XC
)@@G@@    . @F@@@@          SA        A0,SVLEN            SAVE USER LENGTH REQXD
)@@G@@UEST  @ @@@@          ON        BOUNDED   @G@@@@          LMA       A0,AXE
)@@G@@0               LOAD POSITIVE LENGTH REQUESTED  @H@@@@          TLE,U   XF
)@@G@@  A0,EXPINC           IS USER REQUEST > EXPANSION SIZE ?    @ @@@@      XG
)@@G@@    OFF       BOUNDED   @G@@@@          LA,U      A0,EXPINC           LOXH
)@@G@@AD SIZE OF EXPANSION BLOCK    @ @@@@          ON        TRACE     @E@@@@XI
)@@G@@          TNZ       BTRACE              TRACE REQUESTS ?    @E@@@@      XJ
)@@G@@    J         MTTRC               NO.  SKIP LOGGING   @D@@@@          E$XK
)@@G@@BO      16,T$RQST,6         LOG REQUEST   @E@@@@          SA        A0,TXL
)@@G@@SAVE            SAVE A0 OVER TRACE  @E@@@@          PRINT$    T$RQST,T$LXM
)@@G@@RQST      PRINT THE MESSAGE   @D@@@@          LA        A0,TSAVE        XN
)@@G@@    RELOAD A0     @]@@@@MTTRC     . @ @@@@          OFF       TRACE     XO
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LNA,U     A2,,A0              LOAD -(BUFFER LENGTH)     XP
)@@G@@@H@@@@          LXI,U     A2                  CLEAR H1 OF A2, FORMING ENXQ
)@@G@@D BARRIER   @G@@@@          AU        A0,LASTD            COMPUTE HIGHESXR
)@@G@@T ADDRESS NEEDED  @D@@@@          DSC       A0,36               SWAP A0,XS
)@@G@@ A1   @F@@@@          LXI,U     A0,0200000          EXPAND FOR ENTIRE PRXT
)@@G@@OGRAM @E@@@@          MCORE$    .                   OBTAIN THE CORE     XU
)@@G@@@G@@@@          SA        A2,,A0              PUT AT END OF EXPANSION BLXV
)@@G@@OCK   @G@@@@          AA,U      A0,1                COMPUTE NEXT WORD TOXW
)@@G@@ REQUEST    @F@@@@          SA        A0,LASTD            UPDATE END-OF-XX
)@@G@@CORE WORD   @G@@@@          ANA,U     A0,1,A1             A0 = START OF XY
)@@G@@NEW BUFFER AREA   @G@@@@          SA        A1,SIZE,A0          SAVE SIZXZ
)@@G@@E OF BUFFER IN BUFFER   @G@@@@          LA,U      A1,HEAD             GEYA
)@@G@@T ADDRESS OF HEAD OF CHAIN    @G@@@@          SA        A1,BL,A0        YB
)@@G@@    SET UP BACK LINK OF NEW BUFFER  @F@@@@          LA        A1,HEAD+FLYC
)@@G@@          GET FIRST BUFFER IN CHAIN @E@@@@          SA        A1,FL,A0  YD
)@@G@@          LINK TO NEW ONE     @F@@@@          SA        A0,BL,A1        YE
)@@G@@    POINT OLD ONE TO THIS ONE @F@@@@          SZ        HL,A0           YF
)@@G@@    DON'T ALLOW RECOMBINATION @F@@@@          SA        A0,HEAD+FL      YG
)@@G@@    CHAIN THIS ONE TO THE HEAD@F@@@@          LA        A0,SVLEN        YH
)@@G@@    RELOAD LENGTH OF BUFFER   @C@@@@          J         BGET0           YI
)@@G@@    CONTINUE@ @@@@          OFF       EXPINC>0  @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     YJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@.         RELEASE CORE BLOCK  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         LA,U    YK
)@@G@@  A0,<ADDRESS>    @ @@@@.         LMJ       X11,BREL  @E@@@@.         <RYL
)@@G@@ETURN>                      X11, A0 DESTROYED   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@BREL* YM
)@@G@@    ANA,U     A0,NCWIU            POINT TO ACTUAL BUFFER START    @E@@@@YN
)@@G@@          LXI,U     X11,,X11            SAVE RETURN POINT   @F@@@@      YO
)@@G@@    P         CRIT                INVOKE CRITICAL SECTION   @ @@@@      YP
)@@G@@    ON        TRACE     @E@@@@          TNZ       BTRACE              TRYQ
)@@G@@ACING REQUESTS ?  @F@@@@          J         BRLTF               NO.  SKIYR
)@@G@@P THIS EDITING    @C@@@@          SA        A0,TSAVE            SAVE A0 YS
)@@G@@@E@@@@          AA,U      A0,NCWIU            COMPUTE USER ADDRESS@E@@@@YT
)@@G@@          E$BO      38,T$BREL,12        EDIT ADDRESS PASSED @E@@@@      YU
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,,X11             GET RETURN ADDRESS  @D@@@@          ANYV
)@@G@@A,U     A0,1                BACK IT UP    @F@@@@          E$BO      6,T$YW
)@@G@@BREL,6          EDIT IT INTO THE TRACE    @D@@@@          PRINT$    T$BRYX
)@@G@@EL,T$LBREL      PRINT TRACE   @D@@@@          LA        A0,TSAVE        YY
)@@G@@    RELOAD A0     @]@@@@BRLTF     . @ @@@@          OFF       TRACE     YZ
)@@G@@@D@@@@          DS        A1,SVA1             SAVE A1, A2   @ @@@@      ZA
)@@G@@    ON        CHECK     @D@@@@          TN        SIZE,A0             ISZB
)@@G@@ IT IN USE ?@H@@@@          KABONG    2                   NO.  RELEASE OZC
)@@G@@F UNALLOCATED BUFFER    @ @@@@          OFF       CHECK     @ @@@@      ZD
)@@G@@    ON        STATS     @F@@@@          LA        A1,RELCALL          LOZE
)@@G@@AD NUMBER OF BREL CALLS @D@@@@          AA,U      A1,1                INZF
)@@G@@CREMENT IT  @F@@@@          SA        A1,RELCALL          UPDATE TOTAL BZG
)@@G@@REL CALLS   @G@@@@          LA        A1,INUSE            LOAD NUMBER OFZH
)@@G@@ WORDS IN USE     @E@@@@          AA        A1,SIZE,A0          COMPUTE ZI
)@@G@@NEW TOTAL   @E@@@@          SA        A1,INUSE            UPDATE THE TOTZJ
)@@G@@AL    @ @@@@          OFF       STATS     @F@@@@          LA        A2,HZK
)@@G@@L,A0            IS PREVIOUS BLOCK IN USE ?@G@@@@          JNZ       A2,BZL
)@@G@@RL1             NO.  A2 POINTS TO PREVIOUS BLOCK@F@@@@.                 ZM
)@@G@@                      CHAIN TO AVAILABLE LIST   @E@@@@          LA,U    ZN
)@@G@@  A2,HEAD             GET HEAD OF CHAIN   @F@@@@          SA        A2,BZO
)@@G@@L,A0            CHAIN NEW BLOCK TO HEAD   @E@@@@          LA        A2,HZP
)@@G@@EAD+FL          GET FIRST AVAILABLE @E@@@@          SA        A2,FL,A0  ZQ
)@@G@@          CHAIN TO THIS BLOCK @F@@@@          SA        A0,HEAD+FL      ZR
)@@G@@    THIS BUFFER IS NOW FIRST  @I@@@@          SA        A0,BL,A2        ZS
)@@G@@    MAKE OLD FIRST BUFFER POINT TO THIS ONE     @H@@@@          LA,U    ZT
)@@G@@  A2,,A0              LOAD ADDRESS OF BLOCK BEING RETURNED  @E@@@@BRL1  ZU
)@@G@@    ANU       A0,SIZE,A0          POINT TO NEXT BLOCK @ @@@@          ONZV
)@@G@@        CHECK     @F@@@@          TZ        HL,A1               IS BLOCKZW
)@@G@@ MARKED IN USE ?  @F@@@@          KABONG    3                   YES.  BAZX
)@@G@@D NEXT BUFFER LINK@ @@@@          OFF       CHECK     @F@@@@          TPZY
)@@G@@        SIZE,A1             IS NEXT BLOCK AVAILABLE ? @F@@@@          J ZZ
)@@G@@        BRL2                NO.  CANNOT COMBINE IT    @G@@@@.           AA
)@@G@@                            REMOVE NEXT BLOCK FROM FREE LIST@G@@@@      AB
)@@G@@    LXM       X11,FL,A1           GET FORWARD LINK OF NEXT BLOCK  @E@@@@AC
)@@G@@          LA        A0,BL,A1            ...AND BACKWARD LINK@H@@@@      AD
)@@G@@    SX        X11,FL,A0           UPDATE FORWARD LINK OF PREVIOUS BUFFERAE
)@@G@@@H@@@@          SA        A0,BL,X11           UPDATE BACKWARD LINK OF NEAF
)@@G@@XT BUFFER   @G@@@@          AA        A1,SIZE,A1          POINT TO NEXT AG
)@@G@@BLOCK IN CORE     @E@@@@BRL2      SA        A2,HL,A1            POINT NEAH
)@@G@@XT BLOCK    @E@@@@          ANA,U     A1,,A2              COMPUTE TOTAL AI
)@@G@@LENGTH@G@@@@          SA        A1,SIZE,A2          STORE SIZE, MARKING AJ
)@@G@@AVAILABLE   @B@@@@          ON        CORREL**(MANREL=0)    @E@@@@BRL5  AK
)@@G@@    AA,U      A1,1,A2             A1 = END OF BUFFER+1@F@@@@          TNAL
)@@G@@E       A1,LASTD            IS THIS THE END OF CORE ? @H@@@@          J AM
)@@G@@        BRL3                YES.  THINK ABOUT LCORE$ POSSIBILITIES@B@@@@AN
)@@G@@          OFF       CORREL**(MANREL=0)    @[@@@@BRL4. @^@@@@          ONAO
)@@G@@        WAIT@E@@@@          LA        A0,QTF              QUEUE POINTERSAP
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@          TNZ       QCOUNT,A0           IF FROM-QUEUE EMPTY,AQ
)@@G@@@D@@@@          SSC       A0,18               SWITCH THEM.  @ @@@@      AR
)@@G@@    SA        A0,QTF    @F@@@@          LMJ       A2,QUF              STAS
)@@G@@ART WAITING ACTIVITIES. @^@@@@          OFF       WAIT@D@@@@          DLAT
)@@G@@        A1,SVA1             RESTORE A1-A2.@E@@@@          V         CRITAU
)@@G@@                OPEN CRITICAL CODE. @F@@@@          LA        A0,X11    AV
)@@G@@          GET BACK RETURN POINT     @F@@@@          SSL       A0,18     AW
)@@G@@          MOVE RETURN TO MODIFIER   @C@@@@          J         0,A0      AX
)@@G@@          RETURN  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         RELEASE FREE EXPANSION BLOAY
)@@G@@CKS   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON        CORREL    @G@@@@BRL3      ANAZ
)@@G@@A,U     A1,1                POINT TO FINAL (BARRIER) WORD   @E@@@@      BA
)@@G@@    LMA,XH2   A0,,A1              LOAD SIZE SENTINEL  @F@@@@          TEBB
)@@G@@        A0,SIZE,A2          IS THE WHOLE BLOCK FREE ? @E@@@@          J BC
)@@G@@        BRL4                NO.  SKIP THIS STUFF@ @@@@          ON      BD
)@@G@@  TRACE     @E@@@@          TNZ       BTRACE              TRACING REQUESBE
)@@G@@TS ?  @F@@@@          J         BRL3T               NO.  SKIP LCORE LOGGBF
)@@G@@ING   @E@@@@          E$BO      15,T$RTRN,6         EDIT WORDS RELEASED BG
)@@G@@@F@@@@          PRINT$    T$RTRN,T$LRTRN      PRINT LOGGING MESSAGE     BH
)@@G@@@]@@@@BRL3T     . @ @@@@          OFF       TRACE     @F@@@@.           BI
)@@G@@                            UNCHAIN FROM FREE LIST    @G@@@@          LABJ
)@@G@@        A0,FL,A2            LOAD POINTER TO NEXT BUFFER     @G@@@@      BK
)@@G@@    LX        A1,BL,A2            LOAD POINTER TO LAST BUFFER     @E@@@@BL
)@@G@@          SA        A0,FL,A1            CHAIN NEXT TO LAST  @E@@@@      BM
)@@G@@    SX        A1,BL,A0            CHAIN LAST TO NEXT  @F@@@@          SABN
)@@G@@        A2,LASTD            UPDATE NEXT FREE WORD     @E@@@@          LABO
)@@G@@,U      A0,,A2              LOAD TOP OF CORE    @G@@@@          ANA,U   BP
)@@G@@  A0,1                PARAMETER IS HIGHEST WORD NEEDED@G@@@@          LXBQ
)@@G@@I,U     A0,0200000          SET FOR PROGRAM-WIDE RELEASE    @E@@@@      BR
)@@G@@    LCORE$    .                   RELEASE UNUSED CORE @F@@@@          LXBS
)@@G@@I,U     A0                  CLEAR PROGRAM-WIDE FLAG   @F@@@@          TLBT
)@@G@@E,U     A0,LASTD$+1         ARE WE STILL EXPANDED ?   @C@@@@          J BU
)@@G@@        BRL4                RETURN  @H@@@@          LA,XH2    A1,,A0    BV
)@@G@@          YES.  LOAD LENGTH FROM THIS BARRIER   @G@@@@          AU,U    BW
)@@G@@  A1,,A0              A2 = ADDRESS OF LAST BUFFER HEAD@F@@@@          LABX
)@@G@@        A1,SIZE,A2          LOAD SIZE OF THAT BUFFER  @H@@@@          JNBY
)@@G@@        A1,BRL4             DONE WITH CONTRACTION OF THIS ONE BUSY@ @@@@BZ
)@@G@@          ON        MANREL    @H@@@@          AA,U      A1,1,A2         CA
)@@G@@    COMPUTE END OF BUFFER + 1 ADDRESS     @I@@@@          TNE       A1,LCB
)@@G@@ASTD            DOES THIS BUFFER ABUT THE END OF MEMORY?    @F@@@@      CC
)@@G@@    J         BRL3                YES.  INVESTIGATE LCORE$  @G@@@@      CD
)@@G@@    J         BRL4                NO.  NO FURTHER RELEASE POSSIBLE@ @@@@CE
)@@G@@          OFF       MANREL    @ @@@@          ON        MANREL=0  @F@@@@CF
)@@G@@          J         BRL5                CHECK FOR FURTHER RELEASES@ @@@@CG
)@@G@@          OFF       MANREL=0  @ @@@@          OFF       CORREL    @[@@@@CH
)@@G@@/.    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         RELEASE ANY AVAILABLE EXPANSION BUFFERCI
)@@G@@S     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         LMJ       X11,BRELC @E@@@@.         <RCJ
)@@G@@ETURN>                      X11, A0 DESTROYED   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.     CK
)@@G@@    IF THE CONFIGURATION TAGS MANUAL AND LCORE ARE SET, THIS CODE WILL  CL
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         BE ENABLED TO PERMIT THE RELEASE OF EXPANSION BLOCKS AT CM
)@@G@@ANY   @C@@@@.         TIME DESIRED BY THE CALLING PROGRAM.  @[@@@@.     CN
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        MANREL    @E@@@@BRELC*    LXI,U     X11,,X11  CO
)@@G@@          SAVE ENTRY ADDRESS  @G@@@@          P         CRIT            CP
)@@G@@    INVOKE CRITICAL SECTION LOCK    @D@@@@          DS        A1,SVA1   CQ
)@@G@@          SAVE A1, A2   @G@@@@          LA        A1,LASTD            LOCR
)@@G@@AD LAST ALLOCATED ADDRESS + 1 @G@@@@          TLE,U     A1,LASTD$+1     CS
)@@G@@    ARE WE EXPANDED CURRENTLY ?     @F@@@@          J         BRL4      CT
)@@G@@          NO.  DON'T NEED TO RELEASE@H@@@@          LA,U      A2,HEAD   CU
)@@G@@          LOAD ADDRESS OF BUFFER CHAIN HEAD     @G@@@@BRC1      LA      CV
)@@G@@  A2,FL,A2            CHAIN TO NEXT AVAILABLE BUFFER  @F@@@@          TNCW
)@@G@@E,U     A2,HEAD             END OF CHAIN AND NO FIND ?@G@@@@          J CX
)@@G@@        BRL4                YES.  RETURN HAVING DONE NOTHING@F@@@@      CY
)@@G@@    LA        A1,SIZE,A2          LOAD SIZE OF THIS BUFFER  @G@@@@      CZ
)@@G@@    JN        A1,BRC1             IGNORE IT IF IT'S ALLOCATED     @H@@@@DA
)@@G@@          AA,U      A1,1,A2             COMPUTE FIRST WORD AFTER THIS BUDB
)@@G@@FFER  @G@@@@          TE        A1,LASTD            IS IT LAST WORD ALLODC
)@@G@@CATED ?     @H@@@@          J         BRC1                NO.  THIS BUFFDD
)@@G@@ER DOES NOT ADJOIN END  @H@@@@          J         BRL3                YEDE
)@@G@@S.  THIS BUFFER IS AT END AND AVAIL @F@@@@.                             DF
)@@G@@          GO ENTER RELEASE CODE     @ @@@@          OFF       MANREL    DG
)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         STATISTICS EDITOR   @[@@@@.     DH
)@@G@@@ @@@@.         LMJ       X11,BSTATP@E@@@@.         <RETURN>            DI
)@@G@@          NO REGISTERS CHANGED@[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON        STATDJ
)@@G@@S     @E@@@@BSTATP*   P         CRIT                SET CRITICAL SECTIONDK
)@@G@@@C@@@@          SA        A0,SVA1             SAVE A0 @F@@@@          LADL
)@@G@@        A0,GETCALL          LOAD NUMBER OF BGET CALLS @E@@@@          E$DM
)@@G@@BO      8,STATMS,8          EDIT INTO MESSAGE   @F@@@@          LA      DN
)@@G@@  A0,RELCALL          GET NUMBER OF REL CALLS   @G@@@@          E$BO    DO
)@@G@@  29,STATMS,8         AND PUT IT INTO THE MESSAGE     @G@@@@          LADP
)@@G@@        A0,INUSE            LOAD NUMBER OF WORDS IN USE     @E@@@@      DQ
)@@G@@    E$BO      48,STATMS,6         EDIT WORDS IN USE   @F@@@@          LNDR
)@@G@@A       A0,MAXUSE           LOAD MAXIMUM WORDS IN USE @D@@@@          E$DS
)@@G@@BO      89,STATMS,6         EDIT THAT     @^@@@@          ON        WAITDT
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A0,WAITC            LOAD NUMBER OF DELAYS.    DU
)@@G@@@C@@@@          E$BO      97,STATMS,6         EDIT IT.@^@@@@          OFDV
)@@G@@F       WAIT@G@@@@          PRINT$    STATMS,STATMSL      PRINT THE CURRDW
)@@G@@ENT STATISTICS    @E@@@@          LA        A0,SVA1             LOAD UP DX
)@@G@@USER'S A0   @F@@@@          V         CRIT                CLEAR CRITICALDY
)@@G@@ SECTION    @D@@@@          J         0,X11               RETURN TO CALLDZ
)@@G@@@ @@@@          OFF       STATS     @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.     EA
)@@G@@    ERROR AND TRACE HANDLER   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON        ERRLEB
)@@G@@EV>1  @E@@@@KABTRAP   LMJ       A2,$+1              SAVE ADDRESS TRAPPEDEC
)@@G@@@F@@@@          ANA,U     A2,1                BACK UP TO EX INSTRUCTION ED
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LA,H1     A2,,A2              RECOVER ERROR CODE  @D@@@@EE
)@@G@@          LSSL      A2,18+10            SHIFT OFF F, J@F@@@@          SSEF
)@@G@@L       A2,18+10+4          SHIFT OFF X, RIGHT JUSTIFY@F@@@@          LXEG
)@@G@@I,U     A0,,A2              SAVE ERROR CODE FOR USER  @F@@@@          TEEH

)@@G@@G1              YES.  MUST CONVERT X11 TO USER RETURN @ @@@@          ONEK
)@@G@@        EXPINC=0  @G@@@@          TNE,U     A2,4                WAS IT NEL
)@@G@@O MORE CORE ERROR ?     @H@@@@          LNA,XU    A0,NCWIU,A0         YEEM

)@@G@@@]@@@@KABNG2    . @ @@@@          ON        ERRLEV>2  @G@@@@          E$EP
)@@G@@BO      41,REGM,6           EDIT A0 CONTENTS INTO MESSAGE   @E@@@@      EQ

)@@G@@BO      22,REGM,6           EDIT IT INTO THE MESSAGE  @F@@@@          SSES

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@C     @A@@@@C     DIRECTORY VALIDATION PROGRAM  @[@@@@SL

)@@G@@N)')  @^@@@@      READ 2, ANSWER    @#@@@@2     FORMAT (A1) @#@@@@      ST

)@@G@@)) PRT = 1  @#@@@@      SAVPRT = PRT@[@@@@C     @H@@@@C     CALL DIREND SV

)@@G@@                @ COUNT LUT SECTORS @^@@@@      ERROR = .FALSE.   @B@@@@SZ
)@@G@@10    CALL DIRLUT (ECODE,$999,LUTBUF)     @B@@@@11    IF (PRT .NE. 0) PRTA
)@@G@@INT 105, LUTSEC   @A@@@@105   FORMAT ('0LUT SECTOR',I5)     @G@@@@      TB
)@@G@@DO 20 I = 1,28                    @ FOR EACH WORD OF LUT SECTOR...@G@@@@TC

)@@G@@@E@@@@      LINK = LUTBUF(I)                  @ GET SI/LI LINK    @D@@@@TE
)@@G@@      IF (LINK .EQ. 0) GOTO 20          @ SKIP IF ZERO@^@@@@      CALL CTF
)@@G@@HECK ($11)  @F@@@@      IF (LINK .LT. 0) GOTO 15          @ JUMP IF SEARTG
)@@G@@CH ITEM     @[@@@@C     @A@@@@C     LINK POINTS TO A LEAD ITEM    @[@@@@TH
)@@G@@C     @^@@@@      CALL DOLINK ($11) @F@@@@      IF (PRT .NE. 0) PRINT 11TI
)@@G@@0, J, LINK, SECBUF(2), SECBUF(3),   @ @@@@     *SECBUF(4), SECBUF(5)    TJ

)@@G@@6)    @#@@@@      GOTO 20     @[@@@@C     @A@@@@C     LINK POINTS TO A STL

)@@G@@     '@ @@@@      IF (ERROR) Q = '??????' @C@@@@      IF (PRT .NE. 0) PRTN
)@@G@@INT 120, J, LINK, Q     @E@@@@120   FORMAT (' WORD',I3,12X,O12,' = SEARCTO
)@@G@@H ITEM   ',A6)    @H@@@@      DO 18 K = 1,5                     @ FOR EATP
)@@G@@CH ENTRY IN SEARCH ITEM...    @ @@@@      KK = (K - 1) * 5 + 2    @E@@@@TQ
)@@G@@      LINK = SECBUF(KK+4)               @ GET LI LINK       @D@@@@      TR
)@@G@@IF (LINK .EQ. 0) GOTO 18          @ SKIP IF ZERO@^@@@@      CALL CHECK (TS
)@@G@@$11)  @G@@@@      IF (PRT .NE. 0) PRINT 121, K, LINK, SECBUF(KK), SECBUFTT
)@@G@@(KK+1),     @A@@@@     *SECBUF(KK+2), SECBUF(KK+3)    @G@@@@121   FORMATTU
)@@G@@ (10X,'ENTRY',I3,2X,O12,' = LEAD ITEM FOR  ',2A6,' * ',2A6) @E@@@@18    TV

)@@G@@ES   FOR  EXEC-8.   FOR  MOST  ER'S,  TWO  PROC  CALLS  ARE @H@@@@.     XV
)@@G@@     SUPPLIED:   ONE,  CALLED  BY  THE  ER  NAME (E.G, THE PRINT$ ER IS XW
)@@G@@@H@@@@.          GENERATED  BY  A  PROC CALLED PRINT$), IS DESIGNATED THXX
)@@G@@E IMMEDIATE @H@@@@.          VERSION.   THIS  PROC GENERATES THE MOST COXY
)@@G@@MMONLY USED FORM OF THE @H@@@@.          CALLING  SEQUENCE.   THE  OTHERXZ
)@@G@@  FORM, CONSISTING OF THE PROC NAME @H@@@@.          FOLLOWED  BY  THE  YA
)@@G@@LETTER  'P'  (PRINT$P)  ACCEPTS  A  PACKET  AND @H@@@@.          GENERATYB
)@@G@@ES THE APPROPRIATE INSTRUCTIONS TO LOAD THE PACKET ADDRESS. @[@@@@.     YC
)@@G@@@H@@@@.                  IN  EVERY CASE, SIMPLY WRITING THE ER NAME WITHYD
)@@G@@ NO PARAME- @H@@@@.          TERS WILL GENERATE ONLY THE ER INSTRUCTION.YE
)@@G@@  THAT IS, THE CALL:    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.                  PRINT$     YF
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.          WILL GENERATE:     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.     YG
)@@G@@             ER        PRINT$ @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                  THE  YH
)@@G@@IMMEDIATE  PROCS  ARE DESIGNED FOR CONVENIENCE RATHER @H@@@@.          TYI
)@@G@@HAN  CONSISTENCY.   PARAMETERS ARE ARRANGED SO THAT THE MOST FRE- @H@@@@YJ
)@@G@@.          QUENTLY OMITTED PARAMETERS OCCUR LAST.  OMITTED PARAMETERS ARYK
)@@G@@E SET @H@@@@.          TO  THE  MOST  COMMONLY  USED  VALUE, NOT NECESSAYL
)@@G@@RILY ZERO.  AS AN @H@@@@.          ILLUSTRATION  OF  THIS  PHILOSOPHY, LYM
)@@G@@ET US TAKE THE EXAMPLE OF THE @H@@@@.          PROC TO GENERATE THE SNAPYN
)@@G@@$ CALLING SEQUENCE.  THE FULL FORM IS:    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.           YO
)@@G@@       SNAP$,'<REGS>'  <ADDRESS>,<LENGTH>,'<IDENT>'   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@YP
)@@G@@.          AN EXAMPLE OF A CALL WITH ALL PARAMETERS IS:     @[@@@@.     YQ
)@@G@@@C@@@@.                  SNAP$,'XAR'  WORDB,3,'WORDB' @[@@@@.     @C@@@@YR
)@@G@@.          THE OMISSION RULES ARE AS FOLLOWS:   @F@@@@.                 YS
)@@G@@ IF <IDENT> IS OMITTED, IT IS SET TO SPACES.    @H@@@@.                 YT
)@@G@@ IF  '<REGS>'  IS  THE  ONLY  SPECIFICATION,  ALL THE OTHER @H@@@@.     YU
)@@G@@     PARAMETERS  WILL  BE  SET  TO  ZERO,  SO A REGISTER-ONLY DUMP WILL YV
)@@G@@@#@@@@.          OCCUR. @H@@@@.                  IF  <ADDRESS>  IS  SPECYW
)@@G@@IFIED AND <LENGTH> IS NOT, <LENGTH> @C@@@@.          WILL BE ASSUMED TO YX
)@@G@@BE 1.  IN SUMMARY:@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                  SNAP$,'XA'       YY
)@@G@@    . DUMPS X AND A REGISTERS @H@@@@.                  SNAP$     TCELL  YZ
)@@G@@    . DUMPS ONE WORD STARTING AT TCELL    @H@@@@.                  SNAP$ZA
)@@G@@     TCELL,4    . DUMPS 4 WORDS STARTING AT TCELL     @H@@@@.           ZB
)@@G@@       SNAP$,'A' ,,'A0-A15' . DUMPS THE A REGISTERS WITH LABEL    @[@@@@ZC
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@.                  IN GENERAL, THESE PROCS ARE EASIER TO USEZD
)@@G@@ THAN TO EXPLAIN. @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                  PROCS  WHICH  GENZE
)@@G@@ERATE  PACKETS ONE OR TWO WORDS IN LENGTH @H@@@@.          GENERATE  THEZF
)@@G@@M USING THE ASSEMBLER LITERAL MECHANISM.  PROCS WHICH @H@@@@.          GZG
)@@G@@ENERATE  LONGER  PACKETS  SWITCH TO AN ALTERNATE LOCATION COUNTER @H@@@@ZH
)@@G@@.          FOR  THE  PACKET.   THIS COUNTER IS SPECIFIED BY THE ASSEMBLYZI
)@@G@@-TIME @H@@@@.          VARIABLE  CTL$BNK(0).   IF  NOT  SPECIFIED,  THESZJ
)@@G@@E  DATA  WILL  BE @H@@@@.          ASSEMBLED  INTO  $(0).   THE  PROC LIZK
)@@G@@T$, SUPPLIED IN THIS ELEMENT, @H@@@@.          WILL  EQUATE  THE  TAG CTZL
)@@G@@L$BNK(0) TO ITS PARAMETER (OR THE CURRENT @H@@@@.          LOCATION  COUZM
)@@G@@NTER  IF NO PARAMETER IS SUPPLIED).  IT THEN SWITCHES @H@@@@.          TZN
)@@G@@O  THAT  LOCATION COUNTER, AND EXECUTES A LIT DIRECTIVE UNDER THE @ @@@@ZO
)@@G@@.          COUNTER.  THUS:    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.          $(2)    LIT$ ZP
)@@G@@           (OR)            LIT$     2     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.          IZQ

)@@G@@N COUNTER, THERE IS A PROC WITH THE NAME <ER-NAME>PKT WHICH @H@@@@.     ZU

)@@G@@.     @E@@@@.         IALL$     <ADDRESS>,<SELECTION>,<APPLICATION>     LL

)@@G@@LL$     <ADDRESS>,<PARAMETER>,<PARAMETER>,...   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.     LN

)@@G@@D 'ACT'     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@IALL$P*   NALT

)@@G@@    EQU       'IOPR'    @ @@@@A(2)      EQU       'IGDM'    @ @@@@A(3)  LX
)@@G@@    EQU       'IFOF'    @ @@@@A(4)      EQU       'IFUF'    @ @@@@A(5)  LY
)@@G@@    EQU       'IDOF'    @ @@@@A(6)      EQU       'IRST'    @ @@@@A(7)  LZ
)@@G@@    EQU       'IABT'    @ @@@@A(8)      EQU       'IINT'    @ @@@@A(9)  MA
)@@G@@    EQU       'ITS'     @ @@@@A(10)     EQU       'ERR$'    @F@@@@A(11) MB
)@@G@@    EQU       'IAI'               INTER ACTIVITY INTERRUPT  @ @@@@A(12) MC
)@@G@@    EQU       'BRKPT'   @ @@@@A(13)     EQU       'PARITY'  @ @@@@A(14) MD
)@@G@@    EQU       'TIME'    @G@@@@C         EQU       15                  FIME
)@@G@@RST APPLICATION SUBSCRIPT     @ @@@@A(C)      EQU       *'PGM'    @ @@@@MF
)@@G@@A(C+1)    EQU       *'PROGRAM'@ @@@@A(C+2)    EQU       *'ACT'    @A@@@@MG
)@@G@@A(C+3)    EQU       *'ACTIVITY'     @ @@@@A(C+4)    EQU       *'ESI'    MH
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@B(0)      EQU       (P(1)=2)+2*(P(1)=3)   @F@@@@I     MI
)@@G@@    DO        B(0) ,J DO A , DO P(1,I+1)=A(J) ,B(0) EQU 0   @C@@@@I     MJ
)@@G@@    DO        B(0) ,B(I-1) EQU P(1,I+1)   @F@@@@I         DO        P(1)MK
)@@G@@-(P(1)>0) ,J DO A , DO P(1,I+1)=A(J) ,;   @E@@@@B(A(*J))  EQU       B(A(ML
)@@G@@*J))++1*/((J-C*A(*J))*/-A(*J)-1)    @C@@@@DP        EQU       (B(0)<0)++MM
)@@G@@(B(0)>1*/12-1)    @B@@@@IF        FORM      12,6,18,18*DP,18*DP   @D@@@@MN
)@@G@@          DO        DP , DL 12,(IF ,B(1),P(1,1),,B(0))@F@@@@          DOMO
)@@G@@        (P(1)>0)**1-DP , LA 12,(IF B(0),B(1),P(1,1))  @ @@@@          ERMP
)@@G@@        IALL$     @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         COMQ
)@@G@@NTINGENCY TERMINATION   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      0,1 @^@@@@MR
)@@G@@CEND$*    NAME      0   @^@@@@CRTN$*     NAME      1  @B@@@@           DMS
)@@G@@O        P(0,0)=0 , ER CEND$  @B@@@@           DO        P(0,0)=1 , ER CMT
)@@G@@RTN$  @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         SET THE 1110 HMU
)@@G@@ARDWARE BREAKPOINT REGISTER   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         SETPB$,<CONTROMV
)@@G@@L>,<ADDR-MASK>,<BDI>   <ADDRESS>    @A@@@@.         SETBP$P,<BDI>     <PMW
)@@G@@ACKET>@[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         <CONTROL> IS 'P', 'W', 'R', 'WR' OR 'RMX
)@@G@@W'    @F@@@@.                   (THE  DEFAULT  IS  ZERO  WHICH  THE  EXEMY
)@@G@@C     @B@@@@.                   INTERPRETS AS 'P'.)   @F@@@@.         <AMZ
)@@G@@DDR-MASK>  IS IN THE RANGE 0 TO 077 AND SPECIFIES     @F@@@@.           NA
)@@G@@        WHICH LOW-ORDER  BITS  OF  <ADDRESS>  ARE     @D@@@@.           NB
)@@G@@        RELEVANT.  THE DEFAULT IS 077.    @A@@@@.         <BDI>     IS ONC
)@@G@@PTIONAL.    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@SETBP$*   NAND
)@@G@@ME      0   @^@@@@L(1)      EQU       'W' @^@@@@L(2)      EQU       'R' NE
)@@G@@@^@@@@L(3)      EQU       'WR'@^@@@@L(4)      EQU       'P' @C@@@@      NF
)@@G@@    DO        P(0,1)='RW' ,P(0,1) EQU 3   @D@@@@I         DO        L , NG
)@@G@@DO P(0,1)=L(I) ,P(0,1) EQU I  @C@@@@          DO        P(0)>3 ,P(0,1) ENH
)@@G@@QU P(0,1)++8@ @@@@F         FORM      18,2,4,6,6@D@@@@P(3)      EQU     NI
)@@G@@  +(F 0,,P(0,1),P(0,2)+077*(P(0)<3))@D@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 ,P(NJ
)@@G@@2) EQU +(EQUF$ P(1),1)  @H@@@@          DO        (P(2)<1*/16)*(P(1)+P(0NK
)@@G@@)>1) , LA 12,+(OPT$$ P(3),P(2))     @^@@@@SETBP$P*  NAME      1   @H@@@@NL
)@@G@@    DO  (P(1)>0)**P(0,0)++(P(2)>1*/16-1) , LA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1,2-2*P(0,NM
)@@G@@0))   @E@@@@          DO        (P(2)>1*/16-1)*(P(0)>1) , LXI,14 12,P(3)NN
)@@G@@@G@@@@          DO        P(0)>3-2*P(0,0) , LA 13,+(EQUF$ P(0),3-2*P(0,0NO
)@@G@@),*1) @ @@@@          ER        SETBP$    @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@NP
)@@G@@.     @A@@@@.         BASE A DOWNED CORE BANK   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.     NQ
)@@G@@    ABSAD$    <ABS-ADDR>,<SIZE>,<BDI>     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PRNR
)@@G@@OC      *1  @^@@@@ABSAD$*   NAME      0   @ @@@@M         FORM      18,1NS
)@@G@@8,36  @F@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA,14 12,(M P(1,2),P(1,3),P(1,1NT
)@@G@@))    @^@@@@ABSAD$P*  NAME      1   @F@@@@          DO        (P(1)>0)**NU
)@@G@@(P(0,0)=1) , LA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1,2)@ @@@@          ER        ABSAD$    NV
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         ACTIVITY/PROCESSOR DNW
)@@G@@EDICATION   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         ADED$     <PROCESSOR MASK>@[@@@@NX
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@ADED$*    NAME      1   @^@@@@NY
)@@G@@ADED$P*   NAME      -0  @E@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA 12,+(EQUF$NZ
)@@G@@ P(1),1,P(0,0))   @ @@@@          ER        ADED$     @#@@@@          ENOA
)@@G@@D     @D@@@@/.        C O N S O L E   C O M M U N I C A T I O N S @[@@@@OB
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.         COM$,<CONSOLE>  <OUTAD>,<OUTLEN> <INAD>,<INLEN>,<COC
)@@G@@ONTROL>     @E@@@@.                   <CONSOLE> MAY BE 'S', 'I', 'C', OROD
)@@G@@ 'H'. @D@@@@.                   ASSUMES 50 CHARACTERS FOR LENGTHS @[@@@@OE
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@Q         PROC      *2  @^@@@@COM$PGEN*  NAME     0   @^@@@@OF
)@@G@@C(1)      EQU       'S' @^@@@@C(2)      EQU       'I' @^@@@@C(3)      EQOG
)@@G@@U       'C' @^@@@@C(4)      EQU       'H' @ @@@@B(0)      EQU       P(0,OH
)@@G@@1)    @D@@@@I         DO        C , DO B(0)=C(I) ,B(0) EQU I-1    @A@@@@OI
)@@G@@Q1        FORM      6,6,6,18,6,12,18@F@@@@          Q1        0,B(0),P(2OJ
)@@G@@,3),,,P(1,2)+50*(P(1)=1),P(1,1)     @C@@@@          *         P(2,2)+50*OK
)@@G@@(P(2)=1),P(2,1)   @D@@@@          DO        P(2,3)>037 , RES 1. FOR RUNIOL
)@@G@@D     @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *2  OM
)@@G@@@^@@@@COM$PKT*  NAME      0   @#@@@@          COM$PGEN@#@@@@          ENON
)@@G@@D     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *2  @^@@@@COM$*     NAME    OO
)@@G@@  0   @D@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA,14 12,$(CTL$BNK(0))   @ @@@@OP
)@@G@@$(CTL$BNK(0)),F*   PROC      0@#@@@@          COM$PGEN@#@@@@          ENOQ
)@@G@@D     @^@@@@          ER        COM$@ @@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , FOR
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@OS
)@@G@@COM$P*    NAME      0   @D@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA 12,+(EQUF$OT
)@@G@@ P(1),1,2)  @^@@@@          ER        COM$@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@OU
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@.         AWAIT REMOTE BREAK (@@X C) OR CONSOLE II KEYIN    OV
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@.         II$     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC    OW
)@@G@@  0,1 @^@@@@II$*      NAME      0   @^@@@@          ER        II$ @#@@@@OX
)@@G@@          END     @D@@@@/.        S N A P S H O T  D U M P  R E Q U E S OY
)@@G@@T     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         SNAP$PKT,'<REGS>'  <ADDRESS>,<LENGTH>,OZ
)@@G@@'<ID>'@[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         ASSUMES 1 FOR LENGTH IF ADDRESS IS SPEPA
)@@G@@CIEIED@A@@@@.         <REGS> IS 'XA', 'AR', ... @B@@@@.         ID IS SEPB
)@@G@@T TO SPACES IF OMITTED  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@Q         PROC      0,3 @^@@@@PC
)@@G@@SNAP$PGEN*  NAME    0   @B@@@@          DO        P(1)>2 , LJSF$1 P(1,3)PD
)@@G@@@C@@@@          DO        P(1)<3 , * 050505050505     @^@@@@X         EQPE
)@@G@@U       4   @^@@@@A         EQU       2   @^@@@@R         EQU       1   PF
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         SNAP REGISTER CODES @[@@@@.     @^@@@@V(1)  PG
)@@G@@    EQU       'X' @^@@@@V(2)      EQU       'A' @^@@@@V(3)      EQU     PH
)@@G@@  'R' @^@@@@V(4)      EQU       'XA'@^@@@@V(5)      EQU       'AX'@^@@@@PI
)@@G@@V(6)      EQU       'AR'@^@@@@V(7)      EQU       'RA'@^@@@@V(8)      EQPJ
)@@G@@U       'RX'@^@@@@V(9)      EQU       'XR'@ @@@@V(10)     EQU       'XARPK
)@@G@@'     @ @@@@V(11)     EQU       'XRA'     @ @@@@V(12)     EQU       'RAXPL
)@@G@@'     @ @@@@V(13)     EQU       'RXA'     @ @@@@V(14)     EQU       'ARXPM
)@@G@@'     @ @@@@V(15)     EQU       'AXR'     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         NUPN
)@@G@@MERIC CODES FOR REGISTER SELECTION  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@Z(1)      EQU     PO
)@@G@@  X   @^@@@@Z(2)      EQU       A   @^@@@@Z(3)      EQU       R   @^@@@@PP
)@@G@@Z(4)      EQU       X+A @^@@@@Z(5)      EQU       X+A @^@@@@Z(6)      EQPQ
)@@G@@U       A+R @^@@@@Z(7)      EQU       A+R @^@@@@Z(8)      EQU       X+R PR
)@@G@@@^@@@@Z(9)      EQU       X+R @ @@@@Z(10)     EQU       X+A+R     @ @@@@PS
)@@G@@Z(11)     EQU       X+A+R     @ @@@@Z(12)     EQU       X+A+R     @ @@@@PT
)@@G@@Z(13)     EQU       X+A+R     @ @@@@Z(14)     EQU       X+A+R     @ @@@@PU
)@@G@@Z(15)     EQU       X+A+R     @ @@@@SF        FORM      3,15,18,36@G@@@@PV
)@@G@@I         DO        P(0)-1 ,J DO V , DO P(0,I)=V(J) ,RG(I) EQU Z(J)     PW
)@@G@@@G@@@@I         DO        P(0)-1 ,RG(0) EQU RG(0)++RG(I)++P(0,I)*(RG(I)=PX
)@@G@@0)    @D@@@@          SF        RG(0),P(1,2)+(P(1)=1),P(1,1),0    @#@@@@PY
)@@G@@          END     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      1,3 @^@@@@SNAP$PPZ
)@@G@@KT*  NAME     0   @^@@@@          SNAP$PGEN     @#@@@@          END     QA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @H@@@@.         IMMEDIATE CALLING SEQUENCE  (PACKET GENERATEQB
)@@G@@D IN $(CTL$BNK(0)))     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         SNAP$,'XAR'     <ADDQC
)@@G@@RESS>,<LENGTH>,'<IDENT>'@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@QD
)@@G@@SNAP$*    NAME      0   @ @@@@$(CTL$BNK(0)),F*   PROC      0@^@@@@      QE
)@@G@@    SNAP$PGEN     @#@@@@          END     @E@@@@          DO        P(0)QF
)@@G@@+P(1)>1 , SA 12,$(CTL$BNK(0))+2     @E@@@@          DO        P(0)+P(1)>QG
)@@G@@1 , LA,14 12,$(CTL$BNK(0))    @ @@@@          ER        SNAP$     @A@@@@QH
)@@G@@          DO        P(0)+P(1)>1 , F @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     QI
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         SNAP FROM SPECIFIED PACKET@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PRQJ
)@@G@@OC      *1  @^@@@@SNAP$P*   NAME      0   @F@@@@          DO        (P(1QK
)@@G@@)>0)**(P(1)<3) , SA 12,P(1,1)+2,P(1,2)    @D@@@@          DO        P(1)QL
)@@G@@>0 , LA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1,2)  @ @@@@          ER        SNAP$     @#@@@@QM
)@@G@@          END     @E@@@@/.        S Y M B I O N T   I N T E R F A C E   QN
)@@G@@E R ' S     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         OBTAIN INPUT IMAGES QO
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         READ$     <ADDRESS>,<EOF> @A@@@@.         ARQP
)@@G@@EAD$    <ADDRESS>,<EOF> @G@@@@.                                       ASQQ
)@@G@@SUMES $+2 FOR EOF ADDRESS     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  QR
)@@G@@@^@@@@READ$P*   NAME      *0  @^@@@@AREAD$P*  NAME      *1  @D@@@@      QS
)@@G@@    DO        P(1)>0 , LA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1)    @^@@@@READ$*    NAME    QT
)@@G@@  0   @^@@@@AREAD$*   NAME      1   @H@@@@          DO        1-P(0,*0)*QU
)@@G@@*(P(1)>0) , LA 12,(($+2)*(P(1)=1)+P(1,2),P(1,1))@B@@@@          DO      QV
)@@G@@  P(0,0)=0 , ER READ$   @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=1 , ER AREAD$  QW
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         WRITE INTO PRINT FILQX
)@@G@@E     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         PRINT$    <ADDRESS>,<LENGTH>,<SPACING>QY
)@@G@@@C@@@@.         APRINT$   <ADDRESS>,<LENGTH>,<SPACING>@H@@@@.           QZ
)@@G@@                            ASSUMED LENGTH = 22 FIELDATA, 33 ASCII@E@@@@RA
)@@G@@.                                       ASSUMED SPACING = 1 @[@@@@.     RB
)@@G@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@PRINT$P*  NAME      *0  @^@@@@APRINTRC
)@@G@@$P* NAME      *1  @D@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),RD
)@@G@@1)    @^@@@@PRINT$*   NAME      0   @^@@@@APRINT$*  NAME      1   @ @@@@RE
)@@G@@F         FORM      12,6,18   @C@@@@          DO        (1-P(0,*0))**(P(RF
)@@G@@1)>0) , ;   @I@@@@          LA        12,(F P(1,3)+(P(1)<3),(22+11*P(0,0RG
)@@G@@))*(P(1)<2)+P(1,2),P(1,1))    @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=0 , ER PRRH
)@@G@@INT$  @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=1 , ER APRINT$ @#@@@@          ENRI
)@@G@@D     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         OUTPUT PUNCH IMAGES TO PUNCH FILE     RJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         PUNCH$    <ADDRESS>,<LENGTH>    @B@@@@.     RK
)@@G@@    APUNCH$   <ADDRESS>,<LENGTH>    @I@@@@.                             RL
)@@G@@          ASSUMED <LENGTH> = 14 FIELDATA, 20 ASCII    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@RM
)@@G@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@PUNCH$P*  NAME      *0  @^@@@@APUNCH$P*  NRN
)@@G@@AME     *1  @D@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1)    RO
)@@G@@@^@@@@PUNCH$*   NAME      0   @^@@@@APUNCH$*  NAME      1   @C@@@@      RP
