)@@G@@(14+6*P(0,0))*(P(1)<2)+P(1,2),P(1,1)))    @B@@@@          DO        P(0,RR
)@@G@@0)=0 , ER PUNCH$  @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=1 , ER APUNCH$ @#@@@@RS
)@@G@@          END     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         ALTERNATE PRINT LINKAGE   RT
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @^@@@@Q         PROC      0,3 @^@@@@PRNTA$PGEN*  NAME   0   RU
)@@G@@@ @@@@PF        FORM      12,6,18   @H@@@@          PF        P(1,4)+(P(RV
)@@G@@1)<4),(22+11*P(0,0))*(P(1)<3)+P(1,3),P(1,2)     @ @@@@          LJSF$2  RW
)@@G@@  P(1,1)    @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC    RX
)@@G@@  1,3 @^@@@@PRNTA$PKT*  NAME    0   @^@@@@APRNTA$PKT*  NAME   1   @^@@@@RY
)@@G@@          PRNTA$PGEN    @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.     RZ
)@@G@@    PRNTA$    'FILENAME',<ADDRESS>,<LENGTH>,<SPACING> @E@@@@.         APSA
)@@G@@RNTA$   'FILENAME',<ADDRESS>,<LENGTH>,<SPACING> @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.     SB
)@@G@@                                  ASSUMED <LENGTH> IS 132 CHARACTERS    SC
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                                       ASSUMED <SPACING> IS 1    SD
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@PRNTA$*   NAME      0   SE

)@@G@@2,$(CTL$BNK(0))   @ @@@@$(CTL$BNK(0)),F*   PROC      0@^@@@@          PRSG

)@@G@@0)=1 , ER APRNTA$ @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         ALSN
)@@G@@TERNATE PUNCH     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         PNCHA$    'FILE',<ADDRESS>SO
)@@G@@,<LENGTH>   @C@@@@.         APNCHA$   'FILE',<ADDRESS>,<LENGTH>   @[@@@@SP

)@@G@@    PROC      *1  @^@@@@PNCHA$*   NAME      0   @^@@@@APNCHA$*  NAME    SX

)@@G@@>0 , F@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  TC

)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         ALTERNATE READER INTTG
)@@G@@ERFACE@[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         READA$    'FILENAME',<BUFFER>,<EOF>   TH
)@@G@@@C@@@@.         AREADA$   'FILENAME',<BUFFER>,<EOF>   @C@@@@.         ARTI

)@@G@@            READA$PKT ASSUMES (ER ERR$)   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@Q         PRTL
)@@G@@OC      0,3 @^@@@@READA$PGEN*  NAME   0   @A@@@@          *         P(1,TM
)@@G@@3),P(1,2)   @ @@@@          LJSF$2    P(1,1)    @#@@@@          END     TN

)@@G@@  P(0,0)=2 , ER ARDA$   @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.     UD
)@@G@@    CONTROL IMAGE SUBMISSION  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         PRTCN$    <ADDUE
)@@G@@RESS>,<LENGTH>    @B@@@@.         APRTCN$   <ADDRESS>,<LENGTH>    @B@@@@UF
)@@G@@.         PRTCA$    <ADDRESS>,<LENGTH>    @B@@@@.         APRTCA$   <ADDUG

)@@G@@ME      5   @^@@@@PCHCA$*   NAME      6   @^@@@@APCHCA$*  NAME      7   UP

)@@G@@P*   NAME    *2   @^@@@@APRTCA$P*  NAME    *3   @^@@@@PCHCN$P*   NAME   UR
)@@G@@ *4   @^@@@@APCHCN$P*  NAME    *5   @^@@@@PCHCA$P*   NAME    *6   @^@@@@US

)@@G@@ 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1)     @I@@@@          DO        P(1)=1 ,P(1,2) EQU (13UU
)@@G@@2-52*(P(0,0)**4))//(6-2*(P(0,0)**1))+;    @A@@@@                    (P(0UV
)@@G@@,0)**2)     @F@@@@          DO        1-P(0,*0)**(P(1)>0) , LA 12,(P(1,2UW

)@@G@@ ER APCHCN$ @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=6 , ER PCHCA$  @B@@@@      VB
)@@G@@    DO        P(0,0)=7 , ER APCHCA$ @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     VC

)@@G@@TILITY PROCS@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         LJSF$<N>  'STRING'  @ @@@@.     BC
)@@G@@    ALJSF$<N> 'STRING'  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                   <N>  MUST BD
)@@G@@ BE  1  OR  2  AND SPECIFES THE     @F@@@@.                   NUMBER OF BE
)@@G@@WORDS TO GENERATE.  THESE PROCS     @F@@@@.                   WILL   NEVBF
)@@G@@ER  SHIFT  OUT  THE  LOW  ORDER     @F@@@@.                   CHARACTER.BG
)@@G@@  THE PRECISION  OF  THE  INPUT     @E@@@@.                   STRING IS BH
)@@G@@IRRELEVANT TO THE RESULT.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  BI
)@@G@@@^@@@@ALJSF$2*  NAME      *2  @^@@@@LJSF$2*   NAME      2   @H@@@@      BJ
)@@G@@    DO        (P(1,1)-P(1,1)+1)*/36=0 ,P(1,1) EQU P(1,1)**0777777777777DBK
)@@G@@@^@@@@ALJSF$1*  NAME      *1  @^@@@@LJSF$1*   NAME      1   @A@@@@A(2)  BL
)@@G@@    EQU       6+3*P(0,*0)     @A@@@@A(1)      EQU       36/A(2)*P(0,0)-1BM
)@@G@@@A@@@@SPACE     EQU       27*P(0,*0)+5    @C@@@@MASK      EQU       (1*/BN
)@@G@@A(2)-1D)*/(A(1)*A(2))   @H@@@@          DO        A(1) , DO P(1,1)**MASKBO
)@@G@@=0 ,P(1,1) EQU P(1,1)*/A(2)++SPACE  @ @@@@W         FORM      36*P(0,0) BP
)@@G@@@ @@@@          W         P(1,1)    @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     BQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@.         BINARY TO 2 DIGIT DECIMAL FIELDATA AT ASSEMBLY TIME     BR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         LABEL     FDCVT$   <VALUE>@F@@@@.           BS
)@@G@@                            SETS LABEL EQU 'VALUE'    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@BT
)@@G@@P         PROC      1   @^@@@@FDCVT$*   NAME      0   @C@@@@A(0)      EQBU
)@@G@@U       P(1,1)-((P(1,1)/100)*100)   @B@@@@*         EQU       A(0)+A(0)/BV
)@@G@@10*54+06060 @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         LITERAL BW
)@@G@@COUNTER DEFINITION@[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         LIT$      <LOCATION COUNTEBX
)@@G@@R>    @F@@@@.                                       ASSUMES CURRENT COUNBY
)@@G@@TER   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@LIT$*     NAME    BZ
)@@G@@  0   @B@@@@          DO        P(1)=0 ,P(1,1) EQU &  @#@@@@$(P(1,1)) LICA
)@@G@@T     @ @@@@CTL$BNK*(0)  EQU    P(1,1)    @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@CB
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@.         EQUF$   IS USED TO GENERATE AN I$ FORMED WORD GIVECC
)@@G@@N     @F@@@@.         PARAMETERS  PASSED  TO AN OUTER PROC.  IT IS CALLECD
)@@G@@D     @^@@@@.         AS FOLLOWS:   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                 CE
)@@G@@  EQUF$     <PARAFORM>,<LOW SUB>,*<MAX NUM>     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     CF
)@@G@@    <PARAFORM>  IS  THE ROOT PARAFORM THAT CONTAINS THE     @F@@@@.     CG
)@@G@@              ADDRESS. IN A PROC CALLED P  WHOSE  FIRST     @F@@@@.     CH
)@@G@@              FIELD  CONTAINED  THE ADDRESS, <PARAFORM>     @A@@@@.     CI
)@@G@@              WOULD BE:  P(1) @F@@@@.         <LOW SUB>   IS  THE  VALUECJ
)@@G@@  OF  THE RIGHT SUBSCRIPT     @F@@@@.                   CONTAINING THE UCK
)@@G@@ FIELD  OF  THE  ADDRESS.     @F@@@@.                   IN THE <PARAFORMCL
)@@G@@> EXAMPLE, IF THE U FIELD     @F@@@@.                   STARTED IN P(1,2CM
)@@G@@), <LOW SUB> WOULD BE:  2     @F@@@@.                   IF OMITTED, <LOWCN
)@@G@@ SUB> IS ASSUMED TO BE 1.     @F@@@@.                   WARNING: THERE ICO
)@@G@@S AN ASSEMBLER BUG  WHICH     @F@@@@.                   MAY   CAUSE   THCP
)@@G@@E   LOSS   OF  RELOCATION     @E@@@@.                   INFORMATION IF TCQ
)@@G@@HIS FIELD IS OMITTED.   @F@@@@.         <MAX NUM>  IS THE MAXIMUM NUMBERCR
)@@G@@ OF SUBFIELDS (U IS     @F@@@@.                   1, X  IS  2)  WHICH  WCS
)@@G@@ILL  GET  A  FORCED     @F@@@@.                   J-DESIGNATOR  OF 14 (UCT
)@@G@@).  IF <MAX NUM> IS     @F@@@@.                   0 OR OMITTED, NO FORCECU
)@@G@@D J DESIGNATOR WILL     @F@@@@.                   BE APPLIED.  IN THE ABCV
)@@G@@OVE EXAMPLE, CODING     @F@@@@.                   <MAX NUM>  AS  2  WOULCW
)@@G@@D  CAUSE  A  FORCED     @F@@@@.                   J-DESIGNATOR  OF  14 UCX
)@@G@@NLESS THE CALLER OF     @E@@@@.                   PROC P SPECIFIED HIS OCY
)@@G@@WN J-DESIGNATOR.  @F@@@@.         <MAX NUM> MUST  BE  STARRED  IF:   1. CZ
)@@G@@ <MAX NUM> IS     @F@@@@.                   SPECIFIED AND 2.  THE ZEROTHDA
)@@G@@ SUB-FIELD OF     @C@@@@.                   THE <PARAFORM> IS DEFINED.  DB
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         NOTE THAT EQUF$ WILL WORK  CORRECTLY  EVEN  DC
)@@G@@IF  THE     @E@@@@.         OUTER PROC IS PASSED I$ FORMED ITEMS (EQUF'SDD
)@@G@@).    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@E         PROC      1,1 @^@@@@EQUF$*    NAME    DE
)@@G@@  0   @A@@@@C         EQU       E(1,2)+(E(1)<2) @F@@@@A         EQU     DF

)@@G@@.     @F@@@@.         OPT$$     GENERATES AN ECONOMICAL  REFERENCE  TO  DN

)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         BITSPAN   IS  USED  TO  PRODUCE  A SINGLE ORFC
)@@G@@ DOUBLE     @F@@@@.                   PRECISION RESULT WHICH  CONTAINS  FD
)@@G@@ONE  OR     @F@@@@.                   MORE  SPANS  OF BITS.  FOR EXAMPLEFE
)@@G@@: IF IT     @F@@@@.                   WERE DESIRED TO PRODUCE A WORD WITFF

)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                   WOULD  DO IT.  SPECIFYING ANY BIT FI

)@@G@@ECISION     @F@@@@.                   RESULT.   SINCE  THE  BIT BOUNDS WFK

)@@G@@T     @D@@@@.                   N TO THE (RIGHT) END OF THE WORD. @[@@@@FR

)@@G@@@D@@@@.                             LA,S4     A0,TABLE+3,X4 @[@@@@.     LX
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                   ADDITIONALLY, UX WILL ADD ON A NEW X OR J     LY
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                   FIELD IF THEY ARE SPECIFIED AS THE SECOND     LZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                   OR THIRD FIELDS.  IF A THIRD SUB-FIELD IS     MA
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                   GIVEN, ANY J DESIGANTOR SPECIFIED IN  THE     MB
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                   EQUF  DEFINED  TAG  WILL  BE STRIPPED OFF     MC
)@@G@@@D@@@@.                   BEFORE THE THIRD FIELD IS ADDED.  @[@@@@.     MD
)@@G@@@#@@@@UX*       FUNC    @A@@@@A         EQU       1-2*(UX(1)<0)   @^@@@@ME
)@@G@@B(0)      EQU       0   @G@@@@I         DO        18 ,B(0) EQU 2*B(0)+(AMF
)@@G@@*UX(1)>(2*B(0)+1)*/(35-I)-1)  @F@@@@          DO        UX>2 ,B(1) EQU (MG
)@@G@@UX(3)-(B(0)*/-9*A**15))*/26   @ @@@@B(0)      EQU       B(0)*A**31@C@@@@MH
)@@G@@          DO        B(0)=1 ,B(0) EQU UX(*2)     @E@@@@          END     MI
)@@G@@  UX(1)+(UX(2)*2-B(0)+UX(*2))*/17+B(1)    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@MJ
)@@G@@.         THE FOLLOWING FUNC IS USED TO GENERATE A J-REGISTER     @F@@@@MK
)@@G@@.         WORD FOR 1110 CHARACTER  ADDRESSING  OR  1110  BYTE     @F@@@@ML
)@@G@@.         INSTRUCTIONS.   (DESPITE  THE  EXCELLENT JOB UNIVAC     @F@@@@MM
)@@G@@.         HAS DONE OF COMPLICATING THE DESCRIPTION  OF  THESE     @F@@@@MN
)@@G@@.         ADDRESSING  MODES  IN THEIR MANUALS, IT IS ACTUALLY     @F@@@@MO
)@@G@@.         BOTH SIMPLE AND EFFICIENT  TO  USE.)   THE  GENERAL     @#@@@@MP
)@@G@@.         CALL IS:@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                JREG(*<BYTE LENGTH>MQ
)@@G@@,<STARTING BYTE>,*<INCREMENT>)@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         <BYTE LENGTH> MR
)@@G@@ MUST BE 6, 9, 12 OR 18.  IF OMITTED,     @F@@@@.                   9 ISMS
)@@G@@ ASSUMED.  <BYTE  LENGTH>  SHOULD  BE     @F@@@@.                   STARMT
)@@G@@RED  IF SIGN EXTENSION IS DESIRED FOR     @A@@@@.                   BYTEMU
)@@G@@ REFERENCES.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         <STARTING BYTE> IS THE STARTING MV
)@@G@@BYTE  NUMBER.   THE     @F@@@@.                   LEFTMOST  BYTE  IS  NUMW
)@@G@@MBERED  ZERO.   THE     @F@@@@.                   DEFAULT IF OMITTED IS MX
)@@G@@THE FIRST  BYTE  OF     @F@@@@.                   THE SPECIFIED  WORD.  MY
)@@G@@VALUES GREATER THAN     @D@@@@.                   ONE WORD ARE PERFECTLYMZ
)@@G@@ ACCEPTABLE.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         <INCREMENT> IS THE NUMBER OF BYTNA
)@@G@@ES TO INCREMENT FOR     @F@@@@.                   EACH CONSECUTIVE REFERNB
)@@G@@ENCE.  THIS MAY  BE     @F@@@@.                   POSITIVE,  NEGATIVE  ONC
)@@G@@R  ZERO.  THE FIELD     @F@@@@.                   SHOULD BE STARRED IF  ND
)@@G@@THE  INCREMENTATION     @F@@@@.                   BIT  IS NOT TO BE SET.NE
)@@G@@  THE DEFAULT VALUE     @D@@@@.                   (IF THE FIELD IS OMITTNF
)@@G@@ED) IS 1.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         CONTRARY  TO  BOTH  THE  1110 PRNG
)@@G@@OCESSOR AND STORAGE     @F@@@@.         MANUAL AND THE ASSEMBLER MANUAL,NH
)@@G@@  AN  INCREMENT  OF     @F@@@@.         MORE  THAN  PLUS  OR  MINUS  ONENI
)@@G@@  BYTE IS BOTH WELL     @F@@@@.         DEFINED AND A  LEGITIMATE  OPERANJ
)@@G@@TION.   (THERE  ARE     @F@@@@.         SOME   CE   EDUCATION   MANUALS NK
)@@G@@  WHICH  APPEAR  TO     @F@@@@.         ACCURATELY DESCRIBE THE BYTE OPENL
)@@G@@RATIONS.) LIKEWISE,     @F@@@@.         INHIBITING  INCREMENTATION  (VIANM
)@@G@@  A ZERO INCREMENT,     @F@@@@.         FAILURE TO SET THE INCREMENTATIONN
)@@G@@N BIT,  OR  FAILURE     @F@@@@.         TO  SET  THE  'H' BIT OF BYTE INNO
)@@G@@STRUCTIONS) ARE ALL     @F@@@@.         ACCEPTABLE.  USE OF THE SIGN EXTNP
)@@G@@ENTION BIT IS  ALSO     @ @@@@.         ALWAYS PERMISSABLE. @[@@@@.     NQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@.         A TYPICAL REFERENCE WOULD BE:   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.     NR
)@@G@@              L         J1,(JREG(9))@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         THIS  CANS
)@@G@@LL WOULD LOAD J-REGISTER ONE WITH A POINTER     @F@@@@.         FOR QUARNT
)@@G@@TER WORD BYTE OPERATIONS STARTING IN Q1  OF     @F@@@@.         THE  FIRNU
)@@G@@ST  WORD  AND INCREMENTING ONE QUARTER-WORD     @^@@@@.         PER CYCLNV
)@@G@@E.    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@J         FUNC    @^@@@@JREG*     NAME      0   NW
)@@G@@@ @@@@BYTES     EQU       36/J(1)   @D@@@@          DO        36>J(1)*BYNX
)@@G@@TES , EQU 09 . E FLAG   @G@@@@          DO        (BYTES<2)++(BYTES=5)++NY
)@@G@@(BYTES>6) , EQU 09 . E FLAG   @A@@@@          DO        J<4 ,J(3) EQU 1 NZ
)@@G@@@B@@@@BL        EQU       (BYTES**3)-(BYTES=2)  @ @@@@IW        EQU     OA
)@@G@@  J(3)/BYTES@ @@@@OW        EQU       J(2)/BYTES@C@@@@IB        EQU     OB
)@@G@@  (J(3)-IW*BYTES)*/(J(1)//6-1)@C@@@@OB        EQU       (J(2)-OW*BYTES)*OC
)@@G@@/(J(1)//6-1)@A@@@@F         FORM      1,2,1,11,3,15,3 @D@@@@          ENOD
)@@G@@D       +(F 1-J(*3),BL,J(*1),IW,IB,OW,OB) @[@@@@.     @^@@@@DEFUNCT$* PROE
)@@G@@OC      *0  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         CLEAR TEST AND SET INSTRUCTION POF
)@@G@@ROC.  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         CTS       <TS CELL ADDRESS>     @[@@@@OG
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@CTS***    PROC      1,1                 DEFINE AT LEVEL ZEROOH
)@@G@@@B@@@@          SZ,13     +(EQUF$ CTS(1),1)     @#@@@@          END     OI
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         TEST THIRD WORD AND TEST QUARTER WORD.@[@@@@OJ
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@.         TTW     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@TTW***    PROC      0,1 OK
)@@G@@                TEST THIRD WORD MODE@^@@@@          TN,4      $   @#@@@@OL
)@@G@@          END     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@.         TQW     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@OM
)@@G@@TQW***    PROC      0,1                 TEST QUARTER WORD MODE    @^@@@@ON
)@@G@@          TP,4      $   @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.     OO
)@@G@@    REZ - RESERVE AND FILL WITH A CONSTANT VALUE.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@OP
)@@G@@.         REZ       <NUMBER OF CELLS>,<VALUE TO FILL WITH>  @[@@@@.     OQ
)@@G@@@^@@@@REZ***    PROC      *1  @C@@@@          DO        REZ(1,1)<-0 , REOR
)@@G@@S REZ(1,1)  @B@@@@          DO        REZ(1,1)>0 , *REZ(1,2)@A@@@@      OS
)@@G@@    DO        REZ(1,1)<2 , END@#@@@@          UNLIST  @C@@@@          DOOT
)@@G@@        REZ(1,1)-1 , * REZ(1,2)     @#@@@@          LIST    @#@@@@      OU
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         SNZ2      IS  THE  STORE  NON-ZEOV
)@@G@@RO PROC.  THIS PROC     @F@@@@.                   WILL GUARANTEE THAT A OW
)@@G@@WORD (SOME  PARTIAL     @F@@@@.                   WORDS)  IS  NON-ZERO  OX
)@@G@@WITHOUT  KNOWING OR     @F@@@@.                   CHANGING THE CONTENTS OY
)@@G@@ OF  ANY  REGISTER.     @F@@@@.                   IT  GENERATES  TWO  INOZ
)@@G@@STRUCTIONS  EACH OF     @F@@@@.                   WHICH STORES AT LEAST PA
)@@G@@ONE  DIFFERENT  BIT     @F@@@@.                   INTO  DIFFERENT  SUB-FPB
)@@G@@IELDS  OF THE WORD.     @F@@@@.                   SNZ2 MAY ONLY BE USED PC
)@@G@@FOR  THE  FOLLOWING     @F@@@@.                   J-DESIGNATORS:   W, H1PD
)@@G@@, H2, XH1, XH2, T1,     @F@@@@.                   T2, T3 AND Q1.  NOTE TPE
)@@G@@HAT Q2, Q3, Q4  AND     @F@@@@.                   THE  SIXTHS ARE NOT ALPF
)@@G@@LOWED.  ALSO, INDEX     @E@@@@.                   INCREMENTATION MUST NOPG
)@@G@@T BE SPECIFIED.   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@SNZ2***   PROC      1,2 @^@@@@W     PH
)@@G@@    FORM      36  @E@@@@B(0)      EQU       +(I$ +(EQUF$ SNZ2(1),1,0),SNPI
)@@G@@Z2(0,1))    @F@@@@I         DO        4 ,B(1) EQU ((B(1)*2+1)*/(30-I)-1<PJ
)@@G@@B(0))+B(1)*2@ @@@@B(1)      EQU       +(W B(1)) @ @@@@          SA      PK
)@@G@@  12,B(0)   @F@@@@          SNA,B(1)/6*4+(B(1)**9)*2+7-5*(B(1)=0) 12,B(0PL
)@@G@@)-B(1)*/26  @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         DIU     PM
)@@G@@  IS  A  PROC WHICH GENERATES THE BEST POSSIBLE @F@@@@.                 PN
)@@G@@  CODE  TO  PERFORM  AN  INTEGER  DIVIDE  BY  A @F@@@@.                 PO
)@@G@@  CONSTANT.  IT KNOWS ABOUT SHIFTING FOR POWERS @F@@@@.                 PP
)@@G@@  OF TWO  AND  MULTIPLYING  BY  POWERS  OF  TWO @F@@@@.                 PQ
)@@G@@  DIVIDED BY THE CONSTANT.   NOTE THAT  IT  MAY @F@@@@.                 PR
)@@G@@  GENERATE TWO INSTRUCTIONS (E.G. -4) AND, LIKE @F@@@@.                 PS
)@@G@@  DI,   IT  MAY  DESTROY  THE  UPPER  REGISTER. @F@@@@.                 PT
)@@G@@  UNLIKE  DI,  THE  UPPER  REGISTER  WILL   NOT @F@@@@.                 PU
)@@G@@  CONTAIN  THE  REMAINDER AND MORE IMPORTANTLY, @F@@@@.                 PV
)@@G@@  THE DIVIDEND (NUMBER TO BE DIVIDED) SHOULD BE @F@@@@.                 PW
)@@G@@  A  SINGLE  PRECISION  QUANTITY  IN  THE LOWER @F@@@@.                 PX
)@@G@@  (MOST SIGNIFICANT) REGISTER.  FOR EXAMPLE:    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.     PY
)@@G@@                        LA        A0,(CHARACTER COUNT)@C@@@@.           PZ
)@@G@@                  DIU       A0,6    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.                 QA
)@@G@@  DIVIDES CHARACTER COUNT BY SIX.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                 QB
)@@G@@  THERE  ARE  MANY  CASES IN WHICH 2**36 IS     @F@@@@.                 QC
)@@G@@  NOT LARGE ENOUGH TO GUARANTEE  A  CORRECT     @F@@@@.                 QD
)@@G@@  RESULT.   IN  THESE CASES, DIU WILL USE A     @F@@@@.                 QE
)@@G@@  HIGHER POWER OF TWO (SCALED) AND A  SHIFT     @F@@@@.                 QF
)@@G@@  INSTRUCTION.   FREQUENTLY, THIS PROCEDURE     @F@@@@.                 QG
)@@G@@  (AND THE EXTRA  INSTRUCTION  REQUIRED  TO     @F@@@@.                 QH
)@@G@@  PERFORM  IT)  MAY  BE  ELIMINATED  IF THE     @F@@@@.                 QI
)@@G@@  MAXIMUM MAGNITUDE OF THE DIVIDEND (NUMBER     @F@@@@.                 QJ
)@@G@@  TO  BE DIVIDED) IS KNOWN.  IN SUCH CASES,     @F@@@@.                 QK
)@@G@@  THE MAGNITUDE OF THE LARGEST VALUE  WHICH     @F@@@@.                 QL
)@@G@@  MAY  BE PASSED SHOULD BE SPECIFIED AS THE     @F@@@@.                 QM
)@@G@@  (0,1) SUB-FIELD.  FOR EXAMPLE, TO CONVERT     @F@@@@.                 QN
)@@G@@  A  MASS STORAGE  WORD ADDRESS TO A SECTOR     @F@@@@.                 QO
)@@G@@  ADDRESS GIVEN THAT THE  MAXIMUM  POSSIBLE     @C@@@@.                 QP
)@@G@@  WORD ADDRESS IS 1*/30-1:    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.                       QQ
)@@G@@      LA        A0,(WORD ADDRESS)   @C@@@@.                             QR
)@@G@@DIU,1*/30-1 A0,28 @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.           IN  THE  FOLLOWING ALGORQS
)@@G@@ITHM DESCRIPTTION, THE NOTAION@ @@@@.           CONVENTIONS ARE:  @E@@@@QT
)@@G@@.                   Y / X     MEANS Y INTEGER DIVIDED BY X. @E@@@@.     QU
)@@G@@              Y // X    MEANS Y COVER DIVIDED BY X;   @C@@@@.           QV
)@@G@@                  Y//X = (Y+X-1)/X. @C@@@@.                   A * B     QW
)@@G@@MEANS A TIMES B.  @F@@@@.                   I */ N    MEANS I TIMES TWO QX
)@@G@@TO THE POWER N.   @F@@@@.                   MOD(Y, X) MEANS  THE  REMAINQY
)@@G@@DER OF DIVIDING Y @E@@@@.                             BY X; MOD(Y, X) = QZ
)@@G@@Y - (Y/X)*X.@E@@@@.                   ALL VARIABLES ARE NON-NEGATIVE INTRA
)@@G@@EGERS.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.           GIVEN THE  CONSTANT  X,  THE  DESIRERB
)@@G@@D COMPUTATION IS: @B@@@@.                             Z = Y / X   @[@@@@RC
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.                   LET    F(N) = 1*/N // X     @D@@@@.     RD
)@@G@@                          = (1*/N + X - 1) / X  @E@@@@.                 RE
)@@G@@              = (1*/N  +  ALPHA)  /  X    @F@@@@.                   WHERRF
)@@G@@E  ALPHA,  THE LOWEST INTEGER VALUE WHICH @F@@@@.                   SATIRG
)@@G@@SFIES THE ABOVE, IS:  X-1-MOD(1*/N-1,X).  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.           RH
)@@G@@        LET BETA(Y) = MOD(Y,X).     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.                 RI
)@@G@@  LET   MBETA = BETA(MY).     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.           THE PROBLEM RJ
)@@G@@ IS  THEN EQUIVALENT TO:  GIVEN X AND MY, @F@@@@.                   FINDRK
)@@G@@  AN  ACCEPTABLE  N  SUCH  THAT  FOR  ALL @ @@@@.                   -1<YRL
)@@G@@<MY+1:@D@@@@.                         Z=Y/X = (Y*F(N)) / 1*/N     @F@@@@RM
)@@G@@.                (Y-BETA+X-1)/X = (((1*/N+ALPHA) / X) * Y) / 1*/N @F@@@@RN
)@@G@@.                 (Y-BETA+X)*/N > ((1*/N + ALPHA) / X) * (X*Y)    @C@@@@RO
)@@G@@.                               > Y*/N + ALPHA*Y@E@@@@.                 RP
)@@G@@         1*/N > (ALPHA * Y) / (X - BETA)  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.           RQ
)@@G@@        THE EXPRESSION  ON THE RIGHT WILL BE MAXIMUM  @A@@@@.           RR
)@@G@@        EITHER FOR:     @E@@@@.                         Y = MY    OR    RS
)@@G@@Y = MY - MBETA - 1@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                   IN  THE  FIRST  RT
)@@G@@CASE,    BETA  =  MBETA.   IN @F@@@@.                   THE  SECOND  CASRU
)@@G@@E,  BETA = X-1.    THEREFORE, @F@@@@.                   (ALPHA * Y) / (XRV
)@@G@@ - BETA) WILL BE A MAXIMUM OF @E@@@@.                            (ALPHA RW
)@@G@@* MY) / (X - MBETA)     @D@@@@.                       OR    ALPHA * (MY RX
)@@G@@- MBETA - 1)@B@@@@.                   WHICHEVER IS GREATER. @[@@@@.     RY
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                   GIVEN MY AND X, THIS IS SUFFICIENT TO COMPUTE RZ
)@@G@@@A@@@@.                   N AND THUS F(N).@[@@@@.     @^@@@@DIU       PRSA
)@@G@@OC      *1  @#@@@@DIU**     NAME    @^@@@@W         FORM      36  @C@@@@SB
)@@G@@X         EQU       +(W DIU(1,2)--DIU(1,2)*/-72)@B@@@@          DO      SC
)@@G@@  X=0 , DSA DIU(1,1),36 @G@@@@          DO        X=0 , DI DIU(1,1)+12*(SD
)@@G@@DIU(1)<1),+(OPT$$ DIU(1,2))   @ @@@@          DO        X=0 , END @H@@@@SE
)@@G@@MY        EQU       +(W (DIU(0,1)--DIU(0,1)*/-72)+0377777777777*(DIU(0,1SF
)@@G@@)=0)) @ @@@@MBETA     EQU       MY-MY/X*X @A@@@@Y1        EQU       MY/(SG
)@@G@@X-MBETA)    @ @@@@Y2        EQU       MY-MBETA-1@E@@@@. DECIDE WHICH VALSH
)@@G@@UE OF (ALPHA*Y)/(X-BETA) WILL BE LARGER.  @C@@@@. THE LARGER VALUE WILL SI
)@@G@@BE: (ALPHA*NUM) / DNM.  @C@@@@NUM       EQU       (Y1<Y2)*Y2+MY*(Y1>Y2-1SJ
)@@G@@)     @C@@@@DNM       EQU       (X-MBETA-1)*(Y1>Y2-1)+1D    @^@@@@N(-1) SK
)@@G@@    EQU       0   @^@@@@F(0)      EQU       1D  @^@@@@ALPHA(0)  EQU     SL
)@@G@@  X-1 @#@@@@TOP       NAME    @D@@@@N(0)      EQU       N(0)+1.         SM
)@@G@@    TRY THE NEXT N@C@@@@F(0)      EQU       F(0)-(ALPHA(0)*2>X-1)+F(0)  SN
)@@G@@@H@@@@          DO        N(0)>0 ,ALPHA(0) EQU ALPHA(0)-X*(ALPHA(0)*2>X-SO
)@@G@@1)+ALPHA(0) @D@@@@          DO        1+ALPHA(0)*NUM>DNM*/N(0) , GO TOP SP
)@@G@@@ @@@@N(1)      EQU       N(0)+1    @#@@@@DECN      NAME    @ @@@@N(1)  SQ
)@@G@@    EQU       N(1)-1    @C@@@@          DO        N(1)<N(0) ,F(0) EQU F(SR
)@@G@@0)*/-1@B@@@@          DO        F(0)**1=0 , GO DECN   @A@@@@OPT       EQSS
)@@G@@U       F(0)>1D*/35-1   @B@@@@          DO        OPT , DSA DIU(1,1),36 ST
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DO        OPT , DI DIU(1,1),+(OPT$$ DIU(1,2))     @ @@@@SU
)@@G@@OPT0      EQU       F(0)=1    @E@@@@          DO        OPT0 , DO N(1)>0SV
)@@G@@ , SSA DIU(1,1),N(1)    @F@@@@          DO        OPT0 , DO DIU(1,2)<0 ,SW
)@@G@@ LNA DIU(1,1),DIU(1,1)  @A@@@@          DO        OPT++OPT0 , END @A@@@@SX
)@@G@@OPT1      EQU       F(0)*/(36-N(1)) @C@@@@OPT2      EQU       (OPT1<1*/1SY
)@@G@@9)**(N(1)<36)     @G@@@@          DO        OPT2 , MF DIU(1,1),+(OPT$$ OSZ
)@@G@@PT1*/-1--DIU(1,2)*/-72) @E@@@@OPT3      EQU       (OPT1-1<0377777777777)TA
)@@G@@**(N(1)<37)--OPT2 @G@@@@          DO        OPT3 , MI DIU(1,1),+(OPT$$ OTB
)@@G@@PT1--DIU(1,2)*/-72)     @A@@@@OPT4      EQU       OPT2++OPT3--1   @G@@@@TC
)@@G@@          DO        OPT4 , MI DIU(1,1),+(OPT$$ F(0)--DIU(1,2)*/-72)     TD
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DO        OPT4 , DO 36-N(1)<0 , SSA DIU(1,1),N(1)-36    TE
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DO        OPT4 , DO 36-N(1)>0 , LDSC DIU(1,1),36-N(1)   TF
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     TG
)@@G@@@D@@@@          END       .                   DEFUNCT$ END  @D@@@@/.    TH
)@@G@@    F A C I L I T I E S   I N T E R F A C E     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     TI

)@@G@@    DGET$PKT     'FILE NAME',<1ST BUFFER>,<2ND BUFFER>@G@@@@.         DGUP
)@@G@@ETP$PKT    'FILE NAME',<1ST BUFFER>,<2ND BUFFER>,'PACK ID'  @[@@@@.     UQ
)@@G@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@DGET$PKT* NAME      0   @B@@@@DGETP$UR
)@@G@@PKT*          NAME                1 @^@@@@F         FORM      30,6@B@@@@US
)@@G@@          DO        P(0,0) , F ,DGETP$    @B@@@@          DO        1--PUT
)@@G@@(0,0) , F ,DGET$  @ @@@@          LJSF$2    P(1,1)    @]@@@@          0 UU
)@@G@@@A@@@@          +         P(1,2),P(1,3)   @B@@@@          DO        P(0,UV
)@@G@@0) , LJSF$1 P(1,4)@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.         DRUW
)@@G@@EAD$PKT  'FILE NAME',<BUFFER>,<LENGTH>,<START ITEM>,<START SECTOR>@[@@@@UX
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      1,5 @#@@@@DREAD$PKT* NAME   @^@@@@F     UY
)@@G@@    FORM      30,6@ @@@@          F         ,DREAD$   @ @@@@          LJUZ
)@@G@@SF$2    P(1,1)    @A@@@@G         FORM      12,6,18,12,12,12@C@@@@      VA
)@@G@@    G         P(1,3),P(1,4),P(1,2),P(1,5) @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@VB
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@.         DBITS$PKT  'FILE NAME',<SETTING BITS>,<CONTROL BITVC
)@@G@@S>    @C@@@@.         DUNLD$PKT  'FILE NAME',<UNLOAD TIME>  @C@@@@.     VD
)@@G@@    DCYC$PKT   'FILE NAME',<MAX RANGE>    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PRVE
)@@G@@OC      1,4 @^@@@@DBITS$PKT* NAME     0   @^@@@@DUNLD$PKT* NAME     1   VF
)@@G@@@^@@@@DCYC$PKT*  NAME     2   @^@@@@F         FORM      30,6@B@@@@      VG
)@@G@@    DO        P(0,0)=0 , F ,DBITS$  @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=1 ,VH
)@@G@@ F ,DUNLD$  @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=2 , F ,DCYC$   @ @@@@      VI
)@@G@@    LJSF$2    P(1,1)    @C@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=0 , +P(1,2),P(1VJ
)@@G@@,3)   @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=1 , +P(1,2)    @B@@@@          DOVK
)@@G@@        P(0,0)=2 , F P(1,2)   @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@VL
)@@G@@.         DBACK$PKT,<# OF REELS>   'FILE NAME',<TIME&DATE>,<# FULL BLOCKVM
)@@G@@S>,;  @H@@@@.                   <LEN LAST BLOCK>,<START POS IN FILE>,<MEVN
)@@G@@DIA>,<TAPE MODE>,;@E@@@@.                   <NOISE>      <REEL #1>,<REELVO
)@@G@@ #2>,...    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                                       THVP
)@@G@@E NUMBER OF WORDS GENERATED FOR REEL@D@@@@.                             VQ
)@@G@@          NUMBERS IS:   @H@@@@.                                         VR
)@@G@@   MAX(<# OF REELS>,REEL #'S PASSED)@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC    VS
)@@G@@  *2  @#@@@@DBACK$PKT* NAME   @^@@@@F         FORM      30,6@ @@@@      VT
)@@G@@    F         ,DBACK$   @ @@@@          LJSF$2    P(1,1)    @D@@@@NR    VU
)@@G@@    EQU       (P(2)-P(0,1))*(P(2)>P(0,1))+P(0,1)@ @@@@          +       VV
)@@G@@  NR,,0     @ @@@@          +         P(1,2)    @B@@@@G         FORM    VW
)@@G@@  6,6,6,18,12,12,12     @F@@@@          G         P(1,6),P(1,7),,P(1,3),VX
)@@G@@P(1,8),P(1,5),P(1,4)    @B@@@@I         DO        NR , LJSF$1 P(2,I)    VY
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         DLAPS$PKT  'FILE NAMVZ
)@@G@@E',<LAPSE FROM>,<LAPSE TO>    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      1,5 WA
)@@G@@@#@@@@DLAPS$PKT* NAME   @^@@@@F         FORM      30,6@ @@@@          F WB
)@@G@@        ,DLAPS$   @ @@@@          LJSF$2    P(1,1)    @ @@@@          + WC
)@@G@@        P(1,2)    @ @@@@          +         P(1,3)    @#@@@@          ENWD
)@@G@@D     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         DKEY$PKT  'FILE NAME',<OLD RK>,<OLD WKWE
)@@G@@>,<NEW RK>,<NEW WK>     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      1,7 @#@@@@WF
)@@G@@DKEY$PKT* NAME    @^@@@@F         FORM      30,6@ @@@@          F       WG
)@@G@@  ,DKEY$    @ @@@@          LJSF$2    P(1,1)    @E@@@@I         DO      WH
)@@G@@  4 , +(LJSF$1 P(1,I+1))*(1-(P(1,I+1)=0)) @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@WI
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@.        DBB$PKT   'FILE NAME',<EOF>,<BLK SIZE>,<ITEM SIZE> WJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      1,5 @#@@@@DBB$PKT* NAME     @^@@@@WK
)@@G@@F         FORM      30,6@ @@@@          F         ,DBB$     @ @@@@      WL
)@@G@@    LJSF$2    P(1,1)    @A@@@@G         FORM      12,24,18,18     @B@@@@WM
)@@G@@          G         ,P(1,2),P(1,3),P(1,4) @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@WN
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.         DREG$PKT  'FILE NAME','PROJECT','ACCOUNT',<USF>,<#WO
)@@G@@ ASG'S>,;   @C@@@@.                   <CAT TIME>,<LAST REF TIME>  @[@@@@WP
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      1,10@#@@@@DREG$PKT* NAME    @^@@@@F     WQ
)@@G@@    FORM      30,6@ @@@@          F         ,DREG$    @B@@@@I         DOWR
)@@G@@        3 , LJSF$2 P(1,I)     @ @@@@G         FORM      12,6,18   @A@@@@WS
)@@G@@          G         ,P(1,4),P(1,5)  @ @@@@          +         P(1,6)    WT
)@@G@@@ @@@@          +         P(1,7)    @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     WU
)@@G@@@B@@@@.         MSALL$PKT  <BUFFER>,<LENGTH>    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P     WV
)@@G@@    PROC      1,3 @#@@@@MSALL$PKT* NAME   @^@@@@F         FORM      30,6WW
)@@G@@@ @@@@          F         ,MSALL$   @A@@@@          +         P(1,2),P(1WX
)@@G@@,1)   @]@@@@          0 @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.     WY
)@@G@@    TAPE LABEL READ / WRITE   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         LABEL$    'FILWZ
)@@G@@ENAME',<BUFFER>,<FUNCTION>,<ASCII FLAG>   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@Q         PRXA
)@@G@@OC      0,3 @^@@@@LABEL$PGEN*  NAME   0   @ @@@@W         FORM      6,6,XB
)@@G@@6,18  @B@@@@          W         P(1,4),P(1,3),,P(1,2) @ @@@@          LJXC
)@@G@@SF$2    P(1,1)    @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PRXD
)@@G@@OC      1,3 @^@@@@LABEL$PKT*  NAME    0   @^@@@@          LABEL$PGEN    XE
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@XF
)@@G@@LABEL$*   NAME      0   @^@@@@$(CTL$BNK(0)),F*  PROC 0@^@@@@          LAXG
)@@G@@BEL$PGEN    @#@@@@          END     @D@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LXH
)@@G@@A,14 12,$(CTL$BNK(0))   @ @@@@          ER        LABEL$    @ @@@@      XI
)@@G@@    DO        P(1)>0 , F@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P     XJ
)@@G@@    PROC      *1  @^@@@@LABEL$P*  NAME      0   @D@@@@          DO      XK
)@@G@@  P(1)>0 , LA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1,2)  @ @@@@          ER        LABEL$    XL
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @D@@@@/.        P R O G R A M   F I L E   I N T XM
)@@G@@E R F A C E @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         PFS$      <PACKET>  @ @@@@.     XN
)@@G@@    PFD$      <PACKET>  @ @@@@.         PFWL$     <PACKET>  @[@@@@.     XO
)@@G@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@PFS$*     NAME      1   @^@@@@PFD$* XP
)@@G@@    NAME      2   @^@@@@PFWL$*    NAME      3   @^@@@@PFS$P*    NAME    XQ
)@@G@@ *1   @^@@@@PFD$P*    NAME     *2   @^@@@@PFWL$P*   NAME      *3  @D@@@@XR
)@@G@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1,2)  @B@@@@          DOXS
)@@G@@        P(0,0)=1 , ER PFS$    @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=2 , ER PFXT
)@@G@@D$    @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=3 , ER PFWL$   @#@@@@          ENXU
)@@G@@D     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         UPDATE WRITE LOCATION     @[@@@@.     XV
)@@G@@@C@@@@.         PFUWL$    <PACKET> (SECTOR ADDRESS)   @C@@@@.         PFXW
)@@G@@I$      <PACKET> (SECTOR ADDRESS)   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         NOTE THAXX
)@@G@@T SPECIFYING THE (SECTOR ADDRESS) FOR PFI$ CHANGES    @E@@@@.         THXY
)@@G@@E   LA,U A0,<PACKET>    TO A   LNA,U A0,<PACKET>@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P     XZ
)@@G@@    PROC      *2  @^@@@@PFUWL$*   NAME      0   @^@@@@PFI$*     NAME    YA
)@@G@@  1   @^@@@@PFUWL$P*  NAME      *0  @^@@@@PFI$P*    NAME      *1  @H@@@@YB
)@@G@@          DO        (P(1)>0)**(P(0,0)=0)++(P=2) , LA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1,2YC
)@@G@@)     @E@@@@          DO        (P>2)**P(0,0) , LNA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1,2)YD
)@@G@@@D@@@@          DO        P(2)>0 , LA 13,+(EQUF$ P(2),1)    @B@@@@      YE
)@@G@@    DO        P(0,0)=0 , ER PFUWL$  @A@@@@          DO        P(0,0) , EYF
)@@G@@R PFI$@#@@@@          END     @E@@@@/.        C O M M U N I C A T I O N YG
)@@G@@S   I N T E R F A C E   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         CMS$,<NUYH
)@@G@@MBER OF LINE TABLES - 1>    <LINE TABLE ADDRESS>@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P     YI
)@@G@@    PROC      *1  @^@@@@CMS$*     NAME      0   @^@@@@CMS$P*    NAME    YJ
)@@G@@  1   @A@@@@K(1)      EQU       +(EQUF$ P(1),1) @F@@@@          DO      YK
)@@G@@  (P(0)>1)**(P(0,0)=0) ,K(0) EQU +(EQUF$ P(0),1)@E@@@@          DO      YL
)@@G@@  (P(1)>0)**(K=1)++(K(1)>1*/16-1) , ;     @D@@@@          LA        12,+YM
)@@G@@(EQUF$ P(1),1,2-2*P(0,0))     @H@@@@          DO   (P(1)>0)**(K=2)**(K(1YN
)@@G@@)<1*/16)**(K(0)<1*/16) , LA 12,(K(0),K(1))@H@@@@          DO        K=2 YO
)@@G@@, DO (K(0)>1*/16-1)++(K(1)>1*/16-1)++(P(1)=0) , ;     @B@@@@          LXYP
)@@G@@I       12,+(EQUF$ P(0),1,*1) @^@@@@          ER        CMS$@#@@@@      YQ
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         CMD$      <LINE TABLE ADDRESS>  YR
)@@G@@@B@@@@.         CMI$      <LINE TABLE ADDRESS>  @B@@@@.         CMO$    YS
)@@G@@  <LINE TABLE ADDRESS>  @B@@@@.         CMSA$     <LINE TABLE ADDRESS>  YT
)@@G@@@B@@@@.         CMH$      <LINE TABLE ADDRESS>  @B@@@@.         CMT$    YU
)@@G@@  <LINE TABLE ADDRESS>  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@YV
)@@G@@CMD$*     NAME      0   @^@@@@CMI$*     NAME      1   @^@@@@CMO$*     NAYW
)@@G@@ME      2   @^@@@@CMSA$*    NAME      3   @^@@@@CMH$*     NAME      4   YX
)@@G@@@^@@@@CMT$*     NAME      5   @^@@@@CMD$P*    NAME      *0  @^@@@@CMI$P*YY
)@@G@@    NAME      *1  @^@@@@CMO$P*    NAME      *2  @^@@@@CMSA$P*   NAME    YZ
)@@G@@  *3  @^@@@@CMH$P*    NAME      *4  @^@@@@CMT$P*    NAME      *5  @D@@@@ZA
)@@G@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1,2)  @B@@@@          DOZB
)@@G@@        P(0,0)=0 , ER CMD$    @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=1 , ER CMZC
)@@G@@I$    @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=2 , ER CMO$    @B@@@@          DOZD
)@@G@@        P(0,0)=3 , ER CMSA$   @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=4 , ER CMZE
)@@G@@H$    @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=5 , ER CMT$    @#@@@@          ENZF
)@@G@@D     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         REQUEST BUFFER POOL @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ZG
)@@G@@.         CPOOL$    <ADDR>,<LENGTH> <CHAR-COUNT>,<MODE>,<METHOD>  @[@@@@ZH
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *2  @^@@@@CPOOL$*   NAME      0   @^@@@@ZI

)@@G@@12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1,2)    @A@@@@CP        FORM      6,12,18,12,6,18 @C@@@@ZK
)@@G@@          DO        (1-P(0,0))**(P(1)>0) , ;    @F@@@@          LA,14   ZL
)@@G@@  12,(CP P(2,2),P(2,1),P(1,1),,P(2,3),P(1,2))   @ @@@@          ER      ZM
)@@G@@  CPOOL$    @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.         GET BUFFZN
)@@G@@ER    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         CGET$     <NUMBER OF BUFFERS NEEDED>  ZO
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@CGET$*    NAME      0   ZP
)@@G@@@^@@@@CGET$P*   NAME      1   @E@@@@          DO        P(0,0)**(P(1)>0)ZQ

)@@G@@          END     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         CADD$     <PACKET>  @ @@@@ZT
)@@G@@.         CJOIN$    <PACKET>  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  ZU
)@@G@@@^@@@@CADD$*    NAME      0   @^@@@@CJOIN$*   NAME      1   @^@@@@CADD$PZV

)@@G@@ ER CADD$   @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=1 , ER CJOIN$  @#@@@@      ZY
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         ADD & ACTIVATE  (FROM ESI COMPLEZZ
)@@G@@TION) @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         ADACT$    <PACKET>    (<NAME>)  @[@@@@AA
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *2  @^@@@@ADACT$*   NAME      0   @^@@@@AB
)@@G@@ADACT$P*  NAME      1   @D@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA 12,+(EQUF$AC
)@@G@@ P(1),1,2)  @D@@@@          DO        P(2)>0 , LA 13,+(EQUF$ P(2),1)    AD
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ER        ADACT$    @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     AE
)@@G@@@ @@@@.         RELEASE BUFFER POOL @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         CREL$,<AAF
)@@G@@LL> <POOL-ID>     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@CREL$*AG
)@@G@@    NAME      0   @^@@@@CREL$P*   NAME      1   @H@@@@          DO      AH
)@@G@@  (P(0,0)++(P(0,1)=0))**(P(1)>0) , LA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1)    @E@@@@      AI
)@@G@@    DO        (1-P(0,0))**(P(0,1)>0) , LXI,14 12,1    @ @@@@          ERAJ
)@@G@@        CREL$     @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         SPAK
)@@G@@ECIFY LINE ROUTING@[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         ROUTE$,<MODE> <LTT>,<POINTAL
)@@G@@ER>   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@ROUTE$*   NAME    AM
)@@G@@  0   @^@@@@ROUTE$P*  NAME      1   @D@@@@          DO        P(0,0)**(PAN
)@@G@@(1)>0) , LA 12,P(1,1)   @C@@@@          DO        P(1)>1 , LA,14 13,P(1,AO
)@@G@@2)    @F@@@@          DO        (1-P(0,0))**(P(1)>0) , LA 12,(P(0,1),P(1AP
)@@G@@,1))  @ @@@@          ER        ROUTE$    @#@@@@          END     @D@@@@AQ
)@@G@@/.        L O A D E R   I N T E R F A C E   E R ' S   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@AR
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@.         LOAD$,<CLEAR> <NAME>,<JUMP>,<RSEG-ADDR>,<RSEG-BDI>AS

)@@G@@@E@@@@          DO        (P(0,1)=0)**(P(1)>0) , LA,14 12,P(1,1)  @G@@@@AU
)@@G@@          DO        (1-(P(0,1)=0))**(P(1)>0) , LA 12,(1*/17,P(1,1))     AV
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DO        (1-(P(0,1)=0))**(P(1)=0) , LXI,14 12,*0 @C@@@@AW

)@@G@@  P(1)=3 , LA,14 14,P(1,3)    @D@@@@          DO        P(1)>3 , LA 14,(AY
)@@G@@P(1,4),P(1,3))    @ @@@@          ER        LOAD$     @#@@@@          ENAZ
)@@G@@D     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         REGISTER REENTRANT PROCESSOR LIST     BA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         RLIST$    'FILENAME','REP1','REP2',...@[@@@@BB

)@@G@@, LJSF$1 P(1,I+1) @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PRBE
)@@G@@OC      *1  @^@@@@RLIST$PKT*  NAME    0   @^@@@@          RLIST$PGEN    BF
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@BG

)@@G@@>0 , LA 12,+(OPT$$ P(1)-1,$(CTL$BNK(0)))  @ @@@@          ER        RLISBJ

)@@G@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1)    @ @@@@          ERBM
)@@G@@        RLIST$    @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         ATBN
)@@G@@TACH TO REENTRANT PROCESSOR   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         LINK$     '<REBO
)@@G@@P>'   @ @@@@.         RLINK$    '<REP>'   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PRBP
)@@G@@OC      *1  @^@@@@LINK$*    NAME      0   @^@@@@RLINK$*   NAME      1   BQ
)@@G@@@^@@@@LINK$P*   NAME      *0  @^@@@@RLINK$P*  NAME      *1  @F@@@@      BR
)@@G@@    DO        P(0,*0)**(P(1)>0) , LA 12,+(EQUF$ P(1),1)     @F@@@@      BS
)@@G@@    DO        (1-P(0,*0))**(P(1)>0) , LA 12,(LJSF$1 P(1,1)) @B@@@@      BT

)@@G@@ ER RLINK$  @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         DETACH FBV

)@@G@@ PIC Z9.    @D@@@@           05 FILLER PIC X(10) VALUE ' GO AGAIN.'.    KH
)@@G@@@#@@@@       01  T-OUT. @A@@@@           05 OUT OCCURS 10 TIMES.  @ @@@@KI

)@@G@@              07 DOING PIC 9. @#@@@@       01  TIME-C.@A@@@@           0KK
)@@G@@5 FILLER PIC X(11).     @ @@@@           05 TIME-1 PIC 9.   @^@@@@      KL
)@@G@@ 01      MAP.     @A@@@@           05 MAP-1 OCCURS 9 TIMES. @C@@@@      KM
)@@G@@         07 MAP-2  OCCURS 9 TIMES PIC 9.  @#@@@@       01  BUFF.  @^@@@@KN
)@@G@@           05 BR PIC 9. @ @@@@           05 FILLER PIC X.   @^@@@@      KO
)@@G@@     05 BC PIC 9. @ @@@@       PROCEDURE DIVISION.    @#@@@@       STARTKP
)@@G@@-IT.  @ @@@@           OPEN INPUT CRD.    @ @@@@           PERFORM STARTKQ
)@@G@@-3.   @#@@@@       START-1.   @D@@@@           IF NUM-OUT < 9 PERFORM S-KR
)@@G@@1 THRU S-1-EXIT.  @D@@@@       START-2.  READ CRD INTO BUFF AT END STOP KS
)@@G@@RUN.  @D@@@@           IF BUFF = ALL SPACES MOVE ALL '0' TO BUFF. @F@@@@KT
)@@G@@           ADD BR BC GIVING TEST ON SIZE ERROR MOVE 0 TO TEST.    @B@@@@KU
)@@G@@           IF TEST < 2 OR > 18 MOVE 0 TO X@D@@@@               PERFORM MKV
)@@G@@AP-D THRU MAP-D-EXIT 9 TIMES  @ @@@@               GO TO COMP-A.  @D@@@@KW
)@@G@@           IF MAP-2 (BR, BC) = 0 DISPLAY 'MISS' UPON  @A@@@@            KX
)@@G@@   PRINTER GO TO COMP-A.@A@@@@           MOVE MAP-2 (BR, BC) TO X.@A@@@@KY
)@@G@@           MOVE 0 TO DOING (X).     @A@@@@           MOVE 0 TO MAP-2 (BRKZ
)@@G@@, BC).@ @@@@             MOVE 20 TO TEST. @C@@@@           IF NUM-OUT > LA
)@@G@@8 AND MAP = ALL '0'     @B@@@@               NEXT SENTENCE ELSE GO TO   LB
)@@G@@@^@@@@               COMP-A.  @D@@@@           DISPLAY '**YOU WIN KID**'LC
)@@G@@ UPON PRINTER.    @#@@@@       START-3.   @ @@@@           MOVE 0 TO NUMLD
)@@G@@-OUT. @A@@@@           MOVE ALL '0' TO T-OUT.   @A@@@@           MOVE ALLE
)@@G@@L '0' TO MAP.     @D@@@@           DISPLAY '*READY YOU FOOL*' UPON PRINTLF
)@@G@@ER.   @#@@@@       START-X.   @ @@@@           GO TO START-1.     @#@@@@LG
)@@G@@       COMP-A.    @B@@@@           IF TEST = 20 MOVE 0 TO TEST    @ @@@@LH
)@@G@@               MOVE X TO D2-A @B@@@@               DISPLAY D2 UPON PRINTLI
)@@G@@ER    @ @@@@               GO TO START-2. @B@@@@           ACCEPT TIME-CLJ
)@@G@@ FROM DATE-TIME.  @B@@@@           IF TIME-1 = 0 MOVE 5 TO TIME-1.@D@@@@LK
)@@G@@            IF TIME-1 = 5 AND TEST NOT = 0 DISPLAY    @D@@@@            LL
)@@G@@   ' FREE MOVE FOR THE FOOL ' UPON PRINTER@ @@@@                GO TO STLM
)@@G@@ART-2.@D@@@@           IF NUM-OUT = 0 PERFORM S-1 THRU S-1-EXIT.  @ @@@@LN
)@@G@@           MOVE ZERO TO X.    @ @@@@            MOVE TIME-1 TO XX.@C@@@@LO
)@@G@@           PERFORM COMP-MOVE THRU COMP-MOVE-EXIT@ @@@@               NUMLP
)@@G@@-OUT TIMES. @C@@@@           IF MAP-1 (1) = ALL '0' GO TO START-1.@D@@@@LQ
)@@G@@           DISPLAY '*** BARFF!!! ***' UPON PRINTER.   @^@@@@           MLR
)@@G@@OVE 0 TO X. @D@@@@           PERFORM MAP-D THRU MAP-D-EXIT 9 TIMES.     LS
)@@G@@@ @@@@           GO TO START-3.     @]@@@@       S-1 .@B@@@@           ALT
)@@G@@CCEPT TIME-C FROM DATE-TIME.  @B@@@@           IF TIME-1 = 0 MOVE 3 TO TLU
)@@G@@IME-1.@ @@@@            MOVE TIME-1 TO XX.@B@@@@           IF XX > 7 ANDLV
)@@G@@ MAP = ALL '0'    @A@@@@               MOVE 5 TO TIME-1.    @D@@@@      LW
)@@G@@     PERFORM S-1-A THRU S-1-C-EXIT TIME-1 TIMES.@#@@@@       S-1-EXIT.  LX
)@@G@@@#@@@@           EXIT.  @#@@@@       S-1-A.     @ @@@@           MOVE 0 LY
)@@G@@TO TEST X.  @ @@@@           MOVE 1 TO TEST.    @#@@@@       S-1-B.     LZ
)@@G@@@ @@@@           ADD TIME-1 TO XX.  @ @@@@               MOVE XX TO X.  MA
)@@G@@@ @@@@               MOVE X TO XX.  @C@@@@               IF XX = 0 OR > MB
)@@G@@9 ADD 1 TO XX     @ @@@@                 GO TO S-1-B. @C@@@@           IMC
)@@G@@F MAP-2 (9, XX) = 0 GO TO S-1-C.    @ @@@@           ADD 1 TO TEST.     MD
)@@G@@@B@@@@           IF TEST > 12 GO TO S-1-C-EXIT. @^@@@@           GO TO SME
)@@G@@-1-B. @#@@@@       S-1-C.     @B@@@@           IF NUM-OUT > 8 GO TO S-1-MF

)@@G@@OG INTERFACE PACKAGE    @[@@@ .     @F@@@ .                             NB
)@@G@@          JOHN WALKER   AUGUST 1973 @[@@@  .    @A@@@  .    MODIFIED TO NC
)@@G@@HANDLE LOG STACK  @B@@@  .    TAPES WRITTEN WITH FURPUR'S @COPY,GM@B@@@ ND
)@@G@@ .    COMMAND, AND TO SKIP PAST FIRST 224 @C@@@  .    WORDS OF EACH CYCLNE
)@@G@@E ON LEVEL 36 TAPES.    @F@@@  .   ........ ........................  DANF
)@@G@@VID FENG   JANUARY, 1981@[@@@  .    @F@@@  .    MODIFIED TO HANDLE MULTING
)@@G@@-REEL TAPES OF COPY,G OR FANG FOMAT @G@@@  .   .........................NH
)@@G@@........  DAVID FENG    FEBRUARY, 1981    @[@@@ .     @F@B@A.   CONVERTENI
)@@G@@D TO MASM AND CHANGED THE USE NAME TO BE ATTACHED     @F@@@B.      CONVENJ
)@@G@@RTED TO MASM AND CHANGED THE USE NAME TO BE ATTACHED  @ @B@A.   FORM LOGNK
)@@G@@.. TO $LOG$$.     @ @@@B.      FORM LOG TO $LOG$$.    @E@B@A.           NL
)@@G@@                    AVANT ELLIOTT  MAY, 1981    @F@@@B.                 NM
)@@G@@                       AVANT ELLIOTT  MAY, 1981 @[@@@A.     @#@@@       NN
)@@G@@    AXR$    @#@A@           DEFUNCT$@A@@@A          INCLUDE 'ERPROCS/MASNO
)@@G@@M'    @^@@@           LIT$      2   @[@@@ .     @G@@@ .         THE TAG NP
)@@G@@'LEVEL27' CAUSES LGITEM TO ACCEPT LOG ENTRIES WITH    @F@@@ .         A NQ
)@@G@@ZERO RUNID, CHANGING THEM TO EXEC 8 LOG ITEMS.  THESE @D@@@ .         LONR
)@@G@@G ITEMS WERE CREATED BY LEVEL 27 SYSTEMS. @[@@@ .     @F@@@ LEVEL27   EQNS
)@@G@@U       0                   NO ZERO RUNIDS, PLEASE    @[@@@ .     @G@@@ NT
)@@G@@.         THE TAG 'BECHTEL' PERMITS DOLLAR SIGNS IN RUNIDS.  THESE ARE  NU
)@@G@@@F@@@ .         PERMITTED BY A LOCAL CHANGE MADE AT BECHTEL CORPORATION.NV
)@@G@@@[@@@ .     @F@@@ BECHTEL   EQU       0                   TURN OFF DOLLANW
)@@G@@R SIGNS     @[@@@ .     @[@@@ $(1). @[@@@ .     @B@@@ .         COMMON FNX
)@@G@@IELDS IN LOG ENTRIES    @[@@@ .     @D@@@ LITYP     EQUF      0,,S1     NY
)@@G@@          LOG ENTRY TYPE@F@@@ LILEN     EQUF      0,,S2               LENZ
)@@G@@NGTH OF DATA IN ITEM    @F@@@ LITDW     EQUF      25                  TIOA
)@@G@@ME AND DATE OF ENTRY    @F@@@ LIRUNID   EQUF      27                  RUOB
)@@G@@NID ENTRY BELONGS TO    @[@@@ .     @[@@@ .     @A@@@ .         CALL LGIOC
)@@G@@TEM(BUF,$EOF)     @[@@@ .     @G@@@ .         TRANSFERS THE NEXT LOG ENTOD
)@@G@@RY INTO THE BUFFER.  IF THERE ARE NO@E@@@ .         MORE LOG ENTRIES, COOE
)@@G@@NTROL PASSES TO THE EOF LABEL.@[@@@ .     @F@@@ LGITEM*   LA,U      A0,*OF
)@@G@@0,X11           GET USER BUFFER ADDRESS   @F@@@           SA,H2     A0,UOG
)@@G@@BLOC            STORE INTO BUFFER POINTER @F@@@           LA,U      A2,3OH
)@@G@@,X11            LOAD NORMAL RETURN POINT  @E@@@           SA,H2     A2,LOI
)@@G@@GITRT           STORE RETURN POINT  @[@@@ LGTRYA@F@@@           TNZ     OJ
)@@G@@  COPGST              IS IT COPY,G STACK TAPE?  @B@@@           J       OK
)@@G@@  LGTR2               NO@C@@@           LA,U      A0,0                 YOL
)@@G@@ES    @]@@@           . @G@@@           . NOTE: A 'GROUP' FOR COPY,G STAOM
)@@G@@CK TAPE, REFERS TO 1/8 OF A   @D@@@           .       COPY,G TAPE BLOCK,ON
)@@G@@ OR 224 WORDS.    @]@@@           . @E@@@           TLE       A0,GPCNT  OO
)@@G@@          NO MORE GROUPS?     @E@@@           J         LGMOVE          OP
)@@G@@    NO, GO MOVE LOG ITEM@F@@@           J         LGTR3               YEOQ
)@@G@@S, READ ANOTHER BLOCK   @[@@@ LGTR2 @G@@@          TZ        GPENT      OR
)@@G@@        ANY ITEMS LEFT IN THIS BLOCK ?    @H@@@           J         LGMOOS
)@@G@@VE              YES.  GO MOVE IT TO USER'S BUFFER     @E@@@ LGTR3     TZOT
)@@G@@        FIRST               FIRST TIME THROUGH ?@F@@@           J       OU
)@@G@@  FICONT              YES.  SET UP CONTINGENCY  @E@@@           IOW$    OV
)@@G@@  IOPKT               FIRE UP I/O ON FILE @F@@@           TNZ       UAFTOW
)@@G@@AP              READING BECHTEL UAF TAPE ?@G@@@           J         NLGUOX
)@@G@@AF              NO.  PROCESS AS LOG ENTRIES     @F@@@           LA,S1   OY
)@@G@@  A0,IOPKT+3          LOAD I/O STATUS FROM READ @F@@@           JZ      OZ
)@@G@@  A0,LGUAFOK          SKIP IF NORMAL COMPLETION @E@@@           TE,U    PA
)@@G@@  A0,1                NORMAL END OF FILE ?@F@@@           J         BADSPB
)@@G@@TR              NO.  BAD STATUS ON READ   @F@@@           TZ        UAFEPC
)@@G@@OF              SECOND EOF ON UAF TAPE ?  @F@@@           J         BADSPD
)@@G@@TR              YES.  TREAT AS END OF FILE@F@@@           SA        A0,UPE
)@@G@@AFEOF           SET FIRST EOF ENCOUNTERED @E@@@           J         LGTRPF
)@@G@@YA              GO READ NEXT BLOCK  @[@@@ .     @F@@@ LGUAFOK   LA,H2   PG
)@@G@@  A0,IOPKT+3          LOAD WORDS TRANSFERRED    @F@@@           DSL     PH
)@@G@@  A0,36               RIGHT JUSTIFY IN A0,(A1   @F@@@           DI,U    PI
)@@G@@  A0,28               COMPUTE SECTORS IN BLOCK  @F@@@           SA      PJ
)@@G@@  A0,GPENT           SET LOG SECTORS RETURNED   @E@@@           LA,U    PK
)@@G@@  A1,BUFFER           LOAD BUFFER ADDRESS @F@@@           SA,H2     A1,IPL
)@@G@@TMPTR           SET CURRENT BLOCK POINTER @F@@@           J         LGUAPM
)@@G@@F1              SET UP TO PROCESS UAF DATA@[@@@ .     @[@@@ NLGUAF@E@@@ PN
)@@G@@          TZ,S1     IOPKT+3              IS I/O STATUS O.K.?@F@@@       PO
)@@G@@    J         BADSTR               NO, HARDWARE EOF OR ERROR@E@@@       PP
)@@G@@   TNZ        FIRSTF                YES, FIRST FILE?  @C@@@          J  PQ
)@@G@@        NFRS                 NO     @E@@@          SZ         FIRSTF    PR
)@@G@@           YES, CLEAR FLAG    @F@@@          LA         A0,BUFFER       PS
)@@G@@     IS FIRST WORD COPYG?     @A@@@          TE         A0,('COPYG ')   PT
)@@G@@@C@@@          J          NCOPG                NO     @D@@@          LA,PU
)@@G@@U       A0,1                 LOAD A ONE   @H@@@          SA         A0,CPV
)@@G@@OPGST            FLAG PROCESSING A COPY,GM STACK TAPE @E@@@          LA PW
)@@G@@        A0,(1794,BUFF0)      USE A LARGER BUFFER@D@@@          SA       PX
)@@G@@  A0,IOPKT+4           FOR TAPE I/O @[@@@ NFRS  @F@@@          TNZ      PY
)@@G@@  COPGST               IS IT COPY,GM STACK TAPE?@C@@@          J        PZ
)@@G@@  NCOPG                NO     @G@@@          TNZ        NUFIL           QA
)@@G@@     YES, IS IT A NEW FILE CYCLE?   @C@@@          J          NCOPG     QB
)@@G@@           NO     @E@@@          SZ         NUFIL                YES, CLQC
)@@G@@EAR FLAG    @E@@@          J          GOBACK               SKIP LABEL BLQD
)@@G@@OCK   @[@@@ NCOPG @E@@@          SZ         NUFIL                CLEAR NQE
)@@G@@EW FILE FLAG@F@@@           LA,H2     A0,IOPKT+3          LOAD WORDS TRAQF
)@@G@@NSFERRED    @F@@@           LA,U      A3,BUFFER           SET UP FOR BLOQG
)@@G@@CK POINTER  @F@@@           TNZ       FSTBLK              IS IT FIRST DAQH
)@@G@@TA BLOCK?   @B@@@           J         NFST                NO@E@@@       QI
)@@G@@    SZ        FSTBLK              YES, CLEAR FLAG     @ @@@           LAQJ
)@@G@@        A2,BUFFER @G@@@           TE        A2,('SYSLOG')       DOES FILQK
)@@G@@E HAVE CONTROL BLOCK?   @B@@@           J         NFST                NOQL
)@@G@@@G@@@            TNZ       COPGST              YES, IS IT A COPY,G STACKQM
)@@G@@ TAPE?@E@@@            J         LGUAF2              NO, READ NEXT BLOCKQN
)@@G@@@G@@@           ANA,U     A0,224              YES, MOVE PAST THESE 224 WQO
)@@G@@ORDS  @ @@@           AA,U      A3,224    @[@@@ NFST  @H@@@           DSQP
)@@G@@L       A0,36               RIGHT JUSTIFY WORD COUNT IN A0,A1     @F@@@ QQ
)@@G@@          DI,U      A0,224              COMPUTE GROUPS IN BLOCK   @E@@@ QR
)@@G@@          JZ        A0,BADSTR           IF GROUP COUNT <= 0 @F@@@       QS
)@@G@@    JN        A0,BADSTR           THEN TAKE ERROR BRANCH    @C@@@       QT
)@@G@@    SA        A0,GPCNT            STORE IT@G@@@ NF2       LA,S6     A1,,QU
)@@G@@A3              GET IEM COUNT FOR THIS GROUP    @G@@@           JNZ     QV
)@@G@@  A1,NF4              ARE THERE ITEMS IN THIS GROUP?  @F@@@           ANQW
)@@G@@A,U     A0,1                NO, DECREMENT GROUP COUNT @E@@@           JZQX
)@@G@@        A0,GOBACK           NO MORE GROUPS?     @G@@@           AA,U    QY
)@@G@@  A3,224              NO, INCREMENT GROUP POINTER     @E@@@           J QZ
)@@G@@        NF2                 LOOK AT NEXT GROUP  @E@@@ NF4       SA,H2   RA
)@@G@@  A3,ITMPTR            STORE ITEM POINTER @E@@@           AA,U      A3,2RB
)@@G@@24              MOVE UP ITEM POINTER@G@@@           SA        A3,NXTGP  RC
)@@G@@          SAVE IT AS NEXT GROUP POINTER   @G@@@           SA        A0,GRD
)@@G@@PCNT            STORE GROUP COUNT FOR BLOCK     @F@@@           SA      RE
)@@G@@  A1,GPENT            STORE ITEM COUNT FOR GROUP@]@@@           . @G@@@ RF
)@@G@@          TNZ       FILESET             NOT EOF , IS IT USER FILE SET?  RG
)@@G@@@B@@@           J         LGUAF1              NO@G@@@           LA,U    RH
)@@G@@  A0,8                YES, FORCE GROUP TO BE FULL     @F@@@           SARI
)@@G@@        A0,GPENT           SET ITEMS LEFT IN BLOCK    @E@@@ LGUAF1    LARJ
)@@G@@        A0,BLKCNT           LOAD BLOCK COUNT    @F@@@           AA,U    RK
)@@G@@  A0,1                INCREMENT BLOCK COUNT     @F@@@           SA      RL
)@@G@@  A0,BLKCNT           STORE UPDATED BLOCK COUNT @H@@@ LGUAF2    LA      RM
)@@G@@  A0,IOPKT+5          LOAD CURRENT MASS STG. FILE ADDR.     @F@@@       RN
)@@G@@    AA,U      A0,224/28           INCREMENT SECTOR ADDR.    @G@@@       RO
)@@G@@    SA        A0,IOPKT+5          PUT NEXT READ ADDR. IN PACKET   @D@@@ RP
)@@G@@GOBACK    J         LGTRYA              GET NEXT BLOCK@[@@@ .     @A@@@ RQ
)@@G@@.         MOVE DATA TO USER BUFFER  @[@@@ .     @F@@@ LGMOVE    LA      RR
)@@G@@  A0,UBLOC            GET POINTER TO USER BUFFER@F@@@           LA      RS
)@@G@@  A3,ITMPTR           GET POINTER TO NEXT ITEM  @G@@@           LA      RT
)@@G@@  A2,,A3              LOAD FIRST WORD OF LOG ITEM     @G@@@           TNRU
)@@G@@E       A2,(-0)             IS IT END OF FILE SENTINEL ?    @H@@@       RV
)@@G@@    J         BADSTR              YES.  GO PROCESS NEXT CYCLE, IF ANY   RW
)@@G@@@E@@@ LGMNFS    LR,U      R1,28               LOAD LENGTH TO MOVE @G@@@ RX
)@@G@@          BT        A0,,*A3             MOVE NEXT ITEM TO USER BUFFER   RY
)@@G@@@F@@@           SA,H2     A3,ITMPTR           UPDATE NEXT ITEM POINTER  RZ
)@@G@@@E@@@           LA        A0,GPENT           LOAD ENTRIES LEFT    @D@@@ SA
)@@G@@          ANA,U     A0,1                DECREMENT IT  @F@@@           SASB
)@@G@@        A0,GPENT           UPDATE ITEM AVAILABLE COUNT@F@@@           TNSC
)@@G@@Z       COPGST             IS IT COPY,G STACK TAPE?   @B@@@           J SD
)@@G@@        LGM6                NO@F@@@           TZ        GPENT           SE
)@@G@@   NO MORE ITEMS IN GROUP?    @B@@@           J         LGM6            SF
)@@G@@   NO @F@@@           LA        A3,NXTGP           YES, POINT TO NEXT GRSG
)@@G@@OUP   @ @@@           LA        A0,GPCNT  @E@@@ LGM2      ANA,U     A0,1SH
)@@G@@               DECREMENT GROUP COUNT@F@@@           JZ        A0,LGM5   SI
)@@G@@         0 MORE GROUPS IN BLOCK?    @G@@@           LA,S6     A1,,A3    SJ
)@@G@@         GET ITEM COUNT IN NEXT GROUP     @G@@@           JNZ       A1,LSK
)@@G@@GM4            ARE THERE ITEMS IN THIS GROUP?   @F@@@           AA,U    SL
)@@G@@  A3,224             NO, POINT TO NEXT GROUP    @C@@@           J       SM
)@@G@@  LGM2               TRY AGAIN@E@@@ LGM4      SA,H2     A3,ITMPTR       SN
)@@G@@    STORE ITEM POINTER  @E@@@           AA,U      A3,224             POISO
)@@G@@NT TO NEXT GROUP  @E@@@           SA        A3,NXTGP           FOR NEXT SP
)@@G@@TIME AROUND @F@@@           SA        A1,GPENT           STORE ITEM COUNSQ
)@@G@@T FOR GROUP @E@@@ LGM5      SA        A0,GPCNT           STORE GROUP COUSR
)@@G@@NT    @[@@@ LGM6  @F@@@           LA,U      A0,1                GET A ONSS
)@@G@@E TO BUMP COUNTS  @G@@@           AU        A0,RECFIL           INCREMENST
)@@G@@T RECORDS IN THIS FILE  @D@@@           SA        A1,RECFIL           STSU
)@@G@@ORE IT OUT  @G@@@           AU        A0,RECTOT           INCREMENT TOTASV
)@@G@@L RECORDS PASSED  @E@@@           SA        A1,RECTOT           UPDATE TSW
)@@G@@HE COUNT    @[@@@ .     @H@@@ .         VALIDATE LOG ITEM FOR OBVIOUS ERSX
)@@G@@RORS BEFORE PASSING BACK TO USER    @[@@@ .     @E@@@           LA,H2   SY
)@@G@@  A0,UBLOC            GET ADDRESS OF ITEM @G@@@           TNZ       UAFTSZ
)@@G@@AP              PROCESSING A BECHTEL UAF TAPE ? @F@@@           J       TA
)@@G@@  NLUAF2              NO.  SKIP SPECIAL EOF TEST@F@@@           LA      TB
)@@G@@  A1,LITYP,A0         LOAD TYPE OF LOG ITEM     @G@@@           TE,U    TC
)@@G@@  A1,077              BECHTEL UAF TAPE EOF SENTINEL ? @G@@@           J TD
)@@G@@        NLUAF2              NO.  THIS IS A VALID LOG ITEM   @E@@@       TE
)@@G@@    SZ        GPENT              MARK THIS BLOCK EMPTY@G@@@           J TF
)@@G@@        LGTRYA              GO READ NEXT BLOCK (EOF MARK)   @]@@@ NLUAF2TG
)@@G@@    . @F@@@           LA        A1,LILEN,A0         LOAD LENGTH OF LOG ETH
)@@G@@NTRY  @D@@@           TG,U      A1,25               IN RANGE ?    @E@@@ TI
)@@G@@          J         LGERRL              NO.  DUMP BAD ITEM  @G@@@       TJ
)@@G@@    LA,H1     A1,LITDW,A0         LOAD DATE PART OF TDATE$ WORD   @I@@@ TK
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A1,010000           CHECK FOR SPECIAL BAD DATE ON EXTL
)@@G@@EC BOOT     @G@@@           J         LGTDF               SPECIAL FUDGE.TM
)@@G@@  CHECK RUNID     @H@@@           LA,S1     A1,LITDW,A0         LOAD MONTN
)@@G@@THS FIELD FROM TDATE$ WORD    @E@@@           TZ        A1              TO
)@@G@@    IT CANNOT BE ZERO   @G@@@           TG,U      A1,13               NOTP
)@@G@@R CAN IT BE MORE THAN DECEMBER@G@@@           J         LGERRT          TQ
)@@G@@    OTHERWISE IT'S A DATE/TIME ERROR@E@@@           LA,S2     A1,LITDW,ATR
)@@G@@0         LOAD DAYS FIELD     @G@@@           TZ        A1              TS
)@@G@@    PROTECT AGAINST MAY 0, 1964     @G@@@           TG,U      A1,32     TT
)@@G@@          ...AS WELL AS OCTOBER 32, 1984  @E@@@           J         LGERTU
)@@G@@RT              DUMP ENTRY IF BAD   @G@@@           LA,H2     A1,LITDW,ATV
)@@G@@0         LOAD SECONDS AFTER MIDNIGHT     @G@@@           TG,U      A1,6TW
)@@G@@0*60*24+1       MAKE SURE IT'S NOT TOO LARGE    @E@@@           J       TX
)@@G@@  LGERRT              IF SO, REJECT IT    @D@@@ LGTDF     LA        A2,LTY
)@@G@@IRUNID,A0       LOAD THE RUNID@ @@@           ON        LEVEL27   @I@@@ TZ
)@@G@@          TNZ       A2                  FUNNY EXEC RUNID             ***UA
)@@G@@********    @I@@@           LA        A2,('EXEC 8')       YES.  CHANGE IUB
)@@G@@T              ***********    @D@@@           SA        A2,LIRUNID,A0   UC
)@@G@@    PUT IT BACK   @ @@@           OFF       LEVEL27   @F@@@           TNUD
)@@G@@E       A2,('EXEC 8')       PERMIT EXEC-8 LOG ENTRIES @F@@@           J UE
)@@G@@        LGROK               EVEN THOUGH THEY'RE FUNNY @C@@@ CKRND     LAUF
)@@G@@,U      A1,0                CLEAR A1@F@@@           JZ        A2,LGROK  UG
)@@G@@          STOP IF RUNID ALL GONE    @F@@@           LDSL      A1,6      UH
)@@G@@          SHIFT A CHARACTER INTO A1 @E@@@           TNE,U     A1,' '    UI
)@@G@@          IS IT A BLANK ?     @G@@@           J         CKRSP           UJ
)@@G@@    YES.  MAKE SURE REST IS BLANK   @ @@@           ON        BECHTEL   UK
)@@G@@@F@@@           TNE,U     A1,'$'              IS IT A DOLLAR SIGN ?     UL
)@@G@@@I@@@           J         CKRND               YES.  '$' IS LEGAL IN RUNIUM
)@@G@@DS AT BECHTEL     @ @@@           OFF       BECHTEL   @E@@@           TGUN
)@@G@@,U      A1,'0'              IT IT NUMERIC ?     @F@@@           TG,U    UO
)@@G@@  A1,'9'+1            ...REST OF NUMERIC TEST   @G@@@           J       UP
)@@G@@  CKRALF              NO.  SEE IF IT'S ALPHABETIC     @F@@@           J UQ
)@@G@@        CKRND               YES.  CHECK NEXT CHARACTER@E@@@ CKRALF    TGUR
)@@G@@,U      A1,'A'              IS IT ALPHABETIC ?  @E@@@           TG,U    US
)@@G@@  A1,'Z'+1            ...WELL, IT IT ?    @F@@@           J         LGERUT
)@@G@@RR              NO.  RUNID IS IN ERROR    @F@@@           J         CKRNUU
)@@G@@D               YES.  CHECK NEXT CHARACTER@F@@@ CKRSP     JZ        A2,LUV
)@@G@@GROK            STOP IF NO MORE RUNID LEFT@C@@@           LA,U      A1,0UW
)@@G@@                CLEAR A1@F@@@           LDSL      A1,6                MOUX
)@@G@@VE NEXT CHARACTER TO A1 @E@@@           TE,U      A1,' '              ISUY
)@@G@@ IT ALSO A SPACE  @E@@@           J         LGERRR              NO.  MALUZ
)@@G@@FORMED RUNID@F@@@           J         CKRSP               YES.  KEEP ON VA
)@@G@@LOOKING     @]@@@ LGROK     . @F@@@ LGITRT    J         $-$             VB
)@@G@@    RETURN TO USER PROGRAM    @[@@@ .     @D@@@ .         SWAP TO NEXT CVC
)@@G@@YCLE UPON END OF CURRENT FILE @[@@@ .     @F@@@ BADSTR    F$SKIP    5   VD
)@@G@@                INDENT BEFORE MESSAGE     @E@@@           F$DECV    BLKCVE
)@@G@@NT              EDIT BLOCK COUNT    @E@@@           F$MSG     BLP       VF
)@@G@@          COPY END MESSAGE    @F@@@           F$DECV    RECFIL          VG
)@@G@@    EDIT LOG ITEMS IN THE FILE@G@@@           F$MSGR    .               VH
)@@G@@    COPY TO END OF NORMAL MESSAGE   @F@@@           TNZ       REJFIL    VI
)@@G@@          ANY REJECTS IN THIS FILE ?@E@@@           J         NORJF     VJ
)@@G@@          NO.  SKIP MESSAGE   @E@@@           F$CHAR    ','             VK
)@@G@@    YES.  EDIT A COMMA  @E@@@           F$SKIP    1                   SKVL
)@@G@@IP BEFORE NUMBER  @F@@@           F$DECV    REJFIL              EDIT REJVM
)@@G@@ECTS IN THIS FILE @D@@@           F$FD4     (' REJECTS')        EDIT 'REVN
)@@G@@JECTS'@E@@@ NORJF     F$MSGR    .                   COPY REST OF MESSAGEVO
)@@G@@@E@@@           LA,S1     A0,IOPKT+3          LOAD I/O STATUS     @H@@@ VP
)@@G@@          TZ        A0                  NORMAL COMPLETION (AND SENTINEL)VQ
)@@G@@ ?    @F@@@           TNE,U     A0,022              READ OFF END OF FILEVR
)@@G@@ ?    @E@@@           J         BADSTP              RIGHT.  THAT'S OK   VS
)@@G@@@F@@@           TE,U      A0,5                END OF MASS STORAGE FILE ?VT
)@@G@@@G@@@           TNE,U     A0,1                ...OR END OF FILE ON TAPE VU
)@@G@@?     @G@@@           J         BADSTP              YES.  SKIP BAD STATUVV
)@@G@@S MESSAGE   @F@@@           F$MSGR    .                   COPY FIRST PARVW
)@@G@@T OF MESSAGE@D@@@           F$OCTV    IOPKT+3,,S1         EDIT STATUS   VX
)@@G@@@E@@@           F$MSGR    .                   COPY REST OF MESSAGE@H@@@ VY
)@@G@@          SLJ       BOOBOO              FLAG POSSIBLE ACCOUNTING DATA LOVZ
)@@G@@SS    @F@@@           J         BADSPP              ALWAYS PRINT IF IN EWA
)@@G@@RROR  @[@@@ .     @G@@@ BADSTP    TNZ       REJFIL              ANY REJEWB
)@@G@@CTS IN THIS CYCLE ?     @H@@@           TNZ       SHORTFORM           NOWC
)@@G@@.  SUPPRESS CYCLE LOG MESSAGES ?    @F@@@           J         BADSPP    WD
)@@G@@          NO.  PRINT SUMMARY MESSAGE@F@@@           F$DT      .         WE
)@@G@@          CLEAR AND ERASE THE LINE  @F@@@           J         BADSPI    WF
)@@G@@          IGNORE THE LOG MESSAGE    @[@@@ .     @G@@@ BADSPP    F$PRT   WG
)@@G@@  1                   PRINT THE CYCLE SUMMARY LINE    @F@@@ BADSPI    TNWH
)@@G@@Z       STKTAP              PROCESSING A STACK TAPE ? @H@@@           TZWI
)@@G@@        RCVTAP              NO.  PROCESSING A RECOVERY TAPE ?     @H@@@ WJ
)@@G@@          J         NOFRLG              YES.  DON'T FREE IT IF FILES REMWK
)@@G@@AIN   @H@@@           LA,U      A0,FRELOG           LOAD IMAGE TO FREE SWL
)@@G@@TANDARD LOG FILE  @H@@@           TZ        ONEFILE             PROCESSIWM
)@@G@@NG USER-ASSIGNED LOG FILE ?   @G@@@           LA,U      A0,FREINT       WN
)@@G@@    YES.  JUST RELEASE INTERNAL NAME@F@@@           CSF$      .         WO
)@@G@@          FREE THE FILE OR NAME     @F@@@ NOFRLG    SZ        BLKCNT    WP
)@@G@@          CLEAR BLOCK COUNT ON TAPE @F@@@           SZ        RECFIL    WQ
)@@G@@          CLEAR ITEMS IN THIS FILE  @F@@@           SZ        REJFIL    WR
)@@G@@          CLEAR REJECTS IN THIS FILE@G@@@           SZ        GPENT     WS
)@@G@@         CLEAR ITEMS CURRENTLY IN BUFFER  @H@@@           SZ        GPCNWT
)@@G@@T              CLEAR GROUP COUNT FOR COPY,G STACK TAPE@G@@@           SZWU
)@@G@@        IOPKT+5             SET FILE ADDRESS BACK TO START  @^@@@       WV
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,1@E@@@  .        SA        A0,NUFIL            FLAG NEWWW
)@@G@@ FILE CYCLE @F@@@           SA        A0,FSTBLK           FLAG FIRST DATWX
)@@G@@A BLOCK     @E@@@           TZ        ONEFILE             SINGLE FILE MOWY
)@@G@@DE ?  @G@@@           J         FCEND               YES.  DON'T GET A NEWZ
)@@G@@W CYCLE     @F@@@           TNZ       STKTAP              PROCESSING A SXA
)@@G@@TACK TAPE ? @G@@@           J         RTNEXT              NO.  READY TO XB
)@@G@@PROCESS NEXT FILE @F@@@           TNZ,S1    IOPKT+3             TERMINATXC
)@@G@@ED BY END-OF-FILE?@G@@@           J         STKSKG              NO, MUSTXD
)@@G@@ BE BY (-0) SENTINEL    @[@@@  .    @G@@@  .        CHECK FOR END OF TAPXE
)@@G@@E OR END OF REEL FOR MULTI-REEL TAPE.     @[@@@  .    @G@@@           TZXF
)@@G@@        NUFIL               IS NEW FILE CYCLE EXPECTED?     @H@@@       XG
)@@G@@    J         FCEND               YES, MUST BE END OF TAPE (DOUBLE EOF) XH
)@@G@@@E@@@D          IOW$      IOPKT               NO, READ A BLOCK    @ @@@DXI
)@@G@@          L,S1      A0,IOPKT+3@^@@@D          TE,U      A0,1@ @@@D      XJ
)@@G@@    J         EORTEST   @ @@@C          L,S3      A0,IOPKT+3@^@@@C      XK
)@@G@@    TNE,U     A0,3@^@@@C          J         SWAP@E@D@           IOW$    XL
)@@G@@  IOPKT               NO, READ A BLOCK    @]@@@           . @G@@@       XM
)@@G@@    . NOTE: WE CHECK FOR 2 POSSIBLE END OF REEL SENTINELS BECAUSE @F@@@ XN
)@@G@@          .       OF A FANG BUG THAT USES AN EOR SENTINEL WHICH IS@E@@@ XO
)@@G@@          .       DIFFERENT FROM FURPUR'S EOR SENTINEL.     @]@@@DEORTESXP
)@@G@@T     @H@@@           TNZ       COPGST               IS IT FURPUR COPY,GXQ
)@@G@@M STACK TAPE?     @C@@@           J         EORFANG              NO     XR

)@@G@@          TNE       A1,(EORSNL1)         IS IT END OF REEL SENTINEL?    XT
)@@G@@@C@@@           J         SWAP                 YES    @D@@@           J XU
)@@G@@        EORERR               NO, ERROR    @G@@@ EORFANG                 XV
)@@G@@               . CHECK FOR FANG'S EOR SENTINEL  @E@@@           LA      XW
)@@G@@  A1,BUFFER            GET FIRST WORD     @G@@@           TNE       A1,(XX
)@@G@@EORSNL2)         IS IT END OF REEL SENTINEL?    @E@@@           J       XY
)@@G@@  SWAP                 YES, SWAP REELS    @F@@@ EORERR    PRINT$S   ' ERXZ
)@@G@@ROR --- END OF REEL EXPECTED BUT NOT SEEN'@D@@@           J         FCENYA
)@@G@@D                FINISH UP    @]@@@           . @[@@@ SWAP  @E@@@       YB
)@@G@@    LA        A0,(0,TSWPKT)       SWAP TO NEXT REEL   @ @@@           ERYC
)@@G@@        TSWAP$    @E@@@           J         LGTRYA              READ FROYD
)@@G@@M NEXT REEL @[@@@  .    @E@@@ STKSKG    IOW$      IOPKT               REYE
)@@G@@AD A GARBAGE BLOCK@F@@@           LA,S1     A0,IOPKT+3          LOAD STAYF
)@@G@@TUS FROM READ     @H@@@           JZ        A0,STKSKG           CONTINUEYG
)@@G@@ IF IT WAS A GARBAGE BLOCK    @G@@@           TE,U      A0,1            YH
)@@G@@    WAS IT EOF AT END OF CYCLE ?    @H@@@           J         FCEND     YI
)@@G@@          NO. QUIT IF TAPE ERROR ENCOUNTERED    @[@@@ RTNEXT@E@@@       YJ
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,1                FLAG NEW FILE CYCLE @ @@@           SAYK
)@@G@@        A0,NUFIL  @G@@@           TZ        RCVTAP              PROCESSIYL
)@@G@@NG A RECOVERY TAPE ?    @H@@@           J         RCVTBL              YEYM
)@@G@@S.  OBTAIN MAIN ITEM FROM ITS LABEL @F@@@           TNZ       STKTAP    YN
)@@G@@          PROCESSING A STACK TAPE ? @E@@@           TZ        ONEFILE   YO
)@@G@@          SINGLE FILE MODE ?  @H@@@           J         STFPR           YP
)@@G@@    YES.  SKIP ASSIGN AND CYCLE CHECKS    @E@@@           LA        A0,CYQ
)@@G@@URFCYC          LOAD CURRENT F-CYCLE@E@@@           AA,U      A0,1      YR
)@@G@@          TRY NEXT NEWER ONE  @F@@@           TNZ       USECURR         YS
)@@G@@    USE CURRENT F-CYCLE ?     @G@@@           JZ        A0,FCEND        YT
)@@G@@    NO.  STOP AT RELATIVE CYCLE -1  @I@@@           TG,U      A0,1      YU
)@@G@@          YES.  HAS CURRENT CYCLE BEEN PROCESSED ?    @F@@@           J YV
)@@G@@        FCEND               YES.  END OF PROCESSING   @E@@@           SAYW
)@@G@@        A0,CURFCYC          UPDATE CURRENT CYCLE@F@@@           TNZ     YX
)@@G@@  FILESET             PROCESSING USER FILE SET ?@G@@@           J       YY
)@@G@@  EDSYSL              NO.  ASSIGN SYSTEM LOG FILE     @G@@@           F$YZ
)@@G@@MSG1    USEUF               NO.  EDIT @USE FOR USER FILE    @H@@@       ZA
)@@G@@    F$MSG     FILESET,,W          EDIT FIRST PART OF USER FILE NAME     ZB

)@@G@@    IS F-CYCLE ZERO ?   @F@@@           J         EDNFCY              NOZF

)@@G@@ FILE @G@@@           JN        A0,MISFCY           MISSING CYCLE IF UNAZP
)@@G@@SSIGNABLE   @G@@@           MSCON$    DRDPKT              RETRIEVE MAIN ZQ
)@@G@@ITEM FOR THE FILE @E@@@           TP        A0                  ERROR FRZR

)@@G@@R MISSING ABSOLUTE CYCLES IN A CONSECUTIVE RELATIVE   @H@@@ .         CYZX
)@@G@@CLE SET.  THIS INSURES A DELETION OF A LOG CYCLE WILL BE NOTICED  @[@@@ ZY
)@@G@@.     @G@@@           LA        A0,LAFC             LOAD LAST F-CYCLE PRZZ
)@@G@@OCESSED     @G@@@           JZ        A0,RIGHTAC          SKIP THIS CHECAA

)@@G@@@H@@@           SA        A0,LAFC             SET LAST ABSOLUTE F-CYCLE AX
)@@G@@FOR CHECK   @G@@@           TZ        RCVTAP              PROCESSING A RAY
)@@G@@ECOVERY TAPE ?    @G@@@           J         RIACCKSF            YES.  SKAZ

)@@G@@@[@@@ .     @F@@@ .         CONTINGENCY ROUTINE (TO ENABLE I/O 22 TO BE FM

)@@G@@    SAVE A0 IN SNAP PACKET    @D@@@           LA,S1     A0,CGYRTN       FP
)@@G@@    GET ERROR TYPE@E@@@           TE,U      A0,1                IS IT ANFQ

)@@G@@E PROGRAM   @[@@@ .     @E@@@ CGYRTX    LA,H2     A0,CGYRTN           LOGE
)@@G@@AD ERROR ADDRESS  @G@@@           AA,U      A0,1                POINT TOGF

)@@G@@T UP CONTINGENCY ON FIRST CALL@[@@@ .     @G@@@ FICONT    IALL$     CGYRGJ
