)@@G@@          EDIT ABSOLUTE F-CYCLE     @D@@@           F$MSGR    .         GZ
)@@G@@          COPY MESSAGE  @F@@@           F$DECV    BLKCNT              EDHA
)@@G@@IT BLOCK COUNT ON FILE  @C@@@           F$MSGR    .                   COHB
)@@G@@PY    @E@@@           F$DECV    RECFIL              EDIT RECORD IN FILE HC
)@@G@@@C@@@           F$MSGR    .                   COPY    @F@@@           LAHD
)@@G@@        A3,UBLOC            LOAD USER BUFFER POINTER  @E@@@           F$HE
)@@G@@DECV    LITYP,A3            EDIT LOG ENTRY TYPE @C@@@           F$MSGR  HF
)@@G@@  .                   COPY    @F@@@           F$DECV    LILEN,A3        HG
)@@G@@    EDIT LENGTH OF ENTRY DATA @C@@@           F$MSGR    .               HH
)@@G@@    COPY    @D@@@           F$COPY    6,LIRUNID,A3        EDIT RUNID    HI
)@@G@@@F@@@           F$MSGR    .                   COPY TO CREATION DATE     HJ
)@@G@@@F@@@           F$DAY1    LITDW,A3            EDIT DATE OF CREATION     HK
)@@G@@@E@@@           F$SKIP    2                   SKIP SOME SPACE     @F@@@ HL
)@@G@@          F$TIME    LITDW,A3            EDIT TIME OF CREATION     @F@@@ HM
)@@G@@          F$PRT     2                   PRINT THE DUMP HEADER     @[@@@ HN
)@@G@@.     @B@@@ .         DUMP THE TEXT OF THE LOG ENTRY  @[@@@ .     @E@@@ HO
)@@G@@          LA,U      A4                  A4 = WORD INDEX     @G@@@       HP
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A3,1                SET UP INCREMENT ON BUFFER INDEX@H@@@ HQ
)@@G@@          LR,U      R3,6                INITIALISE LINE COUNTER FOR 28 WHR
)@@G@@ORDS  @F@@@ LPDL      F$DECF    2,A4                EDIT WORDS INTO ENTRHS
)@@G@@Y     @F@@@           F$SKIP    4                   SKIP BEFORE OCTAL EDHT
)@@G@@ITING @G@@@           LR,U      R2,3                LOAD COUNTER FOR OCTHU
)@@G@@AL WORDS    @E@@@           SA        A3,A5               SAVE WORD POINHV
)@@G@@TER   @E@@@ LPDW      F$OCTF    12,,*A3             EDIT WORD IN OCTAL  HW
)@@G@@@E@@@           F$SKIP    2                   SKIP BETWEEN WORDS  @F@@@ HX
)@@G@@          JGD       R2,LPDW             DUMP FOUR WORDS IN OCTAL  @G@@@ HY
)@@G@@          F$SKIP    5                   SKIP BEFORE ALPHANUMERIC DUMP   HZ
)@@G@@@E@@@           LA        A3,A5               RELOAD WORD POINTER @E@@@ IA
)@@G@@          LR,U      R2,3                RESET WORD COUNT    @E@@@ LPDAN IB
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,,*A3             LOAD A WORD ADDRESS @G@@@           F$IC
)@@G@@COPY    6                   COPY THE WORD ONTO THE LINE     @E@@@       ID
)@@G@@    F$SKIP    1                   SKIP BETWEEN WORDS  @F@@@           JGIE
)@@G@@D       R2,LPDAN            LOOP FOR ALL ALPHA WORDS  @F@@@           LAIF
)@@G@@,U      A0,1                LOAD NORMAL SKIP COUNT    @D@@@           TNIG
)@@G@@Z       A4                  FIRST LINE ?  @G@@@           LA,U      A0,2IH
)@@G@@                YES.  SKIP TWO FOR FIRST LINE   @C@@@           F$PRT   II
)@@G@@  .                   PRINT IT@E@@@           AA,U      A4,4            IJ
)@@G@@    INCREMENT WORD COUNT@E@@@           JGD       R3,LPDL             LOIK
)@@G@@OP FOR ALL LINES  @F@@@           J         DMPREC              RETURN TIL
)@@G@@O CALLER OF DUMP  @[@@@ .     @A@@@ .         USER SERVICE ROUTINES     IM
)@@G@@@[@@@ .     @G@@@ .         THESE ROUTINES PROVIDE ANCILLARY SERVICES FOIN
)@@G@@R LGITEM.  THEY   @H@@@ .         PERMIT THE CALLER TO SET MODES, SPECIFIO
)@@G@@Y FILES FOR PROCESSING, AND   @C@@@ .         DUMP LOG ITEMS IN AN EDITEIP
)@@G@@D FORMAT.   @[@@@ .     @[@@@ .     @ @@@ .         CALL LGDUMP(BUF)    IQ
)@@G@@@[@@@ .     @H@@@ .         PRODUCES AN EDITED DUMP OF THE LOG ITEM IN TIR
)@@G@@HE SPECIFIED BUFFER.    @H@@@ .         THE DUMP WILL BE LABELED AS IF TIS
)@@G@@HE ITEM DUMPED WAS THE LAST ONE     @B@@@ .         SENT TO THE PROGRAM IT
)@@G@@VIA LGITEM  @[@@@ .     @E@@@ LGDUMP*   LA,U      A0,*0,X11           GEIU
)@@G@@T BUFFER ADDRESS  @F@@@           SA,H2     A0,UBLOC            STORE INIV
)@@G@@TO BUFFER POINTER @E@@@           LA,U      A0,2,X11            LOAD RETIW
)@@G@@URN POINT   @D@@@           SA,H2     A0,LGITRT           SET UP RETURN IX
)@@G@@@D@@@           SLJ       DMPREC              DUMP THE ITEM @C@@@       IY
)@@G@@    J         LGITRT              RETURN  @[@@@ .     @^@@@ .         CAIZ
)@@G@@LL LGCURR   @[@@@ .     @H@@@ .         CONDITIONS LGITEM TO RETURN LOG JA
)@@G@@ITEMS FROM THE LOG FILE CURRENTLY   @G@@@ .         BEING WRITTEN BY THEJB
)@@G@@ SYSTEM.  THIS SHOULD BE CALLED BEFORE THE@H@@@ .         FIRST CALL ON JC
)@@G@@LGITEM.  THE MODE IS CLEARED WHEN THE LAST LOG ITEM   @G@@@ .         ISJD
)@@G@@ RETURNED BY LGITEM.  OBVIOUSLY, THIS CALL HAS MEANING ONLY @B@@@ .     JE
)@@G@@    FOR MASS STORAGE LOG FILES.     @[@@@ .     @D@@@ LGCURR*   LA,U    JF
)@@G@@  A0,1                LOAD A ONE    @G@@@           SA        A0,USECURRJG
)@@G@@          SET 'USE CURRENT CYCLE' FLAG    @F@@@           J         1,X1JH
)@@G@@1               RETURN TO USER PROGRAM    @[@@@ .     @ @@@ .         CAJI
)@@G@@LL LGMSGS(MODE)   @[@@@ .     @G@@@ .         CONTROLS THE MESSAGES PRINJJ
)@@G@@TED BY LGITEM.  MODE IS AN INTEGER. @G@@@ .         IS ZERO, MESSAGES WIJK
)@@G@@LL BE PRINTED LOGGING THE BEGINNING AND   @G@@@ .         END OF EACH LOJL
)@@G@@G CYCLE OR FILE PROCESSED, AND A SUMMARY WILL   @G@@@ .         BE PRINTJM
)@@G@@ED OF THE NUMBER OF BLOCKS AND ITEMS IN EACH FILE.    @G@@@ .         THJN
)@@G@@IS IS THE DEFAULT MODE.  IF ONE, THESE MESSAGES WILL BE     @D@@@ .     JO
)@@G@@    SUPPRESSED UNLESS AN ERROR IS DETECTED.     @[@@@ .     @F@@@ LGMSGSJP
)@@G@@*   LA        A0,*0,X11           LOAD VERBOSITY COEFFICIENT@G@@@       JQ
)@@G@@    SA        A0,SHORTFORM        SET LENGTH OF OUTPUT DESIRED    @E@@@ JR
)@@G@@          J         2,X11               RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@ .     JS
)@@G@@@^@@@ .         CALL LGDEL    @[@@@ .     @F@@@ .         DELETES ALL CYJT
)@@G@@CLES OF THE LOG FILE RETURNED BY LGITEM.  @G@@@ .         NORMALLY CALLEJU
)@@G@@D AFTER THE LOG INFORMATION IS SAFELY ON TAPE.  @[@@@ .     @G@@@ LGDEL*JV
)@@G@@    SX        X11,LGITRT          SAVE RETURN POINT TO CALLER     @G@@@ JW
)@@G@@          LR,U      R3,31               LOAD LOOP COUNT TO DELETE CYCLESJX
)@@G@@@G@@@           LA        A3,(1,0)            LOAD POINTER INTO F-CYCLE JY
)@@G@@LIST  @[@@@ .     @I@@@ LGDNC     LA        A5,FCLIST,*A3       LOAD NEXJZ
)@@G@@T ABSOLUTE CYCLE FROM F-CYCLE LIST  @H@@@           JZ        A5,LGDDONEKA
)@@G@@          IF ZERO, ALL CYCLES HAVE BEEN DELETED @G@@@           F$MSG   KB
)@@G@@  USELOG              EDIT @USE IMAGE FOR LOG CYCLE   @G@@@           F$KC
)@@G@@DECV    A5                  EDIT THE ABSOLUTE CYCLE NUMBER  @G@@@       KD
)@@G@@    F$MSGR    .                   COPY THE REST OF THE USE IMAGE  @H@@@ KE
)@@G@@          CSF$      FL$                 ATTACH THE @USE NAME TO THE CYCLKF
)@@G@@E     @F@@@           F$DT      .                   CLEAR THE EDITING LIKG
)@@G@@NE    @F@@@           LA        A4,('ASSIGN')       LOAD FLAG FOR ASSIGNKH
)@@G@@ ERROR@G@@@           CSF$      ASGAQYD             TRY TO ASSIGN,AQYD TKI
)@@G@@HE LOG CYCLE@G@@@           JN        A0,LGDELER          EDIT ERROR MESKJ
)@@G@@SAGE IF IMPOSSIBLE@G@@@           LA        A4,('FREE')         LOAD FLAKK
)@@G@@G FOR FREE OF LOG CYCLE @G@@@           CSF$      FRELOG              @FKL
)@@G@@REE THE LOG CYCLE, DROPPING IT@I@@@           JN        A0,LGDELER      KM
)@@G@@    EDIT ERROR MESSAGE IF BAD STATUS RETURNED   @G@@@           TZ      KN
)@@G@@  SHORTFORM           ABBREVIATED LISTING DESIRED ?   @G@@@           J KO
)@@G@@        LGDCYCD             YES.  GO PROCESS NEXT CYCLE     @F@@@       KP
)@@G@@    F$MSG     DELLIST             EDIT THE DELETE MESSAGE   @G@@@       KQ
)@@G@@    F$DECV    A5                  EDIT ABSOLUTE CYCLE JUST DELETED@G@@@ KR
)@@G@@          F$MSGR    .                   COPY THE REST OF THE MESSAGE    KS
)@@G@@@E@@@           F$PRT     1                   PRINT THE MESSAGE   @G@@@ KT
)@@G@@LGDCYCD   JGD       R3,LGDNC            LOOP FOR ALL CYCLES IN FCLIST   KU
)@@G@@@E@@@ LGDDONE   LX        X11,LGITRT          LOAD RETURN POINT   @G@@@ KV
)@@G@@          SZ        FCLIST              MARK NO CYCLES TO BE DELETED    KW
)@@G@@@E@@@           J         1,X11               RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@ KX
)@@G@@.     @G@@@ LGDELER   SA        A0,R2               SAVE CSF$ STATUS FROKY
)@@G@@M ERROR     @G@@@           F$MSG     DELERM              EDIT THE DELETKZ
)@@G@@E ERROR MESSAGE   @G@@@           F$DECV    A5                  EDIT CYCLA
)@@G@@LE ERROR ENCOUNTERED ON @G@@@           F$MSGR    .                   COLB
)@@G@@PY MESSAGE TO CSF$ STATUS     @F@@@           F$OCTF    12,R2           LC
)@@G@@    EDIT ASSIGN OR FREE STATUS@F@@@           F$MSGR    .               LD
)@@G@@    COPY TO OPERATION TYPE    @F@@@           F$FD1     A4              LE
)@@G@@    EDIT 'ASSIGN' OR 'FREE'   @G@@@           F$MSGR    .               LF
)@@G@@    COPY THE REST OF THE MESSAGE    @E@@@           F$PRT     1         LG
)@@G@@          PRINT THE MESSAGE   @G@@@           CSF$      FRELOG          LH
)@@G@@    TRY TO FREE THE INTERNAL NAME   @G@@@           J         LGDCYCD   LI
)@@G@@          RETURN TO PROCESS NEXT CYCLE    @[@@@ .     @C@@@ .         CALJ
)@@G@@LL LGFILE(CHARS,'QUAL*FILE(CYC)')   @[@@@ .     @H@@@ .         THIS ROULK
)@@G@@TINE CONDITIONS LGITEM TO RETURN THE LOG ITEMS FROM THE     @G@@@ .     LL
)@@G@@    SPECIFIED FILE.  WHEN THE FILE HAS BEEN EXHAUSTED, LGITEM WILL@ @@@ LM
)@@G@@.         TAKE THE EOF RETURN.@[@@@ .     @[@@@ .     @D@@@ .         CALN
)@@G@@LL LGFLST('QUAL*FILENAME(&)/RKEY/WKEY&')  @[@@@ .     @F@@@ .         THLO
)@@G@@IS ROUTINE CONDITIONS LGITEM TO RETURN LOG ITEMS FROM @F@@@ .         ASLP
)@@G@@CENDING CYCLES OF THE NAMED USER FILE.  THE FILE IS   @F@@@ .         ASLQ
)@@G@@SUMED TO BE IN A FORMAT COMPATIBLE WITH THAT OF THE   @F@@@ .         SYLR
)@@G@@STEM LOG FILE.  (SUCH FILES MAY BE GENERATED WITH THE @F@@@ .         'LLS
)@@G@@OG' SUBROUTINE IN LIBRARY-W).  THE CURRENT CYCLE WILL @F@@@ .         BELT
)@@G@@ PROCESSED ONLY IF 'LGCURR' IS CALLED.  THE ASSIGN    @F@@@ .         IMLU
)@@G@@AGE GENERATED FOR THE USER FILE WILL BE THE IMAGE     @F@@@ .         SULV
)@@G@@PPLIED AS THE PARAMETER TO LGFLST, WITH THE F-CYCLE   @F@@@ .         INLW
)@@G@@SERTED WHERE THE FIRST AMPERSAND APPEARS.  THE SECOND @H@@@ .         AMLX
)@@G@@PERSANE IS REQUIRED TO TERMINATE THE FILE NAME SPECIFICATION.     @[@@@ LY
)@@G@@.     @G@@@ LGFLST*   LA,H2     A0,,X11             LOAD ADDRESS OF FILELZ
)@@G@@ SET IMAGE  @E@@@           SA        A0,FILESET          SAVE FILE SET MA
)@@G@@NAME  @E@@@           J         2,X11               RETURN TO CALLER    MB
)@@G@@@[@@@ .     @A@@@ .         CALL LGTAPE('INTNAME')    @[@@@ .     @G@@@ MC
)@@G@@.         THIS ROUTINE CONDITIONS LOGITEM TO READ A LOG TAPE ASSIGNED   MD
)@@G@@@G@@@ .         TO THE SPECIFIED INTERNAL NAME.  THE FILE MUST BE ASSIGNME
)@@G@@ED    @G@@@ .         BEFORE THE CALL ON LGTAPE IS MADE.  AT THE END OF MF
)@@G@@THE TAPE,   @G@@@ .         LOGITEM WILL RETURN THE END OF FILE STATUS AMG
)@@G@@ND RELEASE ITS    @B@@@ .         INTERNAL NAME ON THE TAPE FILE. @[@@@ MH
)@@G@@.     @E@@@ LGTAPE*   LA,U      A3,,X11             SAVE RETURN POINT   MI
)@@G@@@G@@@           F$MSG     USEUF               EDIT @USE TO USER'S FILE NMJ
)@@G@@AME   @F@@@           F$FD2     *0,A3               EDIT USER'S FILE NAMMK
)@@G@@E     @G@@@           CSF$      FL$                 ATTACH 'LOG' TO USERML
)@@G@@'S FILE NAME@E@@@           F$DT      .                   CLEAR THE IMAGMM
)@@G@@E     @F@@@           DL        A0,IOPKT            LOAD INTERNAL FILE NMN
)@@G@@AME   @E@@@           DS        A0,BUFFER           SET IN I/O BUFFER   MO
)@@G@@@G@@@           FITEM$    BUFFER              RETURN ASSIGNMENT INFORMATMP
)@@G@@ION   @A@@@ .         ** CHECK ASSIGNMENT **    @E@@@           LA      MQ
)@@G@@  A0,BUFFER+11        LOAD REEL NUMBER    @G@@@           SA        A0,RMR
)@@G@@EELNO           SET REEL NUMBER FOR MESSAGES    @D@@@           LA,U    MS
)@@G@@  A0,1                GET NON-ZERO  @E@@@           SA        A0,ONEFILEMT
)@@G@@          SET SINGLE-FILE MODE@H@@@           LA,U      A0,28*63        MU
)@@G@@    LOAD LENGTH OF HISTORY TAPE BLOCKS    @E@@@           SA,H1     A0,IMV
)@@G@@OPKT+4          SET LONG ACCESS WORD@C@@@           J         2,A3      MW
)@@G@@          RETURN  @[@@@ .     @A@@@ .         CALL LGRCVT('INTNAME')    MX
)@@G@@@[@@@ .     @H@@@ .         THIS ROUTINE INITIALISES LGITEM TO READ A REMY
)@@G@@COVERY TAPE GENERATED   @G@@@ .         BY THE LOG FILE RECOVERY MECHANIMZ
)@@G@@SM IN THE EXEC.  SUCH A TAPE  @G@@@ .         CONSISTS OF A SERIES OF FINA
)@@G@@LES, BEGINNING WITH A 28 WORD LABEL @G@@@ .         CONTAINING THE FILE NB
)@@G@@MAIN ITEM, A SERIES OF 224 WORD DATA DUMP @H@@@ .         BLOCKS, AND TENC
)@@G@@RMINATED BY A FILE MARK.  A DOUBLE FILE MARK ENDS     @ @@@ .         THND
)@@G@@E RECOVERY TAPE.  @[@@@ .     @E@@@ LGRCVT*   LA,U      A3,,X11         NE
)@@G@@    SAVE RETURN POINT   @F@@@           F$MSG     USEUF               EDNF
)@@G@@IT @USE TO USER FILE    @F@@@           F$FD2     *0,A3               EDNG
)@@G@@IT USER'S INTERNAL NAME @F@@@           CSF$      FL$                 ATNH
)@@G@@TACH THE INTERNAL NAME  @E@@@           DL        A0,IOPKT            LONI
)@@G@@AD INTERNAL NAME  @E@@@           DS        A0,BUFFER           SET IN INJ
)@@G@@/O BUFFER   @F@@@           FITEM$    BUFFER              GET ASSIGNMENTNK
)@@G@@ INFORMATION@B@@@ .         ** CHECK FILE ASSIGNMENT **     @F@@@       NL
)@@G@@    LA        A0,BUFFER+11        LOAD CURRENT REEL NUMBER  @G@@@       NM
)@@G@@    SA        A0,REELNO           SAVE REEL NUMBER FOR MESSAGES   @E@@@ NN
)@@G@@          F$DT      .                   CLEAR THE IMAGE     @D@@@       NO
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,1                LOAD A ONE    @F@@@           SA      NP
)@@G@@  A0,RCVTAP           SET RECOVERY TAPE MODE    @E@@@           J       NQ
)@@G@@  2,A3                RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@ .     @A@@@ .         CANR
)@@G@@LL LGUAFT('INTNAME')    @[@@@ .     @G@@@ .         THIS ROUTINE INITIALNS
)@@G@@ISES LGITEM TO READ A BECHTEL UAF TAPE.   @H@@@ .         A UAF TAPE CONNT
)@@G@@TAINS TWO FILES, EACH CONSISTING OF 1792 WORD RECORDS.@H@@@ .         THNU
)@@G@@E FIRST FILE CONTAINS USER LOG ENTRIES, AND THE SECOND CONTAINS   @H@@@ NV
)@@G@@.         EXEC LOG ENTRIES.  EACH FILE IS TERMINATED BY A LOG ITEM OF TYNW
)@@G@@PE    @B@@@ .         077 AND AN END OF FILE MARK.    @[@@@ .     @E@@@ NX
)@@G@@LGUAFT*   LA,U      A3,,X11             SAVE RETURN POINT   @F@@@       NY
)@@G@@    F$MSG     USEUF               EDIT @USE TO USER FILE    @F@@@       NZ
)@@G@@    F$FD2     *0,A3               EDIT USER'S INTERNAL NAME @F@@@       OA
)@@G@@    CSF$      FL$                 ATTACH THE INTERNAL NAME  @E@@@       OB
)@@G@@    DL        A0,IOPKT            LOAD INTERNAL NAME  @E@@@           DSOC
)@@G@@        A0,BUFFER           SET IN I/O BUFFER   @F@@@           FITEM$  OD
)@@G@@  BUFFER              GET ASSIGNMENT INFORMATION@B@@@ .         ** CHECKOE
)@@G@@ FILE ASSIGNMENT **     @F@@@           LA        A0,BUFFER+11        LOOF
)@@G@@AD CURRENT REEL NUMBER  @G@@@           SA        A0,REELNO           SAOG
)@@G@@VE REEL NUMBER FOR MESSAGES   @D@@@           F$DT      .               OH
)@@G@@    CLEAR THE LINE@D@@@           LA,U      A0,1                LOAD A OOI
)@@G@@NE    @E@@@           SA        A0,ONEFILE          SET SINGLE FILE MODEOJ
)@@G@@@E@@@           SA        A0,UAFTAP           SET UAF TAPE MODE   @G@@@ OK
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,28*64            LOAD LENGTH OF UAF TAPE BLOCKS  OL
)@@G@@@F@@@           SA,H1     A0,IOPKT+4          SET LENGTH FOR ACCESS WORDOM
)@@G@@@F@@@           SZ        UAFEOF              CLEAR UAF TAPE EOF MODE   ON
)@@G@@@E@@@           J         2,A3                RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@ OO
)@@G@@.     @A@@@ .         CALL LGSTKT('INTNAME')    @[@@@ .     @G@@@ .     OP
)@@G@@    THIS ROUTINE CONDITIONS LGITEM TO RETURN LOG ENTRIES FROM     @F@@@ OQ
)@@G@@.         A TAPE CONTAINING DUMPS OF LOG CYCLES FROM MASS STORAGE.@G@@@ OR
)@@G@@.         EACH LOG CYCLE IS ASSUMED TO CONTAIN THE -0 SENTINEL AT THE   OS
)@@G@@@F@@@ .         END, AND END-OF-FILE MARKS ARE ASSUMED TO SEPARATE THE  OT
)@@G@@@G@@@ .         CYCLES ON TAPE.  THE END OF TAPE IS DELIMITED BY A DOUBLOU
)@@G@@E     @^@@@ .         END OF FILE.  @[@@@ .     @E@@@ LGSTKT*   LA,U    OV
)@@G@@  A3,,X11             SAVE ADDRESS OF CALL@H@@@           F$MSG     USEUOW
)@@G@@F               EDIT @USE STATEMENT FOR USER FILE     @F@@@           F$OX
)@@G@@FD2     *0,A3               EDIT USER'S FILE NAME     @E@@@  . ******** OY
)@@G@@NOTE: THE @USE FUNCTION HAS BEEN MOVED INTO     @F@@@  .                OZ
)@@G@@THE CALLING PROGRAM, TO FACILITATE MULTIPLE     @A@@@  .                PA
)@@G@@REEL TAPE FILES.  @G@A@ .          CSF$      FL$                 ATTACH PB
)@@G@@@USE NAME TO USER FILE  @G@@@A           CSF$      FL$                 APC
)@@G@@TTACH @USE NAME TO USER FILE  @G@@@           DL        A0,IOPKT        PD
)@@G@@    LOAD FILE NAME FROM I/O PACKET  @G@@@           DS        A0,BUFFER PE
)@@G@@          SET IN I/O BUFFER FOR FITEM$    @G@@@           FITEM$    BUFFPF
)@@G@@ER              GET FILE ASSIGNMENT INFORMATION @B@@@ .         ** CHECKPG
)@@G@@ FILE ASSIGNMENT **     @F@@@           LA        A0,BUFFER+11        GEPH
)@@G@@T REEL NUMBER FOR TAPE  @G@@@           SA        A0,REELNO           SAPI
)@@G@@VE REEL NUMBER FOR EDITING    @F@@@           F$DT      .               PJ
)@@G@@    CLEAR THE EDITING LINE    @D@@@           LA,U      A0,1            PK
)@@G@@    LOAD A ONE    @G@@@           SA        A0,STKTAP           FLAG PROPL
)@@G@@CESSING A STACK TAPE    @D@@@           J         2,A3                REPM
)@@G@@TURN TO CALL@[@@@ .     @[@@@  .    @A@@@ .         ** UNREALISED DREAMSPN
)@@G@@ **   @[@@@ .     @]@@@ LBLERR    . @^@@@ NOTRCV    EABT$     .   @[@@@ PO
)@@G@@.     @A@@@ .         BUFFERS AND CONSTANTS     @[@@@ .     @[@@@ $(2). PP
)@@G@@@B@A@ USELOG    '@USE LOG,SYS$*SYSTEM$LOG$(&)&' @C@@@AUSELOG    '@USE $LPQ
)@@G@@OG$$,SYS$*SYSTEM$LOG$(&)&'    @^@A@ USEUF     '@USE LOG,&'  @ @@@AUSEUF PR
)@@G@@    '@USE $LOG$$,&'     @ @A@ FREINT    '@FREE,A LOG . '    @ @@@AFREINTPS
)@@G@@    '@FREE,A $LOG$$ . ' @ @A@ ASGFSL    '@ASG,AE LOG . '    @ @@@AASGFSLPT
)@@G@@    '@ASG,AE $LOG$$ . ' @ @A@ ASGLOG    '@ASG,AQE LOG . '   @ @@@AASGLOGPU
)@@G@@    '@ASG,AQE $LOG$$ . '@ @A@ ASGAQYD   '@ASG,AQYEG LOG . ' @A@@@AASGAQYPV
)@@G@@D   '@ASG,AQYEG $LOG$$ . '    @ @A@ FRELOG    '@FREE   LOG . '    @ @@@APW
)@@G@@FRELOG    '@FREE   $LOG$$ . ' @[@@@ .     @E@@@ CYM       'CYCLE & (RELAPX
)@@G@@TIVE CYCLE &) CREATED AT & ON &'    @A@@@ RCVSRC    ' FROM RECOVERY TAPEPY
)@@G@@ &'   @H@@@ BLP       ' BLOCKS PROCESSED, & LOG ENTRIES&.&  *** I/O ERROPZ
)@@G@@R STATUS: & ***&' @G@@@ CYCHDR    'LOG CYCLE: & BLOCK: & RECORD: & TYPE:QA
)@@G@@ & LENGTH: & RUNID: & ';@^@@@           'CREATED: &'  @B@@@ DELLIST   'AQB
)@@G@@BSOLUTE LOG CYCLE & DELETED.&'@G@@@ DELERM    '***   UNABLE TO DELETE ABQC
)@@G@@SOLUTE LOG CYCLE &.  & STATUS ';    @A@@@           'RETURNED ON &.  ***QD
)@@G@@&'    @I@@@ CGYMSG    'CONTINGENCY WHILE PROCESSING LOG FILE:  ERROR TYPQE
)@@G@@E: &  ERROR CODE:';     @A@@@           ' &  ERROR ADDRESS: &'    @F@@@ QF
)@@G@@MFM       '***  CANNOT ASSIGN RELATIVE CYCLE &, STATUS: &  ***&'  @ @@@ QG
)@@G@@LERML     '** ILLEGAL LENGTH&'@B@@@ LERMT     '** ILLEGAL TIME/DATE WORDQH
)@@G@@ &'   @A@@@ LERMR     '** ILLEGAL RUNID ''&''&' @C@@@ RDEL      ' IN LOGQI
)@@G@@ ENTRY.  RECORD DELETED **&'  @G@@@ WRACM     '***  ABSOLUTE LOG CYCLES QJ
)@@G@@MISSING BETWEEN & (RELATIVE &) ';   @A@@@           'AND & (RELATIVE &) QK
)@@G@@ ***&'@I@@@ MSCEM     '***  CANNOT DETERMINE ABSOLUTE F-CYCLE OF CYCLE &QL
)@@G@@, MSCON$ STATUS: &';    @C@@@           '.  PROCESSING ATTEMPTED ANYWAY.QM
)@@G@@&'    @C@@@ BOOM      '** POSSIBLE ACCOUNTING DATA LOSS ***'@[@@@ .     QN
)@@G@@@B@A@ IOPKT     IO$PKT,R$ 'LOG' 224,BUFFER 0    @B@@@AIOPKT     IO$PKT,RQO
)@@G@@$ '$LOG$$' 224,BUFFER 0 @A@A@ RDLBL     IO$PKT,R$ 'LOG' 28,MI     @A@@@AQP
)@@G@@RDLBL     IO$PKT,R$ '$LOG$$' 28,MI  @A@@@ SPKT      SNAP$PKT,'XAR' CGYRTQQ
)@@G@@N,2   @[@@@ .     @ @@@ DR        FORM      12,6,18   @G@@@ DRDPKT    * QR
)@@G@@        DREAD$              MSCON$ PACKET TO READ MAIN ITEM @^@A@       QS
)@@G@@    'LOG         '@^@@@A          '$LOG$$      '@F@@@           DR      QT
)@@G@@  28,1,MI             READ SECTOR 0 OF MAIN ITEM@ @@@           *       QU
)@@G@@  0,0,0     @[@@@ .     @F@@@ UAFEOF    EQUF      $,,S1               UAQV
)@@G@@F TAPE FIRST EOF FLAG   @E@@@ FIRST     EQUF      $,,S2               FIQW

)@@G@@      FDECF$      FFD2$       FITEM$      R$          DREAD$      LGCURRXM
)@@G@@      @@[@@@@@@@D LGDEL       @@[@@@@@@@DFLGDUMP      @@[@@@@@@@C_LGFLSTXN
)@@G@@      @@[@@@@@@@D_LGITEM      @@[@@@@@@@@@LGMSGS      @@[@@@@@@@DCLGRCVTXO
)@@G@@      @@[@@@@@@@EPLGSTKT      @@[@@@@@@@E;LGTAPE      @@[@@@@@@@E]LGUAFTXP
)@@G@@      @@[@@@@@@@E&RSCR00*[S@@@*SDFF*@@@@@@@D@@@@C     PROGRAM TO PERFORMXQ
)@@G@@ LOOKUP TABLE SIZE ANALYSIS.  @G@@@@C     THE VALUE OF 'DCLUTS' IS INPUTXR
)@@G@@ VIA DATA CARD, BUT CANNOT EXCEED   @A@@@@C     PARAMETER VARIABLE 'MAX'XS
)@@G@@.     @@@@@@@F@@@@C     THIS PROGRAM USES THE DIREC$ SUBROUTINE PACKAGE XT
)@@G@@TO READ UP  @F@@@@C     ALL LEAD ITEMS IN THE SYSTEM, CALLS A HASH SUBROXU
)@@G@@UTINE TO    @F@@@@C     FORM THE TABLE INDEX, AND COUNTS THE NUMBER OF FXV
)@@G@@ILES WHICH  @A@@@@C     USE EACH LOOKUP TABLE ENTRY.  @@@@@@@F@@@@C     XW
)@@G@@                                  DUFF KURLAND, MARCH 1980  @@@@@@@@@@@@XX
)@@G@@@ @@@@      IMPLICIT INTEGER (A-Z)  @ @@@@      PARAMETER MAX = 30000   XY
)@@G@@@ @@@@      PARAMETER DEFALT = 8191 @E@@@@      DIMENSION LUT (MAX), ECOXZ
)@@G@@DE (2), LEAD (28), COUNT(30)  @A@@@@      DIMENSION CHAR(25), LINE(100) YA
)@@G@@@C@@@@      DATA INDEX/0/, ECODE/0,0/, LUT/MAX*0/     @E@@@@      DATA EYB
)@@G@@MPTY/0/, MORE/0/, COUNT/30*0/, HIGH/0/, FILES/0/@F@@@@      DATA CHAR/1HYC
)@@G@@ ,1H.,1H2,1H3,1H4,1H5,1H6,1H7,1H8,1H9,15*1H*/   @@@@@@@#@@@@      PRINT YD
)@@G@@1     @F@]@@1     FORMAT (1H1,'LUT SIZER - WHAT DCLUTS VALUE SHOULD BE UYE
)@@G@@SED?')@G@@@]1     FORMAT (1H1,'LUT SIZER - ENTER DCLUTS, HASH FUNC, S.I.YF
)@@G@@ THRESHOLD')@A@]@@      READ (5,2,END=100) DCLUTS     @C@@@]      READ (YG
)@@G@@5,2,END=100) DCLUTS, WHICH, THRESH  @#@@@@2     FORMAT ()   @B@@@@      YH
)@@G@@IF (DCLUTS .GT. MAX) DCLUTS = MAX   @#@]@[      PRINT 6     @C@]@[6     YI
)@@G@@FORMAT (1H ,'WHICH HASHING ALGORITHM?')   @ @]@[      READ (5,2,END=105)YJ
)@@G@@ WHICH@#@]@@      PRINT 3     @G@]@@3     FORMAT (1H0,'ENTER SEARCH ITEMYK
)@@G@@ THRESHOLD (ZERO TO TURN OFF DIAGNOS@^@]@@     *TIC PRINT).')     @A@]@@YL
)@@G@@      READ (5,2,END=110) THRESH     @#@@@@      GOTO 120    @^@@@@100   YM
)@@G@@DCLUTS = DEFALT   @#@]@[105   WHICH = 0   @#@@@]      WHICH = 0   @#@]@@YN
)@@G@@110   THRESH = 6  @#@@@]      THRESH = 6  @@@@@@@B@@@@120   IF (THRESH .YO
)@@G@@LT. 2) THRESH = 999     @ @[@@      PRINT 4, DCLUTS, THRESH @A@@@[      YP
)@@G@@PRINT 4, DCLUTS, WHICH, THRESH@F@@@@4     FORMAT (1H0,'LOOKUP TABLE SIZEYQ
)@@G@@R, USING DCLUTS VALUE', I6,   @C@[@@     *            ' AND STANDARD HASYR
)@@G@@HING.',/,   @D@@@[     *            ' AND HASHING ALOGRITHM ',I2,/,     YS
)@@G@@@F@@@@     *        1H ,'SEARCH ITEM DIAGNOSTIC THRESHOLD = ',I3,//)    YT
)@@G@@@@@@@@@A@@@@      CALL DIRINT (ECODE,0,2,0)     @A@@@@      IF (ECODE(1)YU
)@@G@@ .NE. 0) GOTO 900 @@@@@@@A@@@@200   CALL DIRSEC (ECODE, 0, LEAD)  @A@@@@YV
)@@G@@      IF (ECODE .EQ. 3) GOTO 300    @A@@@@      IF (ECODE .NE. 0) GOTO 9YW
)@@G@@00    @^@@@@      FILES = FILES + 1 @G@[@@      CALL HASH (LEAD(2), LEADYX
)@@G@@(3), LEAD(4), LEAD(5), DCLUTS, INDEX)     @G@@@[      CALL HASH (WHICH,LYY
)@@G@@EAD(2),LEAD(3),LEAD(4),LEAD(5),DCLUTS,INDEX)    @^@@@@      INDEX = INDEYZ
)@@G@@X + 1 @A@@@@      LUT (INDEX) = LUT (INDEX) + 1 @@@@@@@C@@@@      IF (LUZA
)@@G@@T (INDEX) .LT. THRESH) GOTO 200     @G@@@@      PRINT 5, LEAD(2), LEAD(3ZB
)@@G@@), LEAD(4), LEAD(5), INDEX, LUT (INDEX)   @E@@@@5     FORMAT (1H ,2A6,'*ZC
)@@G@@',2A6,'  INDEX',I6,'  COUNT =',I2)  @#@@@@      GOTO 200    @@@@@@@^@@@@ZD
)@@G@@300   PRINT 10, FILES   @C@@@@10    FORMAT (1H0,'WITH ',I5,' F-CYCLE SETZE
)@@G@@S:',/)@^@@@@      DO 310 I=1,DCLUTS @#@@@@      N = LUT (I) @A@@@@      ZF
)@@G@@IF (N .GT. HIGH) HIGH = N     @B@@@@      IF (N .EQ. 0) EMPTY = EMPTY + ZG
)@@G@@1     @B@@@@      IF (N .GT. 1) MORE  = MORE  + 1     @C@@@@310   IF (N ZH
)@@G@@.GT. 0) COUNT (N) = COUNT (N) + 1   @B@@@@      PRINT 11, EMPTY, COUNT (ZI
)@@G@@1), MORE    @B@@@@11    FORMAT (//,1H ,I5,' EMPTY SLOTS',/, @C@@@@     *ZJ
)@@G@@           1H ,I5,' LEAD ITEM LINKS',/,   @C@@@@     *           1H ,I5,ZK
)@@G@@' SEARCH ITEM LINKS')   @ @@@@      IF (HIGH .LT. 2) STOP   @^@@@@      ZL
)@@G@@DO 320 I=2,HIGH   @D@@@@320   IF (COUNT (I) .NE. 0) PRINT 12, I, COUNT (ZM
)@@G@@I)    @C@@@@12    FORMAT (1H ,8X,'WITH',I3,' FILES:',I5)    @#@@@@      ZN
)@@G@@PRINT 13    @G@@@@13    FORMAT (//,1H ,'LOOKUP TABLE MAP, WHERE  BLANK  ZO
)@@G@@= UNUSED SLOT',/, @D@@@@     *           1H ,25X,'PERIOD = LEAD ITEM LINZP
)@@G@@K',/, @E@@@@     *           1H ,22X,'1-9 AND * = SEARCH ITEM LINK',    ZQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@     *//,1H ,8X,' ',19X,'2',19X,'4',19X,'6',19X,'8',18X,'9',/,    ZR
)@@G@@@G@@@@     *           1H ,8X,'0',19X,'0',19X,'0',19X,'0',19X,'0',18X,'9ZS
)@@G@@',/,  @A@@@@     *           1H ,8X,100('-'))   @ @@@@      DO 340 I=0,DZT
)@@G@@CLUTS,100   @^@@@@      DO 330 J=1,100    @ @@@@      LINE (J) = CHAR (1ZU
)@@G@@)     @B@@@@      IF ((I + J) .GT. DCLUTS) GOTO 330   @^@@@@      K = LUZV
)@@G@@T (I + J)   @B@@@@      IF (K .EQ. 1) LINE (J) = CHAR (2)   @C@@@@      ZW
)@@G@@IF (K .GT. 1) LINE (J) = CHAR (K + 1)     @#@@@@330   CONTINUE    @^@@@@ZX
)@@G@@340   PRINT 14, I, LINE @A@@@@14    FORMAT (1H ,I6, 2X, 100A1)    @]@@@@ZY
)@@G@@      STOP  @@@@@@@^@@@@900   PRINT 901, ECODE  @E@@@@901   FORMAT (1H0,ZZ
)@@G@@'DIREC$ ERROR TYPE ',I2,' CODE ',O12)     @]@@@@      STOP  @@@@@@@]@@@@AA
)@@G@@      END   ___@@@@@@@@@*[S@@[*SDFF*@[@@@] 0)^@)@H@@@] 0)^@)^@)^@)^@)D-\AB
)@@G@@H9:I(0^[4GD+H->^[3HD'G(2^@!^[*GD3H[(H1$^[3I(+IL\I(4HD,G*)^@)@[@@@] 0)^@)AC
)@@G@@@M@@@] 0)^@)^@)^@)^@)CT[D-G^[CCDND@) [CC1PD1# ))EDPCDGAC?^[LE([D)2 ))C1DAD
)@@G@@D- AC?^[ADDGC*2 ))C-#D-PE-N ))DDIC- F@(^@)@[@@@] 0)^@)@I@@@] 0)^@)^@)^@)AE
)@@G@@^@)I9*G(2G*)^[CC1PD1#^@)B*)I9*HD<H@)H[-IT*HD,G8)G15H1<I-(H9,^[4H8)I(3G*)AF
)@@G@@@J@@@] 0)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^[LE([D)1^@)B*)G1(IL3I))IT(J@)GT*GD2GD<I->AG

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@#*.        MAINTSKEL REV 2.7  09/22/77     @[@@@#*.    HU

)@@G@@MBER> @[@@@#*.    @E@@@#*.        <SGS-NAME> AND <SGS-NUMBER> REFER TO AHW
)@@G@@ PARTICULAR @C@@@#*.        MAP, PROCESS, DESCRIBE, OR TOC SGS, OR@E@@@#HX
)@@G@@*.        A PARTICULAR PCF OR TCF ENTRY.  THIS PROCEDURE    @G@@@#*.    HY
)@@G@@    ESTABLISHES THE PROCESSOR AND NON-DEFAULT OPTIONS (IF ANY)    @F@@@#HZ
)@@G@@*.        FOR SOME ELEMENT AND PASSES THE INFORMATION TO MAKESGS. @E@@@#IA
)@@G@@*.        THIS ASSUMES THAT MAP SGSSES ARE PROCESSED FIRST. @G@@@#*.    IB
)@@G@@    OTHERWISE, ALL KINDS OF BAD THINGS WILL HAPPEN IN TERMS OF    @A@@@#IC
)@@G@@*.        PROCESSING TOO MANY MAPS. @[@@@#*.    @#@@@#*DEFINE QUEUE     ID
)@@G@@@]@@@#*CLEAR FOUND@C@@@#*INCREMENT I TO [DOLIST,1] WHILE FOUND IS CLEAR IE
)@@G@@@B@@@#*PROCESS DOSEARCH [#1] [#2] [DOLIST,1,I,1]@[@@@#*LOOP @#@@@#*IF FOIF
)@@G@@UND IS CLEAR@#@@@#*IF [#3] = MAP    @B@@@#*PROCESS MAKESGS [#1] [#2] MAPIG
)@@G@@ MAP [#4]   @[@@@#*ELSE @D@@@#*.        DIDN'T COME FROM MAP SGS. SEE IFIH
)@@G@@ DESCRIBE.  @B@@@#*IF [#3] = DESCRIBE OR [#3] = PROCESS     @B@@@#*IF [#II
)@@G@@3] = DESCRIBE OR [[#3],[#4]] > 1    @D@@@#*PROCESS MAKESGS [#1] [#2] [[#IJ
)@@G@@3],[#4],2,1] [#3] [#4]  @]@@@#*SET FOUND  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @#@@@#IK
)@@G@@*IF FOUND IS CLEAR@D@@@#*.        NOT FROM DESCRIBE. SEE IF IT HAS A DESIL
)@@G@@CRIBE.@D@@@#*INCREMENT DUMMY TO [DESCRIBE] WHILE FOUND IS CLEAR   @D@@@#IM
)@@G@@*IF COLUMN SEARCH FROM DESCRIBE,DUMMY,1,1 FOR [#1]    @ @@@#*IF [DESCRIBIN
)@@G@@E,CARD,1] > 1     @ @@@#*IF [DESCRIBE,CARD,1,2] = [#2]@#@@@#*SET FOUND TIO
)@@G@@O CARD@[@@@#*ELSE @#@@@#*SET DUMMY TO CARD@[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*ELSE @#@@@#IP
)@@G@@*IF [#2] = 'NO'   @#@@@#*SET FOUND TO CARD@[@@@#*ELSE @#@@@#*SET DUMMY TIQ
)@@G@@O CARD@[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*ELSE @#@@@#*SET FOUND TO -1  @[@@@#IR
)@@G@@*END  @[@@@#*LOOP @^@@@#*IF VALUE OF FOUND > 0  @F@@@#*PROCESS MAKESGS [IS
)@@G@@#1] [#2] [DESCRIBE,FOUND,2,1] DESCRIBE [*FOUND] @[@@@#*ELSE @A@@@#*.    IT
)@@G@@    NO DESCRIBE. TRY TOC.     @]@@@#*CLEAR FOUND@C@@@#*INCREMENT DUMMY TIU
)@@G@@O [TOC] WHILE FOUND IS CLEAR  @C@@@#*IF COLUMN SEARCH FROM TOC,DUMMY,1,1IV
)@@G@@ FOR [#1]   @^@@@#*IF [TOC,CARD,3,1] < +5 @ @@@#*IF [TOC,CARD,2,1] = [#2IW
)@@G@@]     @#@@@#*SET FOUND TO CARD@[@@@#*ELSE @B@@@#*IF [#2] = 'NO' AND [TOCIX
)@@G@@,CARD,2,1] = '''' @#@@@#*SET FOUND TO CARD@[@@@#*ELSE @#@@@#*SET DUMMY TIY
)@@G@@O CARD@[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*ELSE @#@@@#*SET DUMMY TO CARD@[@@@#IZ
)@@G@@*END  @[@@@#*ELSE @#@@@#*SET FOUND TO -1  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*LOOP @^@@@#JA
)@@G@@*IF VALUE OF FOUND > 0  @B@@@#*SET THING TO [TOC,FOUND,3,1]+TOCNO-2     JB
)@@G@@@A@@@#*IF VALUE OF THING < VALUE OF TOCNO @A@@@#*SET THING TO [TOC,FOUNDJC
)@@G@@,3,2]+TOCNO1@[@@@#*END  @D@@@#*PROCESS MAKESGS [#1] [#2] [PROCESSOR,THINJD
)@@G@@G,1,1] 0 0  @[@@@#*ELSE @E@@@#*.        WELL, IT'S NOT DESCRIBED ANYWHERJE
)@@G@@E. USE DEFAULT.   @C@@@#*PROCESS MAKESGS [#1] [#2] [LANGUAGE,1,1,1] 0 0 JF
)@@G@@@[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  JG
)@@G@@@[@@@#*EJECT@[@@@#*.    @C@@@#*.        DOSEARCH  <NAME> <VERSION> <DO-SJH
)@@G@@GS>   @[@@@#*.    @D@@@#*.        SEE IF ELEMENT ALREADY APPEARS IN A LIJI
)@@G@@ST.   @[@@@#*.    @#@@@#*DEFINE DOSEARCH  @]@@@#*CLEAR EXIT @C@@@#*INCREJJ
)@@G@@MENT DUMMY TO [[#3]] WHILE EXIT IS CLEAR  @C@@@#*IF COLUMN SEARCH FROM [JK
)@@G@@#3],DUMMY,1,1 FOR [#1]  @ @@@#*IF [[#3],CARD,1,2] = [#2]    @]@@@#*SET FJL
)@@G@@OUND  @]@@@#*SET EXIT   @[@@@#*ELSE @#@@@#*SET DUMMY TO CARD@[@@@#*END  JM
)@@G@@@[@@@#*ELSE @]@@@#*SET EXIT   @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*LOOP @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#JN
)@@G@@*EJECT@[@@@#*.    @G@@@#*.        MAKESGS <ELT> <VER> <SUBTYPE> [<SGS-TYJO
)@@G@@PE> <SGS-NUMBER> / 0 0] @[@@@#*.    @H@@@#*.        WHERE THE LAST TWO AJP
)@@G@@RGUMENTS TELL OF A MAP OR DESCRIBE OR LANGUAGE  @G@@@#*.        SGS GIVIJQ
)@@G@@NG OPTIONS AND NON-STANDARD OUTPUT NAME, PERHAPS.     @I@@@#*.        THJR
)@@G@@IS PROCEDURE CREATES THE DOFIRST, DOPROC, DOLANG, AND DOMAP SGSSES.     JS
)@@G@@@[@@@#*.    @#@@@#*DEFINE MAKESGS   @H@@@#*.        FIND PROPER PROCESSOJT
)@@G@@R SGS AND CORRESPONDING STANDARD PROCESSOR SGS. @C@@@#*IF COLUMN SEARCH JU
)@@G@@FROM PROCESSOR,1,1,1 FOR [#3] @#@@@#*SET INDEX TO CARD@[@@@#*ELSE @G@@@#JV

)@@G@@@^@@@#*SET INDEX TO +ELTNOF   @[@@@#*END  @F@@@#*IF [BACKREF,INDEX,1,1] JX
)@@G@@= +MAPNO AND NOT [#4] = MAP AND [MAP] > 0 @^@@@#*SET INDEX TO +ELTNOF   JY
)@@G@@@[@@@#*END  @A@@@#*SET INDEX2 TO [BACKREF,INDEX,1,1]  @^@@@#*IF VALUE OFJZ

)@@G@@*EJECT@[@@@#*.    @H@@@#*.        FSCAN TAKES ONE ARGUMENT, P OR T, REPRKU

)@@G@@NAME, IT CREATES A 'DOIT' SGS.@C@@@#*.        IT AVOIDS DUPLICATE DOIT EKW
)@@G@@NTRIES.     @[@@@#*.    @#@@@#*DEFINE FSCAN     @^@@@#*INCREMENT I TO [[KX

)@@G@@ME SGS SUCH AS SI TO CREATE ANOTHER.@[@@@#*.    @#@@@#*DEFINE COPYNAME  LD

)@@G@@NAME  @]@@@#*CLEAR EQUAL@E@@@#*IF [[#1],1,1,1] = [[#2],1,1,1] AND [[#1],LK

)@@G@@IED SGS.    @[@@@#*.    @#@@@#*DEFINE ELTNAME   @#@@@#[[#1],[#2],1,1]&  LV

)@@G@@@[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*EJECT@[@@@#*.    @B@@@#*.        MAPCOR    <DO-NAME> LX
)@@G@@<DO-NUMBER> @[@@@#*.    @F@@@#*.        IF PROCESSING A 'MAP' ELEMENT, 'LY
)@@G@@LEVEL' SGS MAY SPECIFY  @E@@@#*.        'EQU' DIRECTIVES TO BE INSERTED LZ
)@@G@@IN THE ELEMENT.   @[@@@#*.    @#@@@#*DEFINE MAPCOR    @A@@@#*IF [#1] = DMA

)@@G@@@G@@@#*IF [*CORE] = 2 AND [LEVEL,1,CORA,2] = [[#1],[#2],1,2] OR [*CORE] MF

)@@G@@@[@@@#*LOOP @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*LOOP @[@@@#*END  MI
)@@G@@@[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*EJECT@[@@@#*.    @ @@@#*.        GET     MJ
)@@G@@  <DO-NAME> @[@@@#*.    @G@@@#*.        FIND ALL SGSSES OF TYPE [#1] (DOMK
)@@G@@FIRST, DOPROC, DOLANG, DOMAP) @F@@@#*.        AND PUT OUT SUITABLE CONTRML
)@@G@@OL CARDS, DELETING THE SGS    @H@@@#*.        AFTERWARDS. IF THERE IS ANMM
)@@G@@ ALPHA SGS, PUT THINGS OUT ALPHABETICALLY.@[@@@#*.    @]@@@#*DEFINE GET MN

)@@G@@2] = 'NO'   @D@@@#*IF [[#1],I,1,2] = 'NO' OR [[#1],I,1,2] < [[#1],D,1,2]MS

)@@G@@= 0   @]@@@#*EDIT ON &  @B@@@#*IF NOT [PROCESSOR,[[#1],D,2,1],1,1] = DOCMV
)@@G@@@[@@@#*.    @C@@@#*.        EDIT A HEADING FOR NON-DOC ELEMENTS   @[@@@#MW
)@@G@@*.    @[@@@##HDG& @#@@@#*IF [HEADING]     @ @@@#*IF NOT [HEADING,1,1,1] MX
)@@G@@= 'NO'@^@@@#,[HEADING,1,1,1]   &    @[@@@#*ELSE @[@@@#     &@[@@@#*END  MY

)@@G@@SS MAPCOR [#1] [*D]     @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*ELSE @^@@@#*IF [AQI
)@@G@@PPLY,1,1,1] = TCF @^@@@#*IF [[#1],D,1,2] = 'NO' @ @@@#*CORRECT [[#1],D,1QJ
)@@G@@,1] TEMP    @ @@@#*PROCESS MAPCOR [#1] [*D]     @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*ELSE QK
)@@G@@@B@@@#*CORRECT [[#1],D,1,1]/[[#1],D,1,2] TEMP   @ @@@#*PROCESS MAPCOR [#QL
)@@G@@1] [*D]     @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  QM
)@@G@@@[@@@#*END  @^@@@#*REMOVE SGS [#1],[*D]   @]@@@#*LOOP DUMMY @[@@@#*END  QN
)@@G@@@[@@@#*EJECT@[@@@#*.    @ @@@#*.        OPTIONS <STRING>    @[@@@#*.    QO
)@@G@@@F@@@#*.        ADDS SPECIFIED OPTIONS TO CONTROL STATEMENT.  PROVIDES  QP
)@@G@@@ @@@#*.        COMMA IF NEEDED.    @[@@@#*.    @#@@@#*DEFINE OPTIONS   QQ
)@@G@@@^@@@#*IF NOT [#1] = 'NO'     @#@@@#*IF COMMA IS CLEAR@[@@@#,&    @]@@@#QR
)@@G@@*SET COMMA  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#[#1]& @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*.    QS
)@@G@@@[@@@#*.    @B@@@#*.        USEROPTS <SGSNAME> <SGS-NUMBER> @[@@@#*.    QT
)@@G@@@G@@@#*.        ADDS OPTIONS GIVEN ON SPECIFIED MAP, PROCESS, OR DESCRIBQU
)@@G@@E SGS.@[@@@#*.    @#@@@#*DEFINE USEROPTS  @^@@@#*IF [[#1],[#2],2] > 1   QV
)@@G@@@A@@@#*PROCESS OPTIONS [[#1],[#2],2,2]    @]@@@#*SET GOTOPTS@[@@@#*END  QW
)@@G@@@[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*EJECT@[@@@#*.    @B@@@#*.        LOOKFOR <P OR T> <SGQX
)@@G@@S-TYPE>     @[@@@#*.    @G@@@#*.        RETURNS WITH GOTCF SET IFF THE CQY
)@@G@@URRENT ELEMENT [[#2],D,...]   @C@@@#*.        APPEARS IN THE NAMED CHANGQZ
)@@G@@E FILE.     @[@@@#*.    @#@@@#*DEFINE LOOKFOR   @]@@@#*CLEAR GOTCF@C@@@#RA
)@@G@@*INCREMENT I TO [[#1]] WHILE GOTCF IS CLEAR     @D@@@#*IF COLUMN SEARCH RB
)@@G@@FROM [#1],1,1,1 FOR [[#2],D,1,1]    @^@@@#*IF [[#1],CARD] = 1     @^@@@#RC
)@@G@@*IF [[#2],D,1,2] = 'NO' @#@@@#*SET GOTCF TO CARD@[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*ELSE RD
)@@G@@@A@@@#*IF [[#1],CARD,2,1] = [[#2],D,1,2]  @#@@@#*SET GOTCF TO CARD@[@@@#RE
)@@G@@*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*ELSE @#@@@#*SET GOTCF TO -1  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#RF
)@@G@@*LOOP @^@@@#*IF VALUE OF GOTCF < 0  @]@@@#*CLEAR GOTCF@[@@@#*END  @[@@@#RG
)@@G@@*END  @[@@@#*EJECT@[@@@#*.    @I@@@#*.        SPECS     <DOIT-NUMBER> <PRH
)@@G@@ROCESSOR-NUMBER> <DESCRIBE OR MAP OR 0> <SGS    @[@@@#*.    @D@@@#*.    RI
)@@G@@    EDIT OUT THE SPEC FIELDS ON PROCESSOR CARD. @[@@@#*.    @#@@@#*DEFINRJ
)@@G@@E SPECS     @]@@@#*CLEAR COMMA@B@@@#*INCREMENT I FROM 2 TO [PROCESSOR,[#RK
)@@G@@2],2] @]@@@#*SET RPTNAM @ @@@#*IF [PROCESSOR,[#2],2,I] = SO @^@@@#*SET RRL
)@@G@@PTNAM TO OKSO     @[@@@#*ELSE @ @@@#*IF [PROCESSOR,[#2],2,I] = PO @^@@@#RM
)@@G@@*SET RPTNAM TO 1-UOPT   @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @#@@@#*IF RPTNAM IS SET RN
)@@G@@@^@@@#*INCREMENT I TO COMMA   @[@@@#,&    @[@@@#*LOOP @]@@@#*CLEAR COMMARO
)@@G@@@B@@@#*PROCESS FILENAME [PROCESSOR,[#2],2,I]    @[@@@#.&    @A@@@#*IF VARP
)@@G@@LUE OF I = 3 AND NOT [#3] = 0 @ @@@#*SET SPECT TO [[#4],[#1],3,2] @^@@@#RQ
)@@G@@*IF [[#3],SPECT] > 2    @#@@@#*CLEAR RPTNAM     @#@@@#[[#3],SPECT,3,1]& RR
)@@G@@@^@@@#*IF [[#3],SPECT,3] > 1  @#@@@#/[[#3],SPECT,3,2]&@[@@@#*END  @[@@@#RS
)@@G@@*END  @[@@@#*END  @#@@@#*IF RPTNAM IS SET @ @@@#*PROCESS ELTNAME [#4] [#RT
)@@G@@1]    @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @^@@@#*SET COMMA TO COMMA+1   @[@@@#*LOOP RU
)@@G@@@[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*EJECT@[@@@#*.    @^@@@#*.        INITIALIZATION@[@@@#RV
)@@G@@*.    @C@@@#*CREATE SGS: DOLIST DOFIRST DOLANG DOPROC DOMAP @[@@@#*.    RW
)@@G@@@E@@@#*. THE 'NUMS' SGSSES ARE USED TO CREATE VARIABLES WHICH TELL@E@@@#RX
)@@G@@*. MAINTSKEL WHERE CERTAIN STANDARD PROCESSOR SUBTYPES ARE  @]@@@#*. LOCRY
)@@G@@ATED  @[@@@#*.    @ @@@#*CREATE SGS: NUMS  PDP,PDPNO  @ @@@#*CREATE SGS:RZ
)@@G@@ NUMS  ASMP,ASMPNO@ @@@#*CREATE SGS: NUMS  COBP,COBPNO@ @@@#*CREATE SGS:SA

)@@G@@ECT TOC' AND OTHER FEATURES TO@^@@@#*. OPERATE CORRECTLY.   @[@@@#*.    SF

)@@G@@ELECT] = 0  @ @@@#*CREATE SGS: SELECT EITHER    @[@@@#*END  @B@@@#*IF [STS

)@@G@@@[@@@#*ELSE @D@@@##MSG,N INTERNAL ERROR - PROCESSOR ELT SGS NOT FOUND   UN

)@@G@@MENTS AS NECESSARY.     @]@@@#*CLEAR EQUAL@^@@@#*PROCESS COMPNAME RI RO VB

)@@G@@L &   @]@@@B#ELT,I&     @A@@@B*IF [LIST] AND [LIST,1,1,1] = NONE  @[@@@BVQ

)@@G@@1,1,1] = DESCRIBE @ @@@#*INCREMENT DESNO TO [DESCRIBE]@ @@@#*IF [DESCRIBWG

)@@G@@@^@@@#*IF [SELECT,1,1,1] = TOC@ @@@#*INCREMENT TOCNO TO [TOC]     @^@@@#WK
)@@G@@*IF [TOC,TOCNO,3,1] < 5 @ @@@#*IF [TOC,TOCNO,2,1] = '' ''   @C@@@#*PROCEWL

)@@G@@UE [TOC,TOCNO,1,1] [TOC,TOCNO,2,1] TOC [*TOCNO] @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  WN
)@@G@@@[@@@#*LOOP @[@@@#*END  @ @@@#*IF [SELECT,1,1,1] = BOTH     @^@@@#*INCREWO
)@@G@@MENT PNO TO [P]   @]@@@#*CLEAR FOUND@B@@@#*INCREMENT TNO TO [T] WHILE FOWP
)@@G@@UND IS CLEAR@C@@@#*IF COLUMN SEARCH FROM T,TNO,1,1 FOR [P,PNO,1,1]@ @@@#WQ
)@@G@@*IF NOT [T,CARD] = [P,PNO]    @#@@@#*SET TNO TO CARD  @[@@@#*ELSE @#@@@#WR
)@@G@@*IF [T,CARD] = 1  @#@@@#*SET FOUND TO CARD@[@@@#*ELSE @ @@@#*IF [T,CARD,WS
)@@G@@2,1] = [P,PNO,2,1]@#@@@#*SET FOUND TO CARD@[@@@#*ELSE @#@@@#*SET TNO TO WT
)@@G@@CARD  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*ELSE @#@@@#*SET FOUND TWU
)@@G@@O -1  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*LOOP @^@@@#*IF VALUE OF FOUND > 0  @#@@@#*IF [PWV
)@@G@@,PNO] > 1   @C@@@#*PROCESS QUEUE [P,PNO,1,1] [P,PNO,2,1] P [*PNO] @[@@@#WW
)@@G@@*ELSE @B@@@#*PROCESS QUEUE [P,PNO,1,1] 'NO' P [*PNO]  @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#WX
)@@G@@*END  @[@@@#*LOOP @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*.    @ @@@#*.        END OF SELECT WY
)@@G@@! !   @[@@@#*.    @[@@@#*.    @[@@@#*EJECT@[@@@#*.    @ @@@#*.        BEWZ
)@@G@@GIN PASS 1: PROCS.@[@@@#*.    @^@@@#*PROCESS GET DOFIRST    @^@@@#*PROCEXA
)@@G@@SS GET DOPROC     @^@@@#*PROCESS GET DOLANG     @A@@@#*IF [MERGE] = 0 ANXB
)@@G@@D [DOMAP] > 0     @]@@@#*EDIT ON &  @]@@@##PREP &     @^@@@#*PROCESS FILXC
)@@G@@ENAME RO    @[@@@#.     @[@@@#*END  @#@@@#*PROCESS GET DOMAP@F@@@#*IF [DXD
)@@G@@OPROC] > 0 OR [DOLANG] > 0 OR [DOMAP] > 0 OR [DOFIRST] > 0  @E@@@##MSG,NXE
)@@G@@ INTERNAL ERROR:[DOPROC] DOPROCS, [DOLANG] DOLANG, ;  @B@@@#   [DOMAP] DXF
)@@G@@OMAPS, [DOFIRST] DOFIRSTS     @[@@@#*END  @[@@@#*.    @E@@@#*.        GEXG

)@@G@@      @A@@@#.         F I L E   M O D I F I E R @[@@@#.     @D@@@#.     XE
)@@G@@    FEBRUARY 1973                  JOHN WALKER  @[@@@#.     @#@@@#      XF
)@@G@@    AXR$    @#@@@#          DEFUNCT$@^@@@#          LIT$      2   @[@@@#XG
)@@G@@$(1). @[@@@#.     @F@@@#BEGIN     LA        A0,(56,INFOR)       GET INFOXH
)@@G@@R BUFFER ADDRESS  @E@@@#          LMJ       X11,RINF$           READ IN XI
)@@G@@INFOR TABLE @G@@@#          J         CALLER              CALL ERROR.  NXJ
)@@G@@O INFOR TABLE     @F@@@#          LA,U      A0,1                GET FIRSXK
)@@G@@T SPECIFICATION   @G@@@#          LMJ       X11,SELT$           BUILD TAXL
)@@G@@BLE FROM SPECIFICATIONS @G@@@#          J         CALLER              NOXM
)@@G@@ FIRST SPECIFICATION.  ERROR  @E@@@#          DL        A0,(LJSF$2 'USE$XN
)@@G@@NAME') GET FILE NAME    @E@@@#          LMJ       X11,DUSE$           ATXO
)@@G@@TACH A USE NAME   @E@@@#          CSF$      ASGIT               ASSIGN TXP
)@@G@@HE FILE     @E@@@#          DSL       A13,72              CLEAR CHANGE FXQ
)@@G@@LAGS  @F@@@^          MSCON$    DREADP              GET MAIN ITEM FOF FIXR
)@@G@@LE    @E@@@^          TP        A0                  NORMAL STATUS ?     XS
)@@G@@@E@@@^          LMJ       X6,MSCERR           NO.  EDIT STATUS    @F@@@^XT
)@@G@@          LA        A0,MI+19            LOAD CATALOGUING TIME     @F@ @^XU
)@@G@@          TDATE$    .                   ************ FUDGE **     @E@@@^XV
)@@G@@          SA        A0,DREGP+8          SET IN DREG$ PACKET @F@@@^      XW
)@@G@@    F$MSG     FINFO               EDIT FILE INFO MESSAGE    @D@@@^      XX
)@@G@@    F$FD2     MI+7                EDIT ACCOUNT  @E@@@^          F$MSGR  XY
)@@G@@  .                   COPY MODE TITLE     @D@@@^          F$FD2     MI+5XZ
)@@G@@                EDIT PROJECT  @C@@@^          F$PRT     1               YA
)@@G@@    PRINT IT@E@@@^          LA        A1,MI+12            LOAD DESCRIPTOYB
)@@G@@R BITS@F@@@^          LA,U      A0,FIBU             LOAD BACKED UP MESSAYC
)@@G@@GE    @E@ @^          TOP       A0,(BIT(34))        SEE IF BACKUP EXISTSYD
)@@G@@@E@@@           TOP       A1,(BIT(34))        SEE IF BACKUP EXISTS@E@@@^YE
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,FINBU            NO.  EDIT NO BACKUP @D@@@^      YF
)@@G@@    F$MSG     .                   COPY THE TEXT @C@@@^          F$PRT   YG
)@@G@@  1                   PRINT IT@F@@@#          LX,U      X5,CHGACT       YH
)@@G@@    ASK ABOUT ACCOUNT NUMBER  @D@@@#          LMJ       X6,ASK          YI
)@@G@@    ASK THE USER  @E@@@#          JZ        A15,NOACTC          NO ACCOUYJ
)@@G@@NT CHANGE   @E@@@#          DL        A0,ANSWER           LOAD THE ANSWEYK
)@@G@@R     @G@@@#          DS        A0,DREGP+5          PUT NEW ACCOUNT IN DYL
)@@G@@REG$ PACKET @E@@@#          LA,U      A14,1               SET FLAG TO DOYM
)@@G@@ DREG$@F@@@#NOACTC    LX,U      X5,CHGPRJ           ASK ABOUT PROJECT NOYN
)@@G@@W     @G@@@#          LMJ       X6,ASK              PUT THE QUESTION TO YO
)@@G@@THE USER    @E@@@#          JZ        A15,NOPROC          NO.  DON'T CHAYP
)@@G@@NGE IT@E@@@#          DL        A0,ANSWER           LOAD NEW PROJECT    YQ
)@@G@@@E@@@#          DS        A0,DREGP+3          PUT IN DREG$ PACKET @E@@@#YR
)@@G@@          LA,U      A14,1               SET DREG$ NECESSARY @G@@@#NOPROCYS
)@@G@@    LX,U      X5,CHGBAK           ASK ABOUT BACKUP OF THIS FILE   @E@@@#YT
)@@G@@          LMJ       X6,ASK              PUT THE QUESTION    @E@@@#      YU
)@@G@@    JZ        A15,NOPROC          ASK AGAIN IF NULL   @G@@@#          LAYV
)@@G@@,S1     A0,ANSWER           GET FIRST CHARACTER OF REPLY    @D@@@#      YW
)@@G@@    TNE,U     A0,'N'              IS IT 'NO' ?  @E@@@#          J       YX
)@@G@@  NOBAK               RIGHT.  DON'T UNBACK@E@@@#          TE,U      A0,'YY
)@@G@@Y'              ...THEN MUST BE YES @E@@@#          J         NOPROC    YZ
)@@G@@          WRONG.  TRY AGAIN   @F@@@#          LA,U      A13,1           ZA
)@@G@@    MARK DBACK$ NECESSARY     @]@@@#NOBAK     . @]@@@#.           @B@@@#ZB
)@@G@@.         SUMMARISE CHANGES REQUESTED     @[@@@#.     @F@@@#          TNZC
)@@G@@Z       DREGP+5             ACCOUNT CHANGE NECESSARY ?@E@@@#          J ZD
)@@G@@        NOACX               NO.  DON'T EDIT     @G@@@#          F$MSG   ZE
)@@G@@  ACCTCH              EDIT ACCOUNT CHANGE MESSAGE     @E@@@#          F$ZF
)@@G@@FD2     DREGP+5             EDIT NEW ACCOUNT    @C@@@#          F$PRT   ZG
)@@G@@  1                   PRINT IT@D@@@#NOACX     TNZ       DREGP+3         ZH
)@@G@@    NEW PROJECT ? @E@@@#          J         NOPRX               NO.  SKIZI
)@@G@@P THIS STUFF@E@@@#          F$MSG     PROJCH              COPY THE MESSAZJ
)@@G@@GE    @E@@@#          F$FD2     DREGP+3             EDIT THE NEW PROJECTZK
)@@G@@@D@@@#          F$PRT     1                   PRINT THE LINE@E@@@#NOPRX ZL
)@@G@@    JZ        A13,NOBKX           CHANGE BACKUP ?     @F@@@#          F$ZM
)@@G@@MSG     BACKCH              COPY BACKUP CHANGE MESSAGE@C@@@#          F$ZN
)@@G@@PRT     1                   PRINT IT@]@@@#NOBKX     . @[@@@#.     @B@@@#ZO
)@@G@@.         ASK USER IF HE REALLY MEANS IT  @[@@@#.     @F@@@#SUREQ     LXZP
)@@G@@,U      X5,SURE             LOAD FINAL QUESTION TEXT  @D@@@#          LMZQ
)@@G@@J       X6,ASK              ASK ABOUT IT  @F@@@#          JZ        A15,ZR
)@@G@@SUREQ           ASK AGAIN IF NULL REPLY   @G@@@#          LA,S1     A0,AZS
)@@G@@NSWER           LOAD THE FIRST ANSWER CHARACTER @C@@@#          TNE,U   ZT
)@@G@@  A0,'N'              NO ?    @F@@@#          J         UNDO            ZU
)@@G@@    UNDO THE ASSIGNMENT, EXIT @E@@@#          TE,U      A0,'Y'          ZV
)@@G@@    ...OR IS IT 'YES'   @D@@@#          J         SUREQ               NOZW
)@@G@@.  ASK AGAIN@D@@@#          JZ        A14,CHKDBK          DREG$ NEEDED ?ZX
)@@G@@@E@@@#          MSCON$    DREGP               SUBMIT THE REQUEST  @E@@@#ZY
)@@G@@          TP        A0                  NORMAL COMPLETION ? @E@@@#      ZZ
)@@G@@    LMJ       X6,MSCERR           NO.  MSCON$ ERROR   @D@@@#CHKDBK    JZAA
)@@G@@        A13,NOXBK           ERASE BACKUP ?@D@@@#          MSCON$    DBKPAB
)@@G@@KT              YES.  ZAP IT  @E@@@#          TP        A0              AC
)@@G@@    NORMAL STATUS ?     @E@@@#          LMJ       X6,MSCERR           NOAD
)@@G@@.  EDIT MESSAGE   @]@@@#NOXBK     . @D@@@#          CSF$      FREEIT    AE
)@@G@@          FREE THE FILE @F@@@#          F$MSG     CHANGED             EDAF
)@@G@@IT FILE CHANGED MESSAGE @C@@@#          F$PRT     1                   PRAG
)@@G@@INT IT@D@@@BTERM0     F$DT      .                   CLEAR THE LINE@E@B@#AH
)@@G@@TERM0     F$MSG     ENDIT               EDIT TERMINATION    @E@@@B      AI
)@@G@@    F$MSG     ENDIT               EDIT TERMINATION    @C@@@#          F$AJ
)@@G@@PRT     1                   PRINT IT@G@@@#          EXIT$     .         AK
)@@G@@          RETURN CONTROL TO THE SYSTEM    @[@@@#.     @D@@@#UNDO      CSAL
)@@G@@F$      FREEIT              FREE THE FILE @E@@@#          F$MSG     NCHAAM
)@@G@@NGED            EDIT NOT CHANGED    @E@@@#          F$PRT     1         AN
)@@G@@          PRINT NOT CHANGED   @E@@@#          J         TERM0           AO
)@@G@@    EXIT THE PROCESSOR  @[@@@#.     @E@@@#CALLER    F$MSG     CALLEM    AP
)@@G@@          EDIT CALL ERROR     @C@@@#          F$PRT     1               AQ
)@@G@@    PRINT IT@C@@@#          J         TERM0               GET OUT @[@@@#AR
)@@G@@.     @E@@@#MSCERR    LA        A5,A0               SAVE ERROR STATUS   AS
)@@G@@@F@@@#          LSSL      A5,12               SHIFT OFF HIGH-ORDER STUFFAT
)@@G@@@F@@@#          SSL       A5,18+12            RIGHT JUSTIFY ERROR CODE  AU
)@@G@@@E@@@#          F$MSG     MSCEM               EDIT ERROR MESSAGE  @E@@@#AV
)@@G@@          F$OCTV    A5                  EDIT ERROR CODE     @D@@@#      AW
)@@G@@    F$MSGR    .                   COPY THE REST @E@@@#          F$PRT   AX
)@@G@@  1                   PRINT ERROR MESSAGE @C@@@#          J         0,X6AY
)@@G@@                RETURN  @[@@@#.     @E@@@#ASK       F$MSG     0,X5      AZ
)@@G@@          EDIT QUESTION TEXT  @D@@@#          F$CHAR    077             BA
)@@G@@    TERMINATE LINE@D@@@#          DL        A0,('            ') GET SPACBB
)@@G@@ES    @D@@@#          DS        A0,ANSWER           CLEAR ANSWER  @F@@@#BC
)@@G@@          TREAD$P   TRDPKT              PUT THE QUESTION TO USER  @E@@@#BD
)@@G@@          LA,U      A15,,A0             SAVE LENGTH OF REPLY@D@@@#      BE
)@@G@@    F$DT      .                   CLEAR THE LINE@C@@@#          J       BF
)@@G@@  0,X6                RETURN  @[@@@#.     @[@@@#$(2). @A@@@#ASGIT     '@BG
)@@G@@ASG,AQYZ USE$NAME . '   @ @@@#FREEIT    '@FREE USE$NAME . ' @A@@@^FINFO BH
)@@G@@    'ACCOUNT: &  PROJECT: &'  @B@@@^FIBU      'BACKUP EXISTS FOR THIS FIBI
)@@G@@LE.&' @D@@@^FINBU     'BACKUP DOES NOT EXIST FOR THIS FILE.&'     @C@@@#BJ
)@@G@@CHGACT    'ENTER NEW ACCOUNT NUMBER OR <CR> &'  @B@@@#CHGPRJ    'ENTER NBK
)@@G@@EW PROJECT OR <CR> &'   @F@@@#CHGBAK    'DUMP THIS FILE ON NEXT SECURE RBL
)@@G@@UN?  (YES OR NO) &'     @A@@@#ACCTCH    'NEW ACCOUNT WILL BE: &'  @A@@@#BM
)@@G@@PROJCH    'NEW PROJECT WILL BE: &'  @D@@@#BACKCH    'FILE WILL BE DUMPEDBN
)@@G@@ BY NEXT SECURE RUN.&'  @G@@@#SURE      'ARE ABOVE PARAMETERS WHAT YOU HBO
)@@G@@AD IN MIND ?  (YES OR NO) &'  @C@@@#MSCEM     'ERROR STATUS CODE & FROM BP
)@@G@@MSCON$.&'   @B@@@#CALLEM    'PROCESSOR CALLED INCORRECTLY.&'@ @@@#CHANGEBQ
)@@G@@D   'FILE CHANGED.&'    @ @@@#NCHANGED  'FILE NOT CHANGED.&'@^@@@#ENDIT BR
)@@G@@    'END MODIFY.&'@[@@@#.     @ @@@^DREADP    *         DREAD$    @^@@@^BS
)@@G@@          'USE$NAME'    @ @@@^          *         030001,MI @^@@@^      BT
)@@G@@    *         0   @ @@@#DREGP     *         DREG$     @^@@@#          'UBU
)@@G@@SE$NAME'    @ @@@#          DO        7 , * 0   @ @@@#DBKPKT    *       BV
)@@G@@  DBACK$    @^@@@#          'USE$NAME'    @^@@@#          DO 6 , * 0    BW
)@@G@@@C@@@#TRDPKT    *         0126,FL$            TYPEOUT @C@@@#          * BX
)@@G@@        TERM0,ANSWER        REPLY   @^@@@#INFOR     RES       56  @E@@@^BY
)@@G@@MI        RES       0300                MAIN ITEM BUFFER    @E@@@#ANSWERBZ
)@@G@@    RES       14                  REPLY FROM TREAD$   @ @@@#          ENCA

)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@ @@@@1  REM ****GAME OF MOO****    DN
)@@G@@@[@@@@2  REM@A@@@@3  REM REQUISITIONED FROM DECUS     @[@@@@4  REM@A@@@@DO
)@@G@@5 PRINT 'DO YOU NEED INSTRUCTIONS'; @]@@@@6 INPUT A$  @ @@@@7 IF A$='NO'DP
)@@G@@ OR A$='N' THEN 20@]@@@@8 PRINT     @E@@@@9 PRINT 'I PICK A FOUR-DIGIT NDQ
)@@G@@UMBER.  NO DIGIT WILL APPEAR' @E@@@@10 PRINT 'MORE THAN ONCE.  YOU GUESSDR
)@@G@@ MY NUMBER BY TYPING IN'@F@@@@12 PRINT 'FOUR-DIGIT TEST NUMBERS.  IF ONEDS
)@@G@@ OF YOUR DIGITS IS'     @F@@@@13 PRINT 'IN MY NUMBER, IT IS EITHER A BULDT
)@@G@@L OR A COW (B OR C).'   @E@@@@14 PRINT 'IF THE DIGIT IS IN THE CORRECT PDU
)@@G@@OSITION, IT''S A' @F@@@@15 PRINT 'BULL...IF IT IS IN MY NUMBER BUT NOT IDV
)@@G@@N THE CORRECT'    @D@@@@16 PRINT 'POSITION, IT''S A COW.  FOUR BULLS WINDW
)@@G@@S.'   @A@@@@20  REM ****PROGRAM INITIALIZATION  @]@@@@70  DIM N(9)@#@@@@DX
)@@G@@80  RANDOMIZE     @]@@@@90  LET G=0 @]@@@@91  LET A=0 @^@@@@92  FOR I=0 DY
)@@G@@TO 9 N(I)=I @B@@@@99  REM ****BEGIN NEW GAME - SET UP N     @]@@@@100 LEDZ
)@@G@@T T=0 @#@@@@115 FOR I=0 TO 3  @#@@@@120 LET K=RND(0)  @^@@@@121 LET K = EA
)@@G@@K * (10-I)  @^@@@@122 LET K = INT (I+K)   @#@@@@125 LET X=N(I)    @#@@@@EB
)@@G@@130 LET N(I)=N(K) @#@@@@135 LET N(K)=X    @]@@@@140 NEXT I  @ @@@@149 REEC
)@@G@@M ****READ PLAYERS GUESS@]@@@@150 PRINT   @ @@@@151 PRINT '4-DIGIT NUMBEED
)@@G@@R';   @]@@@@152 INPUT R$@ @@@@153 IF LEN(R$)<>4 THEN 810    @#@@@@154 CHEE
)@@G@@ANGE R$ TO R@A@@@@155 FOR I=1 TO 4 R(I-1)=R(I)-48     @B@@@@156 REM ***BEF
)@@G@@RANCH IF HE WANTS TO QUIT     @ @@@@157 IF R(0) = -1 GOTO 900     @B@@@@EG
)@@G@@159 REM BRANCH TO 800 IF IMPROPER INPUT   @#@@@@160 FOR I=0 TO 3  @^@@@@EH
)@@G@@163 IF R(I) < 0 GOTO 800@^@@@@165 IF R(I) >9 GOTO 800 @A@@@@167 IF R(I) EI
)@@G@@<> INT(R(I)) GOTO 800   @]@@@@170 NEXT I  @#@@@@171 PRINT '--';   @C@@@@EJ
)@@G@@171 REM ****ALL INPUT OK STEP COUNT OF TRIES    @#@@@@173 LET T=T+1     EK
)@@G@@@A@@@@174 REM****CALCUATE BULLS AND COWS  @]@@@@175 LET B=0 @]@@@@177 LEEL
)@@G@@T C=0 @#@@@@180 FOR I=0 TO 3  @#@@@@182 FOR J=0 TO 3  @ @@@@185 IF R(I) EM
)@@G@@= N(J) GOTO 200   @]@@@@187 NEXT J  @]@@@@190 GOTO 270@^@@@@200 IF I=J GEN
)@@G@@OTO 250     @#@@@@210 LET C =C+1    @]@@@@220 GOTO 270@#@@@@250 LET B=B+EO
)@@G@@1     @]@@@@270 NEXT I  @A@@@@275 REM ****PRINT OUT BULLS AND COWS@ @@@@EP
)@@G@@280 FOR I=1 TO B PRINT 'B';   @#@@@@310 PRINT ',';    @ @@@@320 FOR I=1 EQ
)@@G@@TO C PRINT 'C';   @B@@@@345 REM ****UNLESS HE GOT 4 BULLS GO AGAIN@^@@@@ER
)@@G@@350 IF B < 4 GOTO 150   @A@@@@355  REM *** PRINT INFO AND GO AGAIN@#@@@@ES
)@@G@@360 LET G=G+1     @#@@@@370 LET A=A+T     @]@@@@375 PRINT   @D@@@@380 PRET
)@@G@@INT 'GAME';G;': TRIES =';T;', AVERAGE =';A/G    @]@@@@390 PRINT   @]@@@@EU
)@@G@@400 GOTO 100@^@@@@790 REM ***ILLEGAL INPUT@]@@@@800 PRINT   @F@@@@802 PREV
)@@G@@INT 'NUMBER SHOULD BE INTEGER IN THE RANGE 0000 TO 9999'    @]@@@@804 GOEW
)@@G@@TO 150@]@@@@810 PRINT   @B@@@@812 PRINT 'MUST BE EXACTLY FOUR DIGITS'   EX
)@@G@@@]@@@@814 GOTO 150@^@@@@890 REM ***EXIT GAME    @^@@@@900 IF T=0 GOTO 99EY
)@@G@@9     @]@@@@905 PRINT   @E@@@@910 PRINT 'IT IS ANTISOCIAL TO TRY TO QUITEZ
)@@G@@ IN THE MIDDLE'   @C@@@@920 PRINT'OF A GAME OF MOO. PLEASE CONTINUE.'   FA
)@@G@@@]@@@@940 GOTO 150@]@@@@999 END     ___ 20@]@@@@8 PRINT     @E@@@@9 PRINFB
)@@G@@T 'I PICK A FOUR-DIGIT NUMBER.  NO DIGIT WILL APPEAR' @E@@@@10 PRINT 'MOFC
)@@G@@RE THAN ONCE.  YOU GUESS*[@@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @D@@@@.        M O R S EFD
)@@G@@  /  S Y N T H E S I Z E R   E X E C@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                 FE
)@@G@@                     OCTOBER 1971 BY JOHN WALKER@[@@@@.     @H@@@@.     FF
)@@G@@             YOU BOOT THE TAPE THIS THING WRITES INTO ANY MODULE THROUGHFG
)@@G@@@H@@@@.        ANY CHANNEL OR IOC PATH OF ANY PROCESSOR.  BEFORE PUSHINGFH
)@@G@@ START, PUSH@H@@@@.        THE  'AUDIO'  BUTTON ON THE MAINTENANCE PANELFI
)@@G@@ (IT'S RIGHT BENEATH THE@H@@@@.        PHASE  LIGHTS, AND TO THE LEFT OFFJ
)@@G@@ 'INITIAL LOAD'.)  AFTER STARTING UP@H@@@@.        THE  PROCESSOR, BEHOLFK
)@@G@@D THE MARVELOUS SOUND THAT ISSUES FROM THE ALARM@C@@@@.        SPEAKER OFL
)@@G@@N THE OPERATOR'S CONSOLE.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                  AFTERFM
)@@G@@  YOU  TIRE OF THAT,  TRY TYPING ON THE CONSOLE.  YOUR@H@@@@.        INPFN
)@@G@@UT WILL BE SENT BACK TO YOU IN MORSE CODE.  THE SPEED OF THE MORSE@H@@@@FO
)@@G@@.        CODE  IS  SET BY THE BINARY VALUE IN THE JUMP KEYS 1-10 (1 IS TFP
)@@G@@HE LOW@H@@@@.        ORDER BIT).  THE JUMP KEYS ARE READ WHENEVER THE REFQ
)@@G@@TURN KEY IS HIT.  @H@@@@.        YOU MAY GET AS FAR AHEAD OF THE OUTPUT FR
)@@G@@AS YOU LIKE.  SETTING JUMP KEY@H@@@@.        15 WILL CAUSE INPUT TO BE QFS
)@@G@@UEUED, AND TO BE SENT AFTER JUMP KEY 15 IS@H@@@@.        TURNED OFF.   IFT
)@@G@@F YOU TYPE NOTHING FOR 10 SECONDS AFTER OUTPUT CEASES,@H@@@@.        THEFU
)@@G@@  SYNTHESIZER  WILL  START  AGAIN.   TYPING A HAPPY-PUNCH (") WILL@G@@@@FV
)@@G@@.        IMMEDIATELY ABORT THE MORSE CODE AND START THE SYNTHESIZER.    FW
)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @#@@@@         AXR$     @^@@@@R0       EQU       0100 @[@@@@FX
)@@G@@.     @A@@@@.        'HOW IT SOUNDS' CONSTANTS  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@RATE  FY
)@@G@@   EQU       ;                   HOW FAST TO SHIFT SYNTHESIZER REGISTER FZ
)@@G@@@ @@@@                   100000     @H@@@@BSLENG   EQU       ;          GA
)@@G@@         BASIC TIME INTERVAL FOR MORSE CODE     @^@@@@                  GB
)@@G@@ 3    @G@@@@SYNPTC   EQU       ;                   SYNTHESIZER BASIC HIGGC
)@@G@@H NOTE PITCH@^@@@@                   250  @E@@@@MPITCH   EQU       ;    GD
)@@G@@               COUNT FOR MORSE PITCH@^@@@@                   1000 @[@@@@GE
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@.        REGISTER DEFINITIONS @[@@@@.     @E@@@@XR       EQUGF
)@@G@@       0140                EXEC REGISTERS BIAS  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.     GG
)@@G@@   .         X2                  *INTERRUPT REGISTER* @E@@@@.        .  GH
)@@G@@       X3                  *INTERRUPT REGISTER* @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.     GI
)@@G@@   .         A6                  *INTERRUPT REGISTER* @F@@@@SIX      EQUGJ
)@@G@@       A7                  1 IF RUNNING ON AN 1106    @G@@@@LENGTH   EQUGK
)@@G@@       A8                  LENGTH OF BASIC MORSE INTERVAL   @G@@@@.     GL
)@@G@@   .         A9                  TIMEOUT COUNTER FOR MORSE MODE   @H@@@@GM
)@@G@@BITS     EQU       A10                 FEEDBACK SHIFT REGISTER BITS REGIGN
)@@G@@STER  @G@@@@PITCH    EQU       A11                 PITCH COUNT FOR TONE GO
)@@G@@SUBROUTINE  @G@@@@.        .         A12                 CONSOLE ACCESS GP
)@@G@@WORD (ABSOLUTE)   @I@@@@.        .         A13                 ONE FOR MGQ
)@@G@@ORSE MODE, ZERO FOR SYNTHESIZER     @E@@@@.        .         A14        GR
)@@G@@         GUARD MODE OFF PSR   @E@@@@.        .         A15              GS
)@@G@@   GUARD MODE ON PSR    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@CIP      EQU       R5         GT
)@@G@@         CONSOLE LOAD POINTER @F@@@@CDP      EQU       R6               GU
)@@G@@   CONSOLE DEPOSIT POINTER    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@DOT      EQU       '.'--GV
)@@G@@' '   @ @@@@DASH     EQU       '-'--' '   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P        PROGW
)@@G@@C      0,1  @^@@@@UNGUARD* NAME      0    @^@@@@GUARD*   NAME      1    GX
)@@G@@@A@@@@         DO        P(0,0)=0 , ER 0  @B@@@@         DO        P(0,0GY
)@@G@@)=1 , LMJ X2,TON  @]@@@@         END@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P        PROC     GZ
)@@G@@ 1    @^@@@@ORG*     NAME      0    @G@@@@         DO        +(P(1,1)-$)HA
)@@G@@<0 ,A0 EQU 08+(GOO )+3*RETID+(LA 100)     @ @@@@         RES       P(1,1HB
)@@G@@)-$   @]@@@@         END@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P        PROC      0    @^@@@@HC
)@@G@@TAG*     NAME      0    @ @@@@*        EQU       $-O1000    @]@@@@      HD
)@@G@@   END@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P        PROC      1,1  @^@@@@SCN*     NAME     HE
)@@G@@ 0    @A@@@@         I$        072,014,,,,P(1,1)@]@@@@         END@[@@@@HF
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@S*       FUNC      .    @A@@@@         END       $-O1000+S(1HG
)@@G@@)     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@JKL*     PROC      1,2  @E@@@@         JK       HH
)@@G@@ JKL(1,1),S(2)       REMOVE THIS BIT ?    @B@@@@         ANA,U     A6,1*HI
)@@G@@/(JKL(1,1)-1)  YES@]@@@@         END@[@@@@.     @^@@@@M*       PROC     HJ
)@@G@@ *2   @^@@@@M$$1     NAME      0    @E@@@@         DO        +(M(2,1)**0HK
)@@G@@770000000000)<0 , GO M$$2     @A@@@@M(2,1)   EQU       +(M(2,1)*/6)+' ' HL
)@@G@@@^@@@@         GO        M$$1 @^@@@@M$$2*    NAME      0    @ @@@@CH$*(MHM
)@@G@@(1,1)) EQU   M(2,1)     @]@@@@         END@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P        PROHN
)@@G@@C      0,1  @^@@@@GEN*     NAME      0    @D@@@@         DO        CH$(IHO
)@@G@@-1)=0 ,CH$(I-1) EQU '      '  @B@@@@         +         CH$(I-1)--'      HP
)@@G@@'     @]@@@@         END@[@@@@.     @]@@@@$(1)     LIT@]@@@@O1000    .  HQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @]@@@@BOOT     TAG@E@@@@         SCN       A0+XR            HR
)@@G@@   SAVE BOOT CHANNEL    @F@@@@         LA        A0,040,A0           GETHS
)@@G@@ ACCESS WORD FROM BOOT  @G@@@@         SSL       A0,15               SHIHT
)@@G@@FT ALL BUT MODULE NUMBER OFF  @G@@@@         LSSL      A0,15            HU
)@@G@@   GET BACK BOOT MODULE ADDRESS     @E@@@@         LX,U      X1,,A0     HV
)@@G@@         MOVE IBANK BIAS TO X1@F@@@@         LSSL      A0,9             HW
)@@G@@   SHIFT IBANK BIAS TO BI     @D@@@@         LXM,U     A0,0177000       HX
)@@G@@   SET 65K BS     @D@@@@         LPS       A0+XR               LOAD UP NHY
)@@G@@EW PSR@D@@@@         NOP       5                   WAIT FOR IT    @F@@@@HZ
)@@G@@         LA        A14,A0+XR           GET GUARD MODE OFF PSR     @E@@@@IA
)@@G@@         AU        A14,K1S29           ADD GUARD MODE BIT   @E@@@@      IB
)@@G@@   LA,U      A13                 CLEAR MORSE MODE     @E@@@@         LA IC
)@@G@@       A0,LMJINS           GET TRAP INSTRUCTION @G@@@@         SA       ID
)@@G@@ A0,ISILOC           PUT IN ISI INTERRUPT LOCATION    @F@@@@         LA IE
)@@G@@       A12,K1CDW           LOAD CONSOLE ACCESS WORD   @D@@@@         AA IF
)@@G@@       A12,X1+XR           ADD BASING     @F@@@@         LR        CDP,KIG
)@@G@@1CDBUF         LOAD CONSOLE DATA POINTER  @F@@@@         SR        CDP,CIH
)@@G@@IP             INITIALIZE LOAD POINTER    @G@@@@         LA        A0,K3II
)@@G@@BIG            GET COUNT FOR SPEED DETERMINATION@D@@@@         LA,U     IJ
)@@G@@ SIX                 CLEAR 1106 FLAG@F@@@@         LR,U      R0,2500    IK
)@@G@@         GET RTC COUNT FOR TIMING   @E@@@@         JGD       A0,S(0)    IL
)@@G@@         WAIT FOR A WHILE     @D@@@@         LA        A0,R0            IM
)@@G@@   GET RTC COUNT  @E@@@@         LSSL      A0,18               GET SIGN IN
)@@G@@BIT AS FLAG @G@@@@         JP        A0,S(2)             1108 CAN FINISHIO
)@@G@@ IN ALLOTTED TIME @D@@@@         LA,U      SIX,1               1106 CANNIP
)@@G@@OT.   @F@@@@         LICM      15,A12              BRING UP CONSOLE INPUIQ
)@@G@@T     @F@@@@         LA,U      BITS,1              INITIALIZE BITS NON-ZIR
)@@G@@ERO   @F@@@@         LA        LENGTH,ISNRAT       GET INITIAL SENDING RIS
)@@G@@ATE   @D@@@@         TZ        SIX                 IS IT AN 1106 ?@F@@@@IT
)@@G@@         SSL       LENGTH,1            YES.  FUDGE SENDING RATE   @D@@@@IU
)@@G@@         AAIJ      IDLE                ENTER IDLE LOOP@[@@@@.     @]@@@@IV
)@@G@@NSI      TAG@G@@@@         LPS       X0                  RELOAD PSR AT IIW
)@@G@@NTERRUPT TIME     @D@@@@         AAIJ      0,X2                RETURN TOIX
)@@G@@ CODE @[@@@@.     @]@@@@TOFF     TAG@G@@@@         LPS       A14        IY
)@@G@@         RELOAD PSR WITH GUARD MODE OFF   @C@@@@         AAIJ      0,X2 IZ
)@@G@@               RETURN   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@TON      TAG@F@@@@         LPSJA
)@@G@@       A15                 LOAD GUARD MODE ON PSR     @C@@@@         AAIJB
)@@G@@J      0,X2                RETURN   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@TONE     TAG@E@@@@JC
)@@G@@         GUARD     .                   TURN ON GUARD MODE   @D@@@@      JD
)@@G@@   LR        R4,PITCH            GET PITCH CODE @D@@@@         JGD      JE
)@@G@@ R4,S(0)             WAIT WITH IT ON@E@@@@         UNGUARD   .          JF
)@@G@@         TURN OFF GUARD MODE  @E@@@@         LR        R4,PITCH         JG
)@@G@@   RELOAD PITCH CODE    @E@@@@         JGD       R4,S(0)             WAIJH
)@@G@@T WITH IT OFF     @E@@@@         JGD       A0,TONE             DO FOR TOJI
)@@G@@NAL DURATION@D@@@@         J         0,X11               RETURN TO CALL JJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@ISIIM    TAG@G@@@@         SCN       A6+XR            JK
)@@G@@   GET INTERRUPTING CHANNEL NUMBER  @E@@@@         TE,U      A6,15      JL
)@@G@@         IS IT THE CONSOLE ?  @F@@@@         PAIJ      NSI              JM
)@@G@@   NO.  IGNORE THE INTERRUPT  @F@@@@         LPS       A14              JN
)@@G@@   LOAD GUARD MODE OFF PSR    @G@@@@         NOP       8                JO
)@@G@@   ALLOW IT TO COME INTO EFFECT     @E@@@@         LA        A6,CDW     JP
)@@G@@         GET CONSOLE POINTER  @E@@@@         LX        X3,CDP           JQ
)@@G@@   GET CONSOLE POINTER  @F@@@@         TZ        A13                 AREJR
)@@G@@ WE IN MORSE MODE ?     @E@@@@         J         QCI                 YESJS
)@@G@@.  QUEUE INPUT    @E@@@@         LA,U      A13,1               NO.  SET JT
)@@G@@MORSE MODE  @F@@@@         SA        A6,,*X3             PUT CHARACTER IJU
)@@G@@N BUFFER    @D@@@@         SX        X3,CDP              UPDATE POINTER JV
)@@G@@@E@@@@         LICM      15,A12              BRING CONSOLE BACK UP@E@@@@JW
)@@G@@         AAIJ      MORSE               ENTER MORSE ROUTINE  @[@@@@.     JX
)@@G@@@]@@@@QCI      TAG@F@@@@         TNE,U     A6,'"'              IS IT ABOJY
)@@G@@RT CHARACTER ?    @G@@@@         PAIJ      ABORT               YES.  TERJZ
)@@G@@MINATE MORSE OUTPUT     @E@@@@         TE,U      A6,'#'              IS KA
)@@G@@IT NEW LINE ?     @F@@@@         TNE,U     A6,'^'              IS IT A CKB
)@@G@@ARRIAGE RETURN ?  @F@@@@         PAIJ      COMPUTE             YES.  COMKC
)@@G@@PUTE OUTPUT SPEED @F@@@@         SA        A6,,*X3             PUT CHARAKD
)@@G@@CTER IN BUFFER    @D@@@@         SX        X3,CDP              UPDATE POKE
)@@G@@INTER @]@@@@RTN      TAG@E@@@@         LICM      15,A12              BRIKF
)@@G@@NG INPUT BACK UP  @F@@@@         LX        X2,X2+XR            GET ADDREKG
)@@G@@SS OF INTERRUPT   @G@@@@         PAIJ      NSI                 RETURN TOKH
)@@G@@ INTERRUPTED INSTRUCTION@[@@@@.     @]@@@@ABORT    TAG@E@@@@         LA KI
)@@G@@       A0,K1CDBUF          RELOAD BUFFER POINTER@E@@@@         SA       KJ
)@@G@@ A0,CDP              PUT BACK IN BUFFER   @F@@@@         SA        A0,CIKK
)@@G@@P              RESET LOAD POINTER ALSO    @E@@@@         LA,U      A13  KL
)@@G@@               CLEAR MORSE MODE     @F@@@@         LICM      15,A12     KM
)@@G@@         RESET INPUT ACCESS WORD    @F@@@@         AAIJ      IDLE       KN
)@@G@@         ENTER IDLE SYNTHESIZER     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.        RECOMPUTEKO
)@@G@@ SPEED@[@@@@.     @]@@@@COMPUTE  TAG@D@@@@         LA,U      A6,1*/10-1 KP
)@@G@@         GET ONE BITS   @ @@@@I        DO        10 , JKL I @F@@@@      KQ
)@@G@@   MSI,U     A6,BSLENG           MULTIPLY BY BASE LENGTH    @D@@@@      KR
)@@G@@   TZ        SIX                 IS IT AN 1106 ?@E@@@@         SSL      KS
)@@G@@ A6,1                YES.  FUDGE LENGTH   @D@@@@         SA        A6,LEKT
)@@G@@NGTH           SAVE LENGTH    @H@@@@         PAIJ      RTN              KU
)@@G@@   BRING BACK INPUT, RETURN TO PROCESSING @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.        FEEKV
)@@G@@DBACK SHIFT REGISTER MUSIC SYNTHESIZER    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@IDLE     TAGKW
)@@G@@@E@@@@         LA        A0,K1SEC            ONE SECOND DELAY     @D@@@@KX
)@@G@@         JGD       A0,S(0)             WAIT A WHILE   @]@@@@IDLOOP   TAGKY
)@@G@@@E@@@@         LA        A0,BITS             GET CURRENT BITS     @E@@@@KZ
)@@G@@         AND,U     A0,1*/4             AND OFF FIFTH BIT    @E@@@@      LA
)@@G@@   LA        A2,A1               SAVE ANDED VALUE     @E@@@@         JNBLB
)@@G@@       A0,S(2)             SHIFTING OUT A BIT ? @E@@@@         XOR,U    LC
)@@G@@ A1,1*/4             YES.  FLIP FIFTH BIT @E@@@@         SSL       A0,1 LD
)@@G@@               SHIFT RIGHT ONE PLACE@E@@@@         JZ        A2,S(2)    LE
)@@G@@         ONE BIT TO SHIFT IN ?@F@@@@         AA,U      A0,1*/8          LF
)@@G@@   YES.  SHIFT IN THE BIT     @D@@@@         SA        A0,BITS          LG
)@@G@@   UPDATE BITS    @E@@@@         DSL       A0,36+5             ISOLATE HLH
)@@G@@IGH BITS    @G@@@@         LA,U      A0,SYNPTC           LOAD PITCH BASELI
)@@G@@ FOR SYNTHESISER  @E@@@@         AA,U      A1,1                INSURE BILJ
)@@G@@TS NOT ZERO @E@@@@         MSI       A0,A1               COMPUTE FINAL PLK
)@@G@@ITCH  @D@@@@         TZ        SIX                 IS IT AN 1106 ?@F@@@@LL
)@@G@@         SSL       A0,1                YES.  USE HALF THE COUNT   @D@@@@LM
)@@G@@         SA        A0,PITCH            SAVE PITCH     @E@@@@         LA,LN
)@@G@@U      A1,RATE             GET BASE RATE COUNT  @C@@@@         LA,U     LO
)@@G@@ A0                  CLEAR A0 @G@@@@         DI        A0,PITCH         LP
)@@G@@   COMPUTE NUMBER OF TIMES THRU LOOP@E@@@@         TZ        SIX        LQ
)@@G@@         ARE WE ON AN 1106 ?  @E@@@@         SSL       A0,1             LR
)@@G@@   YES.  HALVE THE COUNT@D@@@@         LMJ       X11,TONE            GENLS
)@@G@@ERATE TONE  @E@@@@         J         IDLOOP              COMPUTE NEXT TOLT
)@@G@@NE    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.        INTERRUPT LOCATIONS  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@LU
)@@G@@         ORG       0217                DAY CLOCK INTERRUPT  @C@@@@      LV
)@@G@@   LMJ       X2,NSI              IGNORE IT@E@@@@         ORG       0220 LW
)@@G@@               ISI INPUT MONITOR    @]@@@@ISILOC   TAG@G@@@@         NOPLX
)@@G@@       4                   SET TO IGNORE BOOT INTERRUPT     @E@@@@      LY
)@@G@@   ORG       0231                REAL TIME INTERRUPT  @C@@@@         LMJLZ
)@@G@@       X2,NSI              IGNORE IT@D@@@@         ORG       0242       MA
)@@G@@         ER INTERRUPT   @E@@@@         LMJ       X2,TOFF             TURMB
)@@G@@N OFF GUARD MODE  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@         ORG       0300 @[@@@@.     MC
)@@G@@@ @@@@.        MORSE CODE GENERATOR @[@@@@.     @]@@@@MORSE    TAG@E@@@@MD
)@@G@@         LA        A0,K1SEC            ONE SECOND DELAY     @F@@@@      ME
)@@G@@   JGD       A0,S(0)             MAKE TRANSITION GENTLE     @E@@@@      MF
)@@G@@   LA,U      A9                  CLEAR TIMEOUT COUNTER@F@@@@         LA,MG
)@@G@@U      A2,MPITCH           GET PITCH CODE FOR MORSE   @D@@@@         TZ MH
)@@G@@       SIX                 IS IT AN 1106 ?@G@@@@         SSL       A2,1 MI
)@@G@@               YES.  CUT LOOP COUNT IN HALF     @D@@@@         SA       MJ
)@@G@@ A2,PITCH            SET UP PITCH   @]@@@@MLOOP    TAG@E@@@@         JK MK
)@@G@@       14,S(0)             JK 14:  QUEUE INPUT  @E@@@@         PAIJ     ML
)@@G@@ S(1)                PREVENT INTERRUPTS   @E@@@@         LA        A0,CIMM
)@@G@@P              GET INPUT POINTER    @H@@@@         TNE       A0,CDP     MN
)@@G@@         IS IT EQUAL TO THE DEPOSIT POINTER ?   @F@@@@         AAIJ     MO
)@@G@@ EMPTY               YES.  NOTHING TO OUTPUT    @E@@@@         AAIJ     MP
)@@G@@ S(1)                ALLOW INTERRUPTS     @G@@@@         LA        A1,,*MQ
)@@G@@A0             GET THE NEXT CHARACTER TO OUTPUT @G@@@@         LA,U     MR
)@@G@@ A9                  CLEAR 'CHARACTER GET FAILED'     @E@@@@         SA MS
)@@G@@       A0,CIP              RESTORE INPUT POINTER@D@@@@         TNE,U    MT
)@@G@@ A1,' '              IS IT A SPACE ?@G@@@@         J         EWORD      MU
)@@G@@         YES.  GENERATE END-OF-WORD PAUSE @G@@@@         LA        A1,MTMV
)@@G@@ABL,A1         CONVERT FIELDATA TO MORSE CODE   @]@@@@MOLOOP   TAG@E@@@@MW
)@@G@@         LA,U      A0                  CLEAR 'DOT OR DASH'  @F@@@@      MX
)@@G@@   LDSL      A0,6                SHIFT NEXT CODE INTO A0    @G@@@@      MY
)@@G@@   JZ        A0,ELETTR           GO TO END OF LETTER PROCESSING   @D@@@@MZ
)@@G@@         TE,U      A0,DOT              IS IT A DOT ?  @E@@@@         J  NA
)@@G@@       DASHP               NO.  MUST BE A DASH  @E@@@@         LA       NB
)@@G@@ A0,LENGTH           GET MORSE TONE LENGTH@C@@@@         LMJ       X11,TNC
)@@G@@ONE            SOUND OFF@]@@@@EBIT     TAG@D@@@@         LA        A0,LEND
)@@G@@NGTH           GET LENGTH CODE@G@@@@         MSI,U     A0,MPITCH*2      NE
)@@G@@   COMPUTE EQUIVALENT LOOP COUNT FOR@G@@@@         JGD       A0,S(0)    NF
)@@G@@         ALLOW ONE TIME INTERVAL TO PASS  @F@@@@         J         MOLOONG
)@@G@@P              PROCESS NEXT DOT OR DASH   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@DASHP    TAGNH
)@@G@@@D@@@@         LA        A0,LENGTH           GET DOT LENGTH @F@@@@      NI
)@@G@@   MSI,U     A0,3                DASH IS THREE TIMES LONGER @D@@@@      NJ
)@@G@@   LMJ       X11,TONE            SEND THAT TONE @G@@@@         J        NK
)@@G@@ EBIT                JOIN PROCESSING FOR END-OF-BIT   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@NL
)@@G@@ELETTR   TAG@E@@@@         LA        A0,LENGTH           GET BASIC LENGTNM
)@@G@@H     @F@@@@         MSI,U     A0,3*MPITCH*2       GET DASH'S WORTH OF SNN
)@@G@@ILENCE@G@@@@         JGD       A0,S(0)             ALLOW THAT MUCH TIME NO
)@@G@@TO PASS     @E@@@@         J         MLOOP               GET NEXT CHARACNP
)@@G@@TER   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@EWORD    TAG@E@@@@         LA        A0,LENGTH  NQ
)@@G@@         GET BASIC LENGTH     @F@@@@         MSI,U     A0,6*MPITCH*2    NR
)@@G@@   GET TWO DASHES OF LENGTH   @F@@@@         JGD       A0,S(0)          NS
)@@G@@   TWO DASHES BETWEEN WORDS   @F@@@@         J         MLOOP            NT
)@@G@@   PROCESS NEXT CHARACTER     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@EMPTY    TAG@F@@@@      NU
)@@G@@   AA,U      A9,1                BUMP NUMBER OF FAILURES    @D@@@@      NV
)@@G@@   TLE       A9,K5BIG            IDLE TOO LONG ?@D@@@@         J        NW
)@@G@@ MLOOP               NO.  TRY AGAIN @E@@@@         JK        14,S(2)    NX
)@@G@@         IGNORE TIMEOUT ?     @F@@@@         PAIJ      ABORT            NY
)@@G@@   NO.  GO BACK TO SYNTHESIZER@D@@@@         LA,U      A9               NZ
)@@G@@   CLEAR TIMEOUT  @E@@@@         J         MLOOP               ENTER MOROA
)@@G@@SE MODE.    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.        MORSE TABLE INITIALIZATION @[@@@@OB
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@.        REF. ARRL HANDBOOK, 1950 EDITION @[@@@@.     @ @@@@OC
)@@G@@         M         'A' '.-'   @ @@@@         M         'B' '-...' @ @@@@OD
)@@G@@         M         'C' '-.-.' @ @@@@         M         'D' '-..'  @ @@@@OE

)@@G@@         M         'Q' '--.-' @ @@@@         M         'R' '.-.'  @ @@@@OL

)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.        FIELDATA TO MORSE CODE CONVERSION TABLE@[@@@@.     OZ
)@@G@@@]@@@@MTABL    TAG@ @@@@I        DO        64 , GEN   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@PA
)@@G@@CDBUF    EQU       02000               START OF CONSOLE DATA@]@@@@CDW   PB
)@@G@@   TAG@F@@@@         *         0                   DATA WORD FOR CONSOLEPC
)@@G@@ INPUT@]@@@@K1S29    TAG@^@@@@         *         1*/29@]@@@@LMJINS   TAGPD
)@@G@@@ @@@@         LMJ       X2,ISIIM   @]@@@@K1CDW    TAG@^@@@@         *  PE
)@@G@@       1,CDW@]@@@@K1CDBUF  TAG@ @@@@         *         1,CDBUF    @]@@@@PF
)@@G@@K3BIG    TAG@ @@@@         *         300000     @]@@@@ISNRAT   TAG@A@@@@PG
)@@G@@         *         BSLENG*(1*/3)    @]@@@@K1SEC    TAG@ @@@@         *  PH
)@@G@@       1250000    @]@@@@K5BIG    TAG@ @@@@         *         500000     PI
)@@G@@@G@@@@         ORG       01777               INSURE ENOUGH CORE ALLOCATEPJ
)@@G@@D     @[@@@@$(2). @E@@@@WRITE    LA,U      A0,WRPKT            LOAD PACKPK

)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@DATA.                                 . MUSIC GOES HERTT
)@@G@@E     @^@@@@. MARY HAD A LITTLE LAMB@C@@@@       GEN   E D C D E E E,2 DTU

)@@G@@G B B B B A B C2 G C2   @[@@@@$(2). @^@@@@NOTES2 EQU     $-DATA2  @[@@@@UL
)@@G@@$(0). @^@@@@NOTES1 EQU     $-DATA1  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@NOTE   EQUF    0,XUM
)@@G@@9,H1                . WORD COUNT FOR NOTE @E@@@@TIME   EQUF    0,*X9,H2 UN
)@@G@@              . DURATION OF NOTE    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@TABLE  +       'C UO
)@@G@@ ',C                . LEGAL NOTES FOR DATA CARDS@^@@@@       +       'CSUP

)@@G@@ +       'GS ',GS @^@@@@       +       'AF ',AF @^@@@@       +       'A UU
