)@@G@@          YES.  SET MEMORY CHARGE AS SORT KEY   @G@@@N          SA      OG
)@@G@@  A0,CBSUPS           SET MEMORY TIME IN SORT RECORD  @G@@@N          LAOH
)@@G@@        A0,LGI+8            LOAD NET CC/ER TIME FOR PROGRAM @E@@@N      OI
)@@G@@    TEP       A6,(OPTION('E'))    SORT BY CC/ER TIME ?@G@@@N          LAOJ
)@@G@@        A5,A0               YES.  SET CC/ER AS SORT KEY     @G@@@N      OK
)@@G@@    SA        A0,CCER             SET CC/ER TIME IN SORT RECORD   @E@@@NOL
)@@G@@          LA        A0,LGI+19           LOAD TOTAL SUP'S    @F@@@N      OM
)@@G@@    SA        A0,SUPTIME          SET TOTAL SUPS IN ITEM    @E@@@N      ON
)@@G@@    ANA       A0,CPUTIME          SUBTRACT CPU TIME   @F@@@N          ANOO
)@@G@@A       A0,CCER             SUBTRACT CC/ER CHARGES    @G@@@N          TPOP
)@@G@@        A0                  HAS I/O TIME GONE NEGATIVE ?    @E@@@N      OQ
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0                  YES.  SET IT TO ZERO@E@@@N          SAOR
)@@G@@        A0,IOT              SET I/O TIME IN ITEM@E@@@N          TEP     OS
)@@G@@  A6,(OPTION('I'))    SORT BY I/O TIME ?  @G@@@N          LA        A5,AOT
)@@G@@0               YES.  SET I/O TIME AS SORT KEY  @F@@@N          SA      OU
)@@G@@  A5,SKEY             SET SORT KEY IN RECORD    @[@@@N.     @F@@@N      OV
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,SORTREC          LOAD SORT RECORD ADDRESS  @G@@@N      OW
)@@G@@    R$REL     .                   PASS THE RECORD TO THE SORT     @F@@@NOX
)@@G@@          J         RELREC              GO RELEASE THE NEXT RECORD@[@@@NOY
)@@G@@.     @D@@@N.         SORT OUTPUT PROCEDURE FOR SORT BY NAMES     @[@@@NOZ
)@@G@@.     @G@@@NRETREC    R$RET     RETEND.             RETURN A RECORD FROMPA
)@@G@@ THE SORT   @H@@@N          LA,U      A14                 CLEAR LOWER WOPB

)@@G@@          DTE       A1,VERNAME          SAME AS VERSION OF LAST ITEM ?  PJ
)@@G@@@G@@@N          J         RETBRK              NO.  THIS IS A DIFFERENT PPK
)@@G@@ROGRAM@G@@@N          LR,U      R1,SRNACM-1         LOAD ACCUMULATOR COUPL
)@@G@@NT IN RECORD@G@@@N          LX,U      A1,4,A0             LOAD ACCUMULATPM

)@@G@@.         OUTPUT THE TOTAL RECORD TO THE INTERMEDIATE FILE WHEN   @F@@@NPX
)@@G@@.         A SEQUENCE BREAK IS ENCOUNTERED IN THE SORTED-BY-NAMES  @#@@@NPY
)@@G@@.         FILE.   @[@@@N.     @G@R@N.                   (JEEZ, IF YOU CAPZ
)@@G@@N TALK LIKE THAT THEY SHOULD GIVE   @E@R@N.                    YOU A CDPQA
)@@G@@ JUST FOR SHEER BULLSHITTING).@[@R@N.     @F@@@NRETEND    LA,U      A0,1QB

)@@G@@@[@@@R.     @#@@@R.         PHASE 2 @[@@@R.     @H@@@R.         THE SUMMQY
)@@G@@ARY RECORDS PREPARED IN PHASE 1, WHICH CONTAIN THE TOTAL    @G@@@R.     QZ

)@@G@@*A0             COPY RECORD TO CANNED ITEM@[@@@N.     @[@@@N.     @C@@@NTF

)@@G@@RMINATE     @[@@@N.     @[@@@N.     @ @@@N.         RETURN CAU TIME     UZ
)@@G@@@[@@@N.     @G@@@N.         THIS SUBROUTINE IS CALLED WITH THE TWO STORAVA
)@@G@@GE REFERENCE COUNT@H@@@N.         WORDS AND RETURNS THE CAU TIME FOR A RVB
)@@G@@UN.  IF CALLED ON AN 1106/8,  @G@@@N.         IT SIMPLY RETURNS THE MEASVC
)@@G@@URED CAU TIME.  IT DETECTS THE TYPE @G@@@N.         OF MACHINE FROM THE VD
)@@G@@CONVENTION THAN THE EXTENDED STORAGE SRC'S@B@@@N.         IS ALWAYS -0 FVE
)@@G@@OR AN 1106/1108.  @[@@@N.     @G@@@N.         DL        A0,SRCWD        VF
)@@G@@    A0 = PS SRC'S, A1 = ES SRC'S    @ @@@N.         LMJ       X11,SRCSUPVG
)@@G@@@F@@@N.         <RETURN>                      A0 =  CAU TIME IN 5000'THSVH
)@@G@@@[@@@N.     @I@@@NSRCSUP    TNZ       A1                  IS EXTENDED STVI

)@@G@@    YES.  IF NEGATIVE IT'S AN EON MACHINE @G@@@N          AA        A0,AVK

)@@G@@  A0,1000             MULTIPLY BY SCALE FACTOR FOR SRCINST  @I@@@N      VM
)@@G@@    DI,U      A0,SRCINST          COMPUTE NUMBER OF INSTRUCTIONS EXECUTEVN

)@@G@@TURN CAU TIME TO CALLER @[@@@N.     @[@@@N.     @F@@@N.         THIS SUBVR
)@@G@@ROUTINE EDITS SUP'S (IN A0) TO HH:MM:SS.DDD     @[@@@N.     @D@@@NSUPED VS
)@@G@@    J         $-$                 ENTRY / EXIT  @F@@@N          TNZ     VT
)@@G@@  HOURS               EDITING TIMES IN HOURS ?  @E@@@N          J       VU
)@@G@@  SUPSEC              NO.  EDIT IN SECONDS@D@@@N          DSL       A0,3VV
)@@G@@6               MOVE TO A1    @D@@@N          DI        A0,(5000*60*60) VW
)@@G@@    A0 = HOURS    @D@@@N          JZ        A0,NOHRS            SKIP IF VX
)@@G@@ZERO  @D@@@N          F$DECV    .                   EDIT HOURS    @D@@@NVY

)@@G@@,U      A0                  CLEAR A0@D@@@N          DI        A0,(5000*6WA
)@@G@@0)        A0 = MINUTES  @E@@@N          JZ        A0,NOMINS           SKWB
)@@G@@IP IF NO MINUTES  @D@@@N          F$DECV    .                   EDIT MINWC

)@@G@@NOMINS    LA,U      A0                  CLEAR A0@D@@@N          DI,U    WE

)@@G@@          F$SKIP    -5                  BACK UP OVER IT     @D@@@N      WJ

)@@G@@  3                   SKIP TO LAST DIGIT  @D@@@N          F$CHAR    ' ' WL
)@@G@@                OBSCURE IT    @E@@@N          J         SUPED           WM
)@@G@@    RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@N.     @A@@@N.         EDIT TIME IN SSSS.DDWN
)@@G@@D     @[@@@N.     @G@@@NSUPSEC    DSL       A0,36               SHIFT DOWO
)@@G@@WN SUP'S INTO TWO WORDS @E@@@N          LDSL      A0,1                MUWP
)@@G@@LTIPLY BY TWO     @H@@@N          DI,U      A0,10000            COMPUTE WQ
)@@G@@SECONDS AND TEN THOUSANDTHS   @G@@@N          SA        A1,A3           WR

)@@G@@          EDIT SECONDS  @E@@@N          LA,U      A0,10000,A3         LOWT
)@@G@@AD TEN THOUSANDTHS@F@@@N          F$DECV    .                   EDIT WITWU
